ng ingredients. Blend until smooth. Place the pot on low-medium heat so the soup will be warm for serving.?#&?#&Now, take a baquette and make 1/2 inch or smaller slices. Coat them in olive oil on both sides. Grill the crostini on indirect heat until toasted, about 2 minutes each side. Remove from grill and layer crostini, cheese, meat, peppers, and arugula and repeat, sandwiching a crostini on each each. Stick a skewer in through the middle to keep the pieces together. Serve with the soup for a sassy presentation that is perfect for dipping in the soup!?#&?#&Alas, this is one of those recipes that I just made that turned out wonderfully. I love those redeeming recipes that come out so great, to make up for the ones that don’t. I hope you enjoy!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'FF6E328DFC23D44E9488797D1B1E0B66', X'CFD8DC56ABCFFD4D876EE48FA752DEEE', X'CFD8DC56ABCFFD4D876EE48FA752DEEE', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/04/cedar-planked-beets-with-goat-cheese-and-balsamic-glaze/', 'Cedar Planked Beets with Goat Cheese and Balsamic Glaze', 2, NULL, 0, 'Cedar Planked Beets with Goat Cheese and Balsamic Glaze', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/IMG_6211-150x150.jpg', '', '', '20 minutes', '20 minutes', '40 minutes', '8', 'Ingredients?#&?#&2 cedar wood planks, soaked in water?#&6 medium sized beets, skin removed?#&Zest of one orange?#&2 tbsp balsamic glaze?#&1 tbsp olive oil?#&½ teaspoon sea salt?#&1 teaspoon fresh ground pepper?#&4 oz goat cheese (you can use cold smoked goat cheese on page x or regular)?#&1 tsp fresh thyme', 'American', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/04/cedar-planked-beets-with-goat-cheese-and-balsamic-glaze/', 'boil, smoked', 'smoked beets, cedar planked beets', 'Apr 27, 2020', 'veggies, American', 'Instructions?#&?#&Boil the beets for 20-30 minutes until they are tender enough for a fork to slightly pierce the flesh.?#&While the beets are boiling, soak the wood planks. Let the beets slightly cool and slice into 1/8” pieces and place on the cedar planks.?#&Drizzle with olive oil and then add the orange zest, salt and pepper.?#&Smoke for 1 hour or until the beet slices can be easily pierced with a fork.?#&Crumble goat cheese on the beets and then drizzle with balsamic glaze. Sprinkle with fresh thyme.?#&?#&Beets can be served as is on the cedar planks when serving as a side, or added to a salad.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'BFC6D0FCDE3E6D43876767D9973CB22C', X'991AC354DD53FB4085E08310DD5BA8EE', X'991AC354DD53FB4085E08310DD5BA8EE', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2017/11/blueberry-peach-cobbler-pitbarrel-cooker/', 'Blueberry Peach Cobbler on the PitBarrel Cooker', 2, NULL, 0, 'Blueberry Peach Cobbler on the PitBarrel Cooker', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/blueberry-peach-cobbler-pbc-logo-visible-EDITED-150x100.jpg', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Ingredients?#&?#&4 peaches, diced?#&1 1/2 cups of blueberries?#&1/4 cup honey?#&1 dash each: nutmeg, cinnamon, allspice?#&1 tbsp lemon zest (lemon really brightens the flavor of the fruit in any dish)?#&jiffy cake mix?#&1 egg?#&1/2 cup water?#&1 tbsp coconut oil or butter to oil cast iron pan', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2017/11/blueberry-peach-cobbler-pitbarrel-cooker/', '', '', 'Nov 4, 2017', '', 'Instructions?#&?#&Combine fruit, honey, spices and lemon zest in one bowl and let macerate. In the meantime, combine the egg and water with the jiffy cake mix.?#&?#&Coat your 12” cast iron pan with butter or coconut oil so that none of your ingredients stick. Next, add your batter on top. Take a fork and spoon and lightly mix the fruit with the batter so that some of the fruit is visible (don’t mix too much- this is a rustic cobbler).?#&?#&Cook on your PitBarrel that has a hot fire going for about 30 minutes or until the fruit has begun to bubble and the batter has browned on the top. Depending on how hot your PBC is and how much charcoal is left, this may take up to 45 minutes.?#&?#&Serve with vanilla ice cream or fresh whipped cream. Delish and super easy!! If you love cobbler, I have a ton of cobbler recipes including a mango ginger cobbler and my Red, White and Blue cobbler that are always a big hit!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'C949EE9ABFD485438E76CCB8288A159A', X'2D1D819C2C13364E926E47A9DBFDD31F', X'2D1D819C2C13364E926E47A9DBFDD31F', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2017/06/bourbon-coke-braised-smoked-short-ribs-pit-barrel-cooker/', 'Bourbon and Coke Braised Short Ribs on the Pit Barrel Cooker', 2, NULL, 0, 'Bourbon and Coke Braised and Smoked Short Ribs on the Pit Barrel Cooker', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/beef-short-ribs-on-the-pit-barrel-cooker-edited-1-1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'INGREDIENTS?#&?#&2 Cups of KC Masterpiece Classic BBQ Sauce (or BBQ sauce of your choice)?#&1 Cup of Honey?#&2 TBSP Beef and Game Pit Rub', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2017/06/bourbon-coke-braised-smoked-short-ribs-pit-barrel-cooker/', '', '', 'Jun 18, 2017', '', 'Instructions?#&?#&Remove ribs from the package, peel off the thick membrane (or “silver”as it’s sometime called) that covers the back side of each rib. Trim off any silver skin or excess fat. Rinse gently with cold water and pat dry with paper towel.?#&Season the ribs with a moderate dusting of the beef and game pit rub to all sides of the ribs, then add ½ TBSP of mustard to each rib and massage into the meat.?#&Light your Pit Barrel Cooker (PBC) according to the instructions. Add your wood chips for smoke (I used cherry wood).?#&Oil the grill grate so the meat will not stick. Place the ribs on the grate bone side down. Cook until you reach an internal temperature of 165 degrees using an internal read instant (I recommend using the Thermapen). Approximately 1 ½ hours depending on the weather conditions.?#&Remove the ribs from the grate and put in an aluminum pan that fits your grate. Pour 2 cups of Coca Cola and 1/8 cup of bourbon into the pan. Cover the pan with aluminum foil, return to the PBC, and cook two more hours. Remove the ribs from the pan. Glaze the ribs with the sweet BBQ glaze. (See recipe below) Don’t overdo the sauce – use just enough to coat the ribs. Put the ribs back on the PBC and cook for 10 to 15 minutes. Just enough to set the glaze.?#&Remove the ribs from the PBC and let the ribs sit. Loosely covered with aluminum foil for 10 to 15 minutes. Then chow down.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'79409C91E8550E4DBD73BD3DE6C1933A', X'1D3D8094B536A242A239F7CA5188CE25', X'1D3D8094B536A242A239F7CA5188CE25', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2017/04/beef-jerky-pit-barrel-cooker/', 'Beef Jerky on the Pit Barrel Cooker', 2, NULL, 0, 'Beef Jerky on the Pit Barrel Cooker', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/beefjerkyonpitbarrell1-150x101.jpg', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Ingredients?#&?#&• 2 lbs beef- Use Top Round, Eye Round or Flank Steak- (jerky meat should be lean with minimal fat)?#&• 1/3 cup Tamari?#&• 1/2 tbsp sea salt?#&• 1 tbsp course ground pepper?#&• 4 garlic cloves?#&• 1 tsp onion powder?#&• 1 tsp smoked paprika?#&• 1/2 tsp apple cider vinegar?#&• 1 tsp agave syrup?#&?#&Additional Materials?#&?#&• 12 skewers?#&• Charcoal?#&• Wood for smoking- I recommend pecan, hickory or cherry', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2017/04/beef-jerky-pit-barrel-cooker/', '', '', 'Apr 15, 2017', '', 'Instructions?#&?#&Overview?#&?#&Marinate the meat overnight, or for a minimum of 8 hours for maximum flavor. On the grill, the meat is going to hang on skewers to be as far away from the flame as possible and then transition to the grates at the end to ensure all pieces are fully dehydrated over the course of the cook.?#&?#&Directions?#&?#&Combine all the ingredients for the marinade, then pulse with a stick blender/immersion blender to fully mix all ingredients together and chop the fresh garlic.?#&Slice the meat into 1/4” slices, removing all fat. Cut it in half so each strip is no longer than 5 inches in length and no longer than 4 inches in width.?#&In large gallon zip lock bags, add the meat and the marinade and let marinate in the fridge overnight.?#&?#&After removing from the fridge?#&?#&Double up the skewers so that each piece is hanging from two skewers. The double skewers ensure the weight of the meat doesn’t cause the skewer to break. Make sure the meat pieces are not touching each other. Leave enough room on each end (approximately 4 inches) of the skewer so that there is room to hang on the rods of the PBC.?#&Fill less than half of a standard chimney starter with Kingsford Charcoal and ignite it. Don’t let it get fully lit- only 3/4 of the way. Dump the charcoal into the Charcoal Ring and move it to one side.?#&On the opposite side of the charcoal, hang your skewers on the rods suspending your jerky above the unlit/indirect side of the charcoal.?#&Add your preferred wood to the fire.?#&Let the jerky smoke for 2 hours (lid closed), watching it very closely the ENTIRE time. The skewers closest to the flame will need to be rotated to the other end of the barrel so they do not overcook. Add charcoal briquettes as needed to maintain the fire but never letting it get too big or hot.?#&**If using lump charcoal, use the same amount of charcoal in the starter. However, you can use a spray bottle and mist the lump if it is getting too hot. This cannot be done with Kingsford as it gets sandy/mushy.?#&After the jerky has dehydrated and cooked down- approximately two hours or so, some pieces may still have “wet spots” or areas that may have touched others or haven’t fully dehydrated. At this point, remove the jerky and rods and add the grate. Remove the jerky pieces and lay on the grate on the indirect side. Some pieces may already be done and will not need this final step.?#&Let these remaining pieces continue to dehydrate on indirect until there are no “wet” parts left on the jerky, this will be a manual process- keep an eye on your PBC! This could take 30 minutes to an hour.?#&Once all “wet” spots are dehydrated and the jerky has reduced in size and is firm yet still flexible, it is ready to eat.?#&?#&Store in the refrigerator for maximum freshness- the jerky will last a few weeks. Enjoy!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'66D82B0017F7604E9EEE35A8B139F4F7', X'2E4B332D8AB02E468E281FEBAA1DD229', X'2E4B332D8AB02E468E281FEBAA1DD229', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2013/04/bbq-sriracha-chicken-wings-on-the-pit-barrel-cooker/', 'Sriracha BBQ Chicken Wings on the Pit Barrel Cooker', 2, NULL, 0, 'Sriracha BBQ Chicken Wings on the Pit Barrel Cooker', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Wings-on-the-Pit-Barrel-Smoker-150x150.jpg', '', '', '25 min', '30 min', '55 minutes', '4', 'Ingredients?#&?#&20 Chicken Drummettes (or “wings” if you prefer, I’m a “drummette” person)?#&Pit Barrel Cooker All Purpose Pit Rub OR a BBQ rub that doesn’t have sugar?#&1/2 cup (or more) of BBQ Sauce?#&2 tbsp Sriracha', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2013/04/bbq-sriracha-chicken-wings-on-the-pit-barrel-cooker/', 'Grilled', 'Sriracha BBQ Wings, Chicken Drummettes, Spicy BBQ sauce, Pit Barrel Cooker recipe, charcoal chicken wings, wings glaze', 'Apr 13, 2013', 'Chicken Wings', 'Instructions?#&?#&Rinse the chicken wings and pat dry. Generously sprinkle the wings with BBQ rub.?#&Next, combine the BBQ sauce and Sriracha hot sauce to form a glaze.?#&Prepare the Pit Barrel smoker for grilling (this includes lighting the charcoal and letting it heat up for about 20-25 minutes).?#&Put the wings on the grill and let them cook with the lid on for 20 minutes.?#&Flip the wings, and coat with the glaze and let them continue to cook for another 10 minutes or until the internal temp (I recommend using the instant read Thermapen) reads 170 degrees.?#&Tent the wings for 10 minutes under foil before serving.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'CF510E996A30254BB8304E08C73C5C40', X'03A5571BCB761446A9B1F6CBD23DE64F', X'03A5571BCB761446A9B1F6CBD23DE64F', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/08/rum-pineapple-pork-ribs-recipe-sweet-and-tangy/', 'Rum Pineapple Pork Ribs are Sweet and Tangy', 2, NULL, 0, 'Rum Pineapple Pork Ribs are Sweet and Tangy', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/rum-pineapple-ribs-150x150.jpeg', '', '', '20 minutes', '5 hours', '5 hours 20 minutes', '', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 slab baby back ribs?#&Mustard?#&3 tbsp smoked all purpose rub ?#&1 pineapple, cored and sliced into 1/2” rings – should make about 9 rings total – 3 of which are used in the sauce, save juice for sauce (if using canned look for a corn syrup free, reduced sugar version)?#&?#&Texas Crutch?#&?#&1/4 cup apple juice?#&2 tbsp pineapple preserves?#&?#&Pineapple Rum BBQ Sauce?#&?#&1/3 cup BBQ sauce or your favorite store bought variety?#&3 tbsp pineapple preserves?#&1/4 cup Myers rum?#&3 tbsp pineapple juice?#&Dash allspice?#&3 slice pineapple, chopped', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/08/rum-pineapple-pork-ribs-recipe-sweet-and-tangy/', '2-2-1 Method', 'pork ribs, baby back ribs, 2-2-1 ribs, smoked BBQ ribs, texas crutch, pork ribs recipe', 'Aug 29, 2019', 'Pork Ribs', 'Instructions?#&?#&Smoke Temp: 225F?#&?#&Smoking Woods: FRUIT WOODS- (apple, pecan, pear) OR mix with OAK, PECAN, MAPLE?#&?#&The ribs are going to use the 2-2-1 method: 2 hours in the smoker, 2 hours in foil, 1 hour letting the sauce glaze.?#&?#&Start by removing the membrane from the ribs. This is easier with a paper towel for gripping and a butter knife for separating from the meat.?#&Prepare your smoker for 225 degrees- this recipe can be made on any kind of smoker (and was originally created for my Healthy Electric Smoker Cookbook).?#&Next, slather with mustard so the rub can adhere. Apply the rub and smoke the meat for 2 hours.?#&After 2 hours, remove from the smoker and do the “Texas Crutch,” i.e., “wrap in foil”. Mix the apple juice and pineapple preserve and add to the foil packet. Let smoke another two hours.?#&Meanwhile, as the meat is smoking make your rum barbecue sauce. Combine the BBQ sauce, pineapple preserves, rum, chopped pineapple, pineapple juice and allspice. Let reduce down for 20 minutes on medium simmer.?#&During the last hour, remove the ribs from foil and glaze with the pineapple rum BBQ sauce.?#&Layer slices of pineapple on top of the ribs and drizzle more sauce over the pineapple.?#&Let smoke for an additional hour to let the sauce set. Serve immediately.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'D9A0709F04063442882072E345C05B2D', X'30C9A2C65A32014E82D45A5FA8FE185C', X'30C9A2C65A32014E82D45A5FA8FE185C', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/01/top-5-keto-friendly-apps-for-the-super-bowl/', 'Top 5 Keto Friendly Apps for the Super Bowl', 2, NULL, 0, 'Bacon Jalapeno Deviled EggsINSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'5BEBBE4EFA2DF84380EDCE717613B3D1', X'0D9A3D4D32C92E40BEB25595179B58FA', X'0D9A3D4D32C92E40BEB25595179B58FA', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/01/pellet-grill-smoke-roasted-wings/', 'Pellet Grill Smoke Roasted Wings', 2, NULL, 0, 'Pellet Grill Smoke Roasted Wings', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/AdobeStock_289056237-150x150.jpg', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Preparation for smoke roasted wings is as simple as can be. I prepare mine with:?#&?#&a dash of salt,?#&a dash of pepper?#&Garlic Mix: consists of 4 parts Kosher salt, 2 parts restaurant grind black pepper and 1 part granulated garlic.', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/01/pellet-grill-smoke-roasted-wings/', '', '', 'Jan 30, 2019', '', 'Instructions?#&?#&(30 minutes at 225 degrees)?#&(30-50 minuts at 350 – roast until internal temp is at least 165 degrees)?#&?#&Get your pellet smoker running and up to 225°F. Use whatever flavor wood pellets you enjoy.?#&?#&Load up your wings.  This is the smoking part. Your pellet grill will impart more smoke flavor at a lower temp.?#&?#&Smoke these wings at 225° for about 30 minutes.?#&?#&Take your pellet grill temperature up to 350°F for the roasting step.  This high temperature will crisp up the skin and render out the fat that’s in the wings.  This step will take 30-50 minutes.  I know that’s a wide gap but BBQ and grilling is more by temperature than time.  You will want to cook these wings until they have an internal temperature of at least 165°f.  Be sure you use a good instant read thermometer like a Themapen or thermopop from ThermoWorks!  I like to take my wings up to 170°-180°.  The added temp really helps give a nice texture to the skin.?#&?#&As your wings start to approach your finish temperature be ready to take them off as they finish.  There’s a good chance some will finish before others due to their inconsistent size.?#&?#&Place them in a pan and keep that covered in foil.?#&?#&Once done you wings are ready to enjoy as is or dressed up with a multitude of sauces.  BBQ, teriyaki, Buffalo style and on and on. The only limit is your imagination.  Now go get yourself some wings and get that pellet grill started!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'01F199974310284C9BD22C3F432B36FB', X'6F24D4FAFFF50543A33A89C7114F9139', X'6F24D4FAFFF50543A33A89C7114F9139', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2018/07/kingsford-premium-wood-pellets-review/', 'Kingsford Premium Wood Pellets Review', 2, NULL, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2018/07/kingsford-premium-wood-pellets-review/', '', '', 'Jul 23, 2018', '', '');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'7FE0B468F647F64A87F9B496C72EF8B0', X'E2653FB4FAE5CF45BC848E290A395791', X'E2653FB4FAE5CF45BC848E290A395791', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2018/04/pellet-smoker-sheet-pan-dinner-smoked-chicken-thighs-with-maple-thyme-glazed-delicata-squash/', 'Sheet Pan Dinner: Chicken Thighs with Glazed Delicata Squash', 2, NULL, 0, 'Pellet Smoker Sheet Pan Dinner: Smoked Chicken Thighs with Maple Thyme Glazed Delicata Squash', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/sheet-pan-chicken-and-delicata-squash-green-mountain-grillJPG-150x150.jpg', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 18 X 12″ (half) sheet pan?#&1 lb boneless chicken thighs?#&2 tbsp smoked paprika?#&1 tbsp sea salt (such as maldon, French grey, smoked, etc)?#&1 tbsp of fresh ground pepper?#&¾ lb delicate squash?#&1/2 lb turnips?#&A few sprigs of fresh thyme, leaves removed from stems OR ½ tsp dried thyme?#&2 tbsp maple syrup', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2018/04/pellet-smoker-sheet-pan-dinner-smoked-chicken-thighs-with-maple-thyme-glazed-delicata-squash/', '', '', 'Apr 5, 2018', '', 'Instructions?#&?#&Rinse the veggies before slicing. Using a mandolin, slice the turnips and delicate squash with the largest slice setting on a mandolin- about 1/4″ thick. It is important to use a mandolin so that the veggies are sliced thinly and uniformly.?#&Set your pellet smoker for 350 degrees, smoking setting. Ie, vents are set for maximum ventilation.?#&Line a 12″ X 18” sheet pan with parchment or foil (parchment is better for the environment).?#&Arrange the chicken on one side of the pan, and then lay out the squash and turnips. Sprinkle the chicken with the smoked paprika.?#&Sprinkle all ingredients with the salt and pepper and thyme. Drizzle the squash with the maple syrup.?#&Smoke the sheet pan dinner at 350 degrees, for 30 minutes, or until the chicken has reached an internal temperature of 170 degrees. I recommend using a Thermapen internal read thermometer.?#&?#&Serve immediately- easy peasy! The beauty of this recipe is that it combines the simplicity of the “sheet pan dinner” with the great flavor and ease of use of the Green Mountain Grill Pellet Smoker. If you can make it in your oven, you can easily make it in your pellet smoker!!?#&?#&Note: This recipe was produced in partnership with Green Mountain Grills. I only work with companies I use and endorse. Thanks!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'13EFD90148AE1448A5FE9C458CCBA502', X'6B9C0AFA0227DB4588E1B4928248EE7F', X'6B9C0AFA0227DB4588E1B4928248EE7F', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2017/12/lemongrass-cilantro-garlic-grilled-chicken-wings/', 'Lemongrass, Cilantro & Garlic Grilled Chicken Wings', 2, NULL, 0, 'Lemongrass, Cilantro & Garlic Grilled Chicken Wings', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Sri-lankan-chicken-wings-up-close-EDITED-150x150.jpg', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'ingredients for marinade)', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2017/12/lemongrass-cilantro-garlic-grilled-chicken-wings/', '', '', 'Dec 8, 2017', '', 'Instructions?#&?#&The making of the spice paste!?#&?#&Combine olive oil, lemongrass/or zest, cilantro, garlic, turmeric, sea salt and pepper in the food processor and pulse until uniformly mixed- you are looking to make a seasoning “paste”. Next, reserve about 2 tbsp of the marinade to drizzle before serving. Marinate the chicken wings for 30 minutes before putting on the grill.?#&?#&Prepare your grill for medium direct heat at 350 degrees. I used my Green Mountain Grill Pellet Smoker and set it for 375 degrees with the smoker holes wide open. Grill your wings, turning halfway during the process, for approximately 15-18 minutes OR until the internal temperature has reached 170 degrees with an internal read thermometer.?#&?#&The Chicken wings on the Green Mountain Grill.?#&?#& ?#&?#&The Chicken wings on the Green Mountain Grill.?#&?#&Once you’ve reached 170 degrees (I recommend using an internal read thermometer such as the thermapen to check internal temp), pull the wings off and drizzle with the remaining marinade. Prepare for out of this world flavor combination! Enjoy!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'E52D3D0731834F44A7087E7D45D3A0F5', X'D3118DF24F073B48A3EAC6CE34CDE877', X'D3118DF24F073B48A3EAC6CE34CDE877', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2017/09/smoked-watermelon-gazpacho/', 'Smoked Watermelon Gazpacho', 2, NULL, 0, 'Smoked Watermelon Gazpacho', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/smoked-watermelon-gazpacho-green-mountain-grills-edited-150x150.jpg', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Produce:?#&?#&1/2 large watermelon, sliced in wedges?#&3 large cucumbers, skinned and sliced lengthwise?#&1 lb mini bell peppers?#&2 medium sized shallots?#&5 cloves garlic, put them on a skewer so they don’t fall through the grill grates?#&4 medium beefsteak tomatoes, cut in half?#&1 LARGE bunch of Basil, plus more for garnishEtcetera:?#&2 tbsp balsamic vinegar?#&3 tbsp olive oil?#&4 tbsp water?#&1 heaping tbsp. smoked sea salt (I prefer smoked sea salt if you have it!)?#&1 tsp fresh ground pepper (or to taste)', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2017/09/smoked-watermelon-gazpacho/', '', '', 'Sep 10, 2017', '', 'Instructions?#&?#&Preheat your Green Mountain Grill or your other grill to 350 degrees. While getting your grill heated up, finish slicing your veggies. One your grill is at temperature, put your veggies on. Check your veggies every so often to ensure they are not burning- the garlic and peppers will cook the quickest- don’t let the garlic burn, just put it on long enough to soften and get some smoke. As char marks form, turn the veggies over and let the other side cook. Ideally you are looking for good char marks and the veggies and watermelon to caramelize on the grill. NOTE, the watermelon will not get as charred as the rest of the veggies unless you sliced it extremely thin and that is okay. The inherent nature of this fruit having so much water content takes it longer to get char marks- be patient. As veggies develop the char marks, remove them and let them cool in a big bowl.?#&?#&Once all veggies have been remove, place them in the largest pot you have and get out your stick blender. Now, go ahead and add your additional ingredients: balsamic, olive oil, water, sea salt and pepper and the the basil leaves. Pulse the content with your immersion blender until it is pureed. Don’t over puree it, you want it to have the consistency of a fine salsa.?#&?#&Let chill in the refrigerator for at least an hour before serving. Garnish with additional basil. Great served with grilled bread as an appetizer, also great for a light lunch. Goat cheese or sliced avocado are also a great addition for garnish!?#&?#&Enjoy being the creative cook on your block- I promise your friends and family will rave over this recipe!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'9793393FF944DE42B5605C4E3C4AF4D5', X'E860017655588140AFF526284ABE83F0', X'E860017655588140AFF526284ABE83F0', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2012/06/readers-recipes-spicy-honey-kissed-chicken-wings/', 'Spicy Honey Kissed Chicken Wings', 2, NULL, 0, 'Spicy Honey Kissed Chicken Wings', 'Neil Buchwalter', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/IMG_2067-150x150.jpg', '', '', '30 min', '2 hours', '2 hours 30 minutes', '4', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 ½ to 2 dozen chicken wings?#&½ cup hot sauce?#&½ cup French dressing?#&3 tablespoon honey?#&1 tablespoon crushed red pepper?#&½ teaspoon cayenne pepper?#&½ teaspoon coarse ground pepper?#&?#&2 tablespoon garlic powder?#&2 tablespoon paprika?#&1 tablespoon onion powder?#&1 tablespoon ground cumin?#&1 tablespoon chili powder?#&1 tablespoon pepper?#&½ tablespoon cayenne pepper', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2012/06/readers-recipes-spicy-honey-kissed-chicken-wings/', 'Smoked', 'Honey Hot Wings, Honey Hot Sauce, Smoked Hot Wings, Sweet and Spicy Chicken Wings', 'Jun 26, 2012', 'Chicken Wings', 'Instructions?#&?#&About 3 hours before serving remove wings from the refrigerator and separate into 3 parts by cutting at the joints. Discard the wing tips.?#&Place wing pieces into a large bowl and top with rub ingredients or approximately ½ cup of your favorite spicy chicken rub. (Use more or less to taste.) Mix the chicken and the rub until all wings are evenly coated. Let wings come to room temperature, about 20 to 30 minutes.?#&Preheat smoker to 230°F.?#&Place wings on smoker. For best results, turn wings after 45 minutes and again after 45 minutes.?#&While wings are smoking: Combine hot sauce, French dressing, honey, pepper flakes, cayenne and black pepper in a saucepan. Bring to a simmer on the stove, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat and allow mixture to cool.?#&Remove wings from smoker when cooked (internal temperature reads at least 165°F – about 2 hours or about 2 ½ hours if you prefer well-done wings).?#&Toss wings with sauce mixture and serve with blue cheese dressing.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'B85B9278B284B242964D4606906A5830', X'3804FDE63B02BE41B1ED88427C2CE0A2', X'3804FDE63B02BE41B1ED88427C2CE0A2', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2010/02/chipotle-dark-chocolate-cherry-chunk-cookies/', 'Chipotle Dark Chocolate Cherry Chunk Cookies', 2, NULL, 0, 'Chipotle Dark Chocolate Cherry Chunk Cookies', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/food-photographer-jennifer-pallian-OfdDiqx8Cz8-unsplash-150x150.jpg', '', '', '10 minutes', '10 minuetes', '20 minutes', '2- 3 dozen', 'Ingredients?#&?#&3/4 c. granulated sugar?#&3/4 c. packed brown sugar?#&1 c. stick butter, softened?#&1 large egg?#&2 1/4 c. all purpose flour (not self rising)?#&1 tsp. baking soda?#&1/2 tsp. salt?#&1/2– 3/4 c. dried cherries?#&3 large dark chocolate bars (85% cocoa)= approximately 12 ounces, chopped into small pieces (will equal roughly 2 cups)?#&pinch cinammon?#&1–2 dried chipotle peppers, chopped fine (amount depends on if you like hear or not, use one for less heat)', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2010/02/chipotle-dark-chocolate-cherry-chunk-cookies/', '', '', 'Feb 24, 2010', '', 'Instructions?#&?#&Preheat the oven to 375 degrees.?#&Mix sugars, butter and egg in large bowl. Next, stir in the flour, salt and baking soda. Then add in the chocolate and cherries. The batter will be very stiff!!?#&Drop dough by tablespoons onto an ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.?#&Bake for 8-10 minutes until lightly browned. Let cool- the center of the cookie will still be soft when you take the pan out of the oven!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'C3AD264EB9E2524CAEB3670B04D69E53', X'E7E42C26301B904984FB6A3CEC034328', X'E7E42C26301B904984FB6A3CEC034328', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/fire-roasted-poblano-queso-dip/', 'Fire Roasted Poblano Queso Dip', 2, NULL, 0, 'Fire Roasted Poblano Queso', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/smoked-poblano-queso-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '8', 'Ingredients?#&?#&16 oz Velveeta Queso Blanco (you need to use Velveeta in this recipe because of the way it melts)?#&1 poblano pepper?#&1 roma tomato, sliced in half lengthwise?#&dash smoked paprika?#&large bunch cilantro, added at the end', 'American, Mexican', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/fire-roasted-poblano-queso-dip/', 'Grill', 'smoked cheese dip, smoked queso, smoked poblano queso dip, velveeta mexican dip recipe, cheese dip on pellet smoker', 'Jan 30, 2020', 'Appetizer', 'Instructions?#&?#&Put the Velveeta in a grill safe bowl or cast iron pot. Preheat your grill to 350 degrees.?#&Add the cast iron pot, and let the poblano and tomato roast on the grill.?#&When the cheese has completely melted, and the poblano has begun to char, remove the poblano and tomato.?#&Roughly slice vegetables, and add to the cheese, stirring to combine.?#&Remove the cheese dip from the grill and roughly chop the cilantro and place as garnish on top.?#&Serve with tortilla chips. Or if you are eating low carb, try it with pork rinds.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'DEF1BB045179C04FB0886A9F1F99B4B1', X'8A65F90518A7C34EBC183757DCABA8B4', X'8A65F90518A7C34EBC183757DCABA8B4', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/pimento-cheese-jalapeno-poppers-atomic-buffalo-turds/', 'Pimento Cheese Jalapeno Poppers (Atomic Buffalo Turds)', 2, NULL, 0, 'Pimento Cheese Jalapeno Poppers (Atomic Buffalo Turds)', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Pimento-Cheese-Jalapeno-Poppers-ABT-72-e1580352593740-150x150.jpg', '', '', '10', '10', '20 minutes', '4', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 lb jalapenos, sliced lengthwise with seeds removed?#&1 lb bacon – precook the bacon for 3 minutes in microwave before placing on poppers?#&1/2 cup cream cheese?#&1/2 cup pimento cheese?#&dash bbq rub', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/pimento-cheese-jalapeno-poppers-atomic-buffalo-turds/', 'Grilled', 'ABT, atomic buffalo turds recipe, jalapeno poppers with bacon, cream cheese jalapeno, grilled jalapeno recipe, green mountain grills recipe, gmg jalapeno poppers recipe,', 'Jan 29, 2020', 'Appetizer', 'Instructions?#&?#&Place the cream cheese out so it can soften. Meanwhile, cut the tops off the jalapenos and slice them lengthwise in half, while also removing the seeds.?#&Microwave or cook the bacon so it is halfway done — this is about 3 minutes in the microwave.?#&Mix the cream cheese with the pimento cheese and add a generous scoop in each jalapeno.?#&Add a light dusting of bbq rub to the poppers.?#&Finish with a hearty piece of bacon on the top of the cheese mixture. This can be cut to fit.?#&Cook the jalapeno poppers at 350 degrees on your pellet smoker or grill for about 10 minutes or until the bottoms have begun to form nice char marks and the cheese has begun to melt.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'51F3133C1BEE4E449F781FA8DE34995D', X'CD73D7EACD819B45BEC54D6D0066E7FE', X'CD73D7EACD819B45BEC54D6D0066E7FE', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/alabama-white-sauce-chicken-wings/', 'Alabama White Sauce Chicken Wings', 2, NULL, 0, 'Alabama White Sauce Wings', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Alabama-White-Sauce-Chicken-wings-72dpi-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 min', '30 min', '35 minutes', '4', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 ¾ cups mayonnaise?#&¾ cup distilled white vinegar?#&½ cup apple juice?#&2 tsp prepared horseradish?#&1 tbsp fresh grated black pepper?#&Juice and zest of one lemon?#&1 tsp sea salt?#&Dash cayenne pepper?#&1 tsp sugar?#&Dash hot sauce?#&Dash smoked paprika, plus more for serving.', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/alabama-white-sauce-chicken-wings/', '', 'alabama white sauce, white bbq sauce recipe, chicken wings white sauce, mayo sauce, green mountain grills recipe idea, green mountain grills chicken wings, gmg recipe', 'Jan 29, 2020', 'Chicken Wings', 'Instructions?#&?#&Sauce Directions:?#&?#&Combine all ingredients in a pint sized mason jar, stir to combine, then shake to mix well. Can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.?#&?#&Grilling Directions:?#&?#&Preheat your pellet smoker to 350. Let chicken wings cook for about 25 minutes, then crank the smoker to 400 to get crispy skin. Use a thermapen or an internal read thermometer (if you use the Green Mountain Grill it comes with its own thermometer and it will tell you! I love that about this grill!) to test internal temperature – once the wings have reached an internal temperature of 170, pull them off the grill. Sprinkle with smoked paprika for color then drizzle with sauce before serving.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'01CF391641BD804E9C2E9A3F0F9D7852', X'A5731EF9FE297A4BA38F4C37210A5578', X'A5731EF9FE297A4BA38F4C37210A5578', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/citrus-and-herb-smoked-whole-snapper/', 'Citrus and Herb Smoked Whole Snapper', 2, NULL, 0, 'Citrus and Herb Smoked Whole Snapper', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/smoked-whole-snapper-1280x640-1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '10 minutes', '30 minutes', '40 minutes', '2', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 Whole Snapper, inside gizzards removed and de-scaled (have your butcher do this for you)?#&1 lemon, thinly sliced?#&1 lime, thinly sliced?#&2 garlic cloves, minced?#&1 small bunch thyme?#&½ tbsp olive oil?#&2 tsp sea salt?#&2 tsp fresh ground pepper', 'American, Seafood', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/citrus-and-herb-smoked-whole-snapper/', 'Smoked, Grilled', 'smoked snapper, how to smoke snapper, how to smoke fish', 'Jan 21, 2020', 'American, Seafood, Fish', 'Instructions?#&?#&1) Drizzle the insides of the snapper first with olive oil, then add the salt, pepper and garlic and spread in the inside of the cavity evenly.?#&?#&2) layer lemon and lime slices in the cavity starting from front to back and then add the thyme sprigs in the cavity. Save any remaining lemon and lime slices for serving with the fish once it’s cooked.?#&?#&3) Place the snapper on a frog mat and smoke until the internal temperature reaches 145 degrees- this will take anywhere from 45 minutes to an hour depending on the size of the fish.?#&?#&4) Once the internal temp has been met, remove and serve immediately with remaining lemon and lime slices. The outer filets will remove pretty cleanly for serving but be extra vigilant about looking for bones before serving guests.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'64A3E562F573164BB0B4B29ABB2C29DC', X'4466B71586A2C74F8A5967E12B521DAD', X'4466B71586A2C74F8A5967E12B521DAD', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake/', 'Smoked S’mores Cheesecake', 2, NULL, 0, 'Smoked S’mores Cheesecake', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake-1280x640-1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '30 minutes', '1 hour and a half', '2 hours', '8', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Equipment:?#&?#&Springform cheesecake pan (2 parts)?#&?#&Crust:?#&?#&12 oz (1 cup and a half) graham crackers, pureed in food processor (If Keto, skip or use almond flour instead)?#&3 tbsp light brown sugar (if Keto, swap with Swerve Brown Sugar)?#&6 tbsp melted butter – coconut oil could also be used?#&?#&Filling:?#&?#&4– 8 oz (block) Neufchatel cheese, room temperature?#&1/3 cup light brown sugar (or if keto, swap with Swerve Brown Sugar)?#&2 tbsp maple syrup (if keto, swap with Choc Zero Maple Syrup)?#&1 tsp lemon zest?#&1 tbsp fresh lemon juice?#&2 tsp vanilla extract?#&1 tbsp butter, melted?#&5 large eggs?#&2/3 cup cold smoked 70% cocoa dark chocolate (cold smoking part is optional) (if Keto, swap with no sugar chocolate, such as Choc Zero Dark Chocolate)?#&1 cup small marshmallows (if Keto, use sugar free marshmallows or skip this ingredient)?#&?#&Plus, additional 1tbsp butter or coconut oil for coating the pan', 'American', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake/', 'Smoked, Grilled, Baked', 'Smoked Cheesecake Recipe, Smores Cheesecake Recipe, How to Smoke a Cheesecake, Traeger Smoked Cheesecake, Keto Cheesecake', 'Jan 20, 2020', 'Dessert, Cheesecake, Keto Cheesecake', 'Instructions?#&?#&Preheat your oven oven to 400 degrees (to bake the crust).?#&?#&Lightly oil your springform pan with a bit of coconut oil or butter. Pulse the graham crackers in the food processor until they have turned into crumbs. Add the brown sugar and gradually add the melted butter until mixed.?#&?#&Press the graham cracker crust into the pan, it will go up the side of the pan about 1/3 of the way, trying to make as even in thickness as possible. Bake for about 8 minutes or until lightly browned.?#&?#&Filling:?#&?#&In a food processor or stand mixer, combine the cream cheese, sugar, maple syrup, vanilla, lemon juice and zest. Gradually add the eggs slowly one by one until everything is well combined.?#&?#&Pour the batter in the springform pan.?#&?#&Smoke the cheesecake for 30 minutes – during this time, the top will become golden from the smoke. Meanwhile, turn the oven to 350 degrees. Remove the cheesecake from the smoker and place in oven and cook for an additional 45 minutes or until the middle no longer ripples when touching it. While cooking in the oven, the cake will expand much more and gain volume on the top that will eventually go back down as the cake continues to cook.?#&?#&Remove from the oven and let cool on the counter for 20 minutes, then transfer to the refrigerator and let the cake cool for a few hours until ready to serve.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'6ABBA15F8035094888349E0BF6E48068', X'F3987AE875BBD2439F4F073976358FE5', X'F3987AE875BBD2439F4F073976358FE5', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/11/thanksgiving-big-green-egg-turkey-recipe/', 'Guide to Cooking Thanksgiving Turkey on a Big Green Egg', 2, NULL, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/11/thanksgiving-big-green-egg-turkey-recipe/', '', '', 'Nov 5, 2019', '', '');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'DF95AC99E56FAE4D8E0A50F4DB1A4E67', X'07535F3E05F0AA438444B13092A6222A', X'07535F3E05F0AA438444B13092A6222A', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/10/grilled-chicken-for-3-easy-weeknight-meals-plus-keto-and-paleo-options/', 'Grilled Chicken for 3 Easy Weeknight Meals (Plus Keto and Paleo Options)', 2, NULL, 0, 'Grilled Chicken for 3 Easy Weeknight Dinners (Plus Keto and Paleo Options)', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chicken-thighs-on-the-grill72-150x150.jpg', '', '', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '35', '4 lbs grilled chicken', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Grilled Chicken + Salad Night:?#&?#&4 lbs boneless skinless chicken breast?#&1 container arugula?#&Olive oil, balsamic glaze, – or your favorite salad dressing for salad for night #1?#&Your favorite BBQ Rub, you can make your own with my ALL PURPOSE BBQ RUB RECIPE?#&?#&Taco Night:?#&?#&One pack of tortillas?#&1 large bunch Cilantro?#&4 Roma tomatoes?#&2 Avocados?#&?#&Pasta Night?#&?#&3 packages frozen zoodles OR 5 large zucchini that will need to be spiralized OR 1 box fettuccine noodles?#&1 1/2 cups Cream (paleo swap out: coconut cream or a nut butter)?#&1/2 cup Butter?#&1 ½ cups fresh grated Parmesan?#&2 cloves minced garlic', 'American', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/10/grilled-chicken-for-3-easy-weeknight-meals-plus-keto-and-paleo-options/', 'grill', 'grilled chicken for 3 nights of meals, grilled chicken tacos, grilled chicken alfredo, keto friendly chicken alfredo', 'Oct 25, 2019', 'american', 'Instructions?#&?#&Directions For Grilled Chicken:?#&?#&Fill your grill with Kingsford Charcoal Briquettes and prepare your grill for direct heat (charcoal spread out evenly on the bottom versus only on one side). If you would like to learn about how to start a charcoal grill or how to create direct and indirect zones on your grill they are part of my GRILL SCHOOL series which will teach you the fundamentals of grilling!?#&?#&Oil your grill grates with avocado oil or another high heat oil so your chicken doesn’t stick. Grill the chicken thighs on direct heat until the internal temperature reads 170 degrees as determined by an instant read thermometer like the Thermapen or the Thermopop.?#&?#&Remove the chicken from the grill and let rest before cutting into it. Serve with arugula salad and sliced heirloom tomatoes with a drizzle of balsamic glaze and olive oil on the first night. Reserve remaining chicken for dinner on night #2 and #3.?#&?#&Night 1: Chicken and Simple Arugula Salad?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Remove the chicken from the grill and let rest before cutting into it.?#&?#&Serve with arugula salad and sliced heirloom tomatoes with a drizzle of balsamic glaze and olive oil.?#&?#&If you eat carbs, you can easily throw in a grilled Texas Toast or bread to round out the mail. ?#&?#&Night 2: Chicken Tacos?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Reheat about 5-7 chicken thighs and tortillas in the toaster oven at 325. Serve with chopped cilantro, sour cream, and chopped tomatoes with your favorite hot sauce. Notes: Add black beans and rice to round out the meal if you have bigger appetites- this can be made in advance with canned beans and rice done in your rice cooker.?#&?#&Keto/Low Carb: Opt for low car tortillas OR use lettuce as your tortilla and pair with full fat sour cream?#&Paleo: Opt for grain free tortillas, such as almond, coconut or cassava tortillas from Siete foods, pair with coconut cream instead of sour cream?#&?#&Night 3: Cajun Chicken Alfredo ?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Boil noodles or pan fry your noodles until they are aldente. Meanwhile, make your sauce.?#&?#&Melt butter, and cream until it begins to simmer. Add the parmesan and let it continue to cook until the parm has melted.?#&?#&Add a tsp or more to taste of your favorite cajun seasoning.?#&?#&Keto: Your’e good to go- Alfredo sauce is naturally Keto (but pasta is not!) You’ll want to use zoodles or mirarcle noodles to be Keto, Low Carb or Paleo.?#&Paleo: You’re going to need to swap the cream with a nut milk and switch the Parmesan with nutritional yeast. The taste won’t be exactly the same but it will still be good. If you still use some parm it will be “paleoish” and still taste great!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'36A881DEDAB88D4DB8D2704E068AEB09', X'DD94A5626BAC57459E1244CFEA65E61F', X'DD94A5626BAC57459E1244CFEA65E61F', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/09/keto-bbq-pork-pizzas/', 'Keto BBQ Pork Pizzas', 2, NULL, 0, 'Keto BBQ Pizzas', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/KETO-BBQ-PORK-Pizzas-72-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '4 personal pizzas', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 Smithfield Slow Roasted Golden Rotisserie Tenderloin?#&4 Low Carb Tortillas?#&1 cup sugar free, low carb BBQ sauce?#&1 cup shredded cheddar/mozzarella cheese?#&1 large bunch fresh oregano', 'American, BBQ', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/09/keto-bbq-pork-pizzas/', 'saute, bake', 'Keto BBQ Pizza, Keto BBQ Pork Pizza, Keto Pizza no fathead dough, keto pizza with low carb tortillas', 'Sep 9, 2019', 'American', 'Instructions?#&?#&Preheat oven to 375 degrees. While the oven preheats, slice the pork tenderloin into small, uniformly sized pieces.?#&Add a tbsp of coconut oil or avocado oil to a skillet and sauté the pork until it reaches an internal temp of 145 degrees; this should take 10 minutes or less.?#&While the pork is sautéing, toast the tortillas for 5 minutes.?#&Remove the tortillas, layer with BBQ sauce, cheese, and pork – equally divided among 4 pizzas.?#&Place pizzas back in the oven for 5 minutes or until the cheese has melted.?#&Remove the pizzas from the oven and garnish with fresh oregano and fresh pepper.?#&?#&Serve immediately!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'35EDE77D0140A84A9A43A82E4C6EED33', X'D7223BAC8EE8AD49AA326DB3B90BF704', X'D7223BAC8EE8AD49AA326DB3B90BF704', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/07/cast-iron-grilled-mussels-in-a-white-wine-bacon-herb-butter-sauce/', 'Cast Iron Grilled Mussels in a White Wine, Bacon Herb Butter Sauce', 2, NULL, 0, 'Cast Iron Grilled Mussels in a White Wine, Bacon Herb Butter Sauce', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/DSC_016172-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '3', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 dozen mussels?#&2/3 cup Beringer Main and Vine Pinot Grigio?#&3 tbsp butter?#&1 strip bacon, partially cooked?#&1 small bunch of fresh thyme sprigs?#&4 cloves garlic, minced?#&Salt, to taste?#&1 tsp pepper', 'American, French', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/07/cast-iron-grilled-mussels-in-a-white-wine-bacon-herb-butter-sauce/', 'grill, cast iron', 'how to grill mussels, cast iron grilled mussels', 'Jul 26, 2019', 'american, grilled', 'Instructions?#&?#&Precook a slice of bacon so it is ¾ of the way cooked- this can easily be done in the microwave. Next, add the wine, butter, garlic, bacon (remove fatty parts of the bacon and chop before adding), thyme, salt and pepper.?#&?#&Add the mussels to the cast iron skillet and grill on direct heat over Kingsford Charcoal until the mussels open up- about 15 minutes or less. Serve with grilled or toasted crusty bread like ciabatta or French bread to sop up the white wine sauce.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'0A99701D41644049B3E515AD911AF32D', X'AD6DA2D929A6B1499DFAC793D4186577', X'AD6DA2D929A6B1499DFAC793D4186577', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/06/low-carb-char-siu-pork-belly-burnt-ends/', 'Low-Carb “Char Siu” Pork Belly Burnt Ends', 2, NULL, 0, 'Low Carb Char Siu Pork Belly Burnt Ends', 'Jon Solberg', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/85C2B6BE-A957-44D6-B29B-F77BB54698A1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '45 min', '3-5 hour', '4-6 hours', '6', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Aluminum foil 1/2 pan?#&Smoking wood of choice, I used four chunks of oak?#&3 lbs. skinless pork belly?#&1½ Tsp of kosher salt (Morton)?#&½ Tsp black pepper (restaurant grind)?#&1 Tbsp olive oil?#&?#&Char Siu sauce:?#&?#&4 Tbsp tamari?#&2 Tbsp natural smooth peanut butter?#&4 Tbsp Sukrin Gold sugar substitute, or whatever sugar substitute you like?#&1 Tbsp oyster sauce?#&4 Tsp rice wine?#&1 Tsp Smoked Paprika?#&3 Tsp sesame oil?#&1 Tsp Louisiana hot sauce?#&1 Tsp ginger powder?#&1 Tsp garlic powder?#&½ Tsp 5-spice powder', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/06/low-carb-char-siu-pork-belly-burnt-ends/', '', 'char siu, 5-spice, pork belly, pork, chinese bbq', 'Jun 6, 2019', '', 'Instructions?#&?#&Cut pork belly into 1” cubes. In a large bowl toss the cubes in the olive oil, salt, and pepper.?#&?#&Combine the remaining ingredients in a saucepan over medium-to-low heat and whisk together until everything is dissolved. Remove the pan from the heat.?#&?#&Set your Big Green Egg up for indirect cooking and get the temperature to 275° and the cooking grate level.?#&?#&Smoke the pork belly with the fat side down until the cubes reach an internal temperature of around 190°f.   This will take around 2-3 hours.?#&?#&Try using a Thermapen for a precise temperature reading.?#&?#&Remove the cubes from the smoker and place in the aluminum ½ pan.?#&?#&Toss in the Char Sui sauce. Coat the cubes well then return to the smoker.?#&?#&Continue to cook uncovered for an additional hour or until the sauce has reduced.?#&?#&Plate and enjoy!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'0DBE2C13DB44EE47A438EC26A445320F', X'E55E2AB154155C458D732B799DC9E53B', X'E55E2AB154155C458D732B799DC9E53B', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/fire-roasted-poblano-queso-dip/', 'Fire Roasted Poblano Queso Dip', 2, NULL, 0, 'Fire Roasted Poblano Queso', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/smoked-poblano-queso-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '8', 'Ingredients?#&?#&16 oz Velveeta Queso Blanco (you need to use Velveeta in this recipe because of the way it melts)?#&1 poblano pepper?#&1 roma tomato, sliced in half lengthwise?#&dash smoked paprika?#&large bunch cilantro, added at the end', 'American, Mexican', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/fire-roasted-poblano-queso-dip/', 'Grill', 'smoked cheese dip, smoked queso, smoked poblano queso dip, velveeta mexican dip recipe, cheese dip on pellet smoker', 'Jan 30, 2020', 'Appetizer', 'Instructions?#&?#&Put the Velveeta in a grill safe bowl or cast iron pot. Preheat your grill to 350 degrees.?#&Add the cast iron pot, and let the poblano and tomato roast on the grill.?#&When the cheese has completely melted, and the poblano has begun to char, remove the poblano and tomato.?#&Roughly slice vegetables, and add to the cheese, stirring to combine.?#&Remove the cheese dip from the grill and roughly chop the cilantro and place as garnish on top.?#&Serve with tortilla chips. Or if you are eating low carb, try it with pork rinds.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'888807A1EC9A694EB219416B983CC9D1', X'7460D6BA5E94F444A5F91AEDA3716B7F', X'7460D6BA5E94F444A5F91AEDA3716B7F', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/pimento-cheese-jalapeno-poppers-atomic-buffalo-turds/', 'Pimento Cheese Jalapeno Poppers (Atomic Buffalo Turds)', 2, NULL, 0, 'Pimento Cheese Jalapeno Poppers (Atomic Buffalo Turds)', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Pimento-Cheese-Jalapeno-Poppers-ABT-72-e1580352593740-150x150.jpg', '', '', '10', '10', '20 minutes', '4', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 lb jalapenos, sliced lengthwise with seeds removed?#&1 lb bacon – precook the bacon for 3 minutes in microwave before placing on poppers?#&1/2 cup cream cheese?#&1/2 cup pimento cheese?#&dash bbq rub', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/pimento-cheese-jalapeno-poppers-atomic-buffalo-turds/', 'Grilled', 'ABT, atomic buffalo turds recipe, jalapeno poppers with bacon, cream cheese jalapeno, grilled jalapeno recipe, green mountain grills recipe, gmg jalapeno poppers recipe,', 'Jan 29, 2020', 'Appetizer', 'Instructions?#&?#&Place the cream cheese out so it can soften. Meanwhile, cut the tops off the jalapenos and slice them lengthwise in half, while also removing the seeds.?#&Microwave or cook the bacon so it is halfway done — this is about 3 minutes in the microwave.?#&Mix the cream cheese with the pimento cheese and add a generous scoop in each jalapeno.?#&Add a light dusting of bbq rub to the poppers.?#&Finish with a hearty piece of bacon on the top of the cheese mixture. This can be cut to fit.?#&Cook the jalapeno poppers at 350 degrees on your pellet smoker or grill for about 10 minutes or until the bottoms have begun to form nice char marks and the cheese has begun to melt.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'5AFA491738C5EB4D9311618403E0E3D9', X'4B54B4DB0F354747B6F1C114FAB0A0FE', X'4B54B4DB0F354747B6F1C114FAB0A0FE', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/alabama-white-sauce-chicken-wings/', 'Alabama White Sauce Chicken Wings', 2, NULL, 0, 'Alabama White Sauce Wings', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Alabama-White-Sauce-Chicken-wings-72dpi-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 min', '30 min', '35 minutes', '4', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 ¾ cups mayonnaise?#&¾ cup distilled white vinegar?#&½ cup apple juice?#&2 tsp prepared horseradish?#&1 tbsp fresh grated black pepper?#&Juice and zest of one lemon?#&1 tsp sea salt?#&Dash cayenne pepper?#&1 tsp sugar?#&Dash hot sauce?#&Dash smoked paprika, plus more for serving.', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/alabama-white-sauce-chicken-wings/', '', 'alabama white sauce, white bbq sauce recipe, chicken wings white sauce, mayo sauce, green mountain grills recipe idea, green mountain grills chicken wings, gmg recipe', 'Jan 29, 2020', 'Chicken Wings', 'Instructions?#&?#&Sauce Directions:?#&?#&Combine all ingredients in a pint sized mason jar, stir to combine, then shake to mix well. Can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.?#&?#&Grilling Directions:?#&?#&Preheat your pellet smoker to 350. Let chicken wings cook for about 25 minutes, then crank the smoker to 400 to get crispy skin. Use a thermapen or an internal read thermometer (if you use the Green Mountain Grill it comes with its own thermometer and it will tell you! I love that about this grill!) to test internal temperature – once the wings have reached an internal temperature of 170, pull them off the grill. Sprinkle with smoked paprika for color then drizzle with sauce before serving.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'2FEFD9252D79374DB4E2ECC84B662154', X'546EC3D5DC7C4D46B53645B8374B8C4C', X'546EC3D5DC7C4D46B53645B8374B8C4C', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/citrus-and-herb-smoked-whole-snapper/', 'Citrus and Herb Smoked Whole Snapper', 2, NULL, 0, 'Citrus and Herb Smoked Whole Snapper', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/smoked-whole-snapper-1280x640-1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '10 minutes', '30 minutes', '40 minutes', '2', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 Whole Snapper, inside gizzards removed and de-scaled (have your butcher do this for you)?#&1 lemon, thinly sliced?#&1 lime, thinly sliced?#&2 garlic cloves, minced?#&1 small bunch thyme?#&½ tbsp olive oil?#&2 tsp sea salt?#&2 tsp fresh ground pepper', 'American, Seafood', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/citrus-and-herb-smoked-whole-snapper/', 'Smoked, Grilled', 'smoked snapper, how to smoke snapper, how to smoke fish', 'Jan 21, 2020', 'American, Seafood, Fish', 'Instructions?#&?#&1) Drizzle the insides of the snapper first with olive oil, then add the salt, pepper and garlic and spread in the inside of the cavity evenly.?#&?#&2) layer lemon and lime slices in the cavity starting from front to back and then add the thyme sprigs in the cavity. Save any remaining lemon and lime slices for serving with the fish once it’s cooked.?#&?#&3) Place the snapper on a frog mat and smoke until the internal temperature reaches 145 degrees- this will take anywhere from 45 minutes to an hour depending on the size of the fish.?#&?#&4) Once the internal temp has been met, remove and serve immediately with remaining lemon and lime slices. The outer filets will remove pretty cleanly for serving but be extra vigilant about looking for bones before serving guests.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'6A6B6655FA18C94BB1C8376F42129055', X'E5853DFF13AC2047A785644DDF5AB565', X'E5853DFF13AC2047A785644DDF5AB565', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake/', 'Smoked S’mores Cheesecake', 2, NULL, 0, 'Smoked S’mores Cheesecake', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake-1280x640-1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '30 minutes', '1 hour and a half', '2 hours', '8', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Equipment:?#&?#&Springform cheesecake pan (2 parts)?#&?#&Crust:?#&?#&12 oz (1 cup and a half) graham crackers, pureed in food processor (If Keto, skip or use almond flour instead)?#&3 tbsp light brown sugar (if Keto, swap with Swerve Brown Sugar)?#&6 tbsp melted butter – coconut oil could also be used?#&?#&Filling:?#&?#&4– 8 oz (block) Neufchatel cheese, room temperature?#&1/3 cup light brown sugar (or if keto, swap with Swerve Brown Sugar)?#&2 tbsp maple syrup (if keto, swap with Choc Zero Maple Syrup)?#&1 tsp lemon zest?#&1 tbsp fresh lemon juice?#&2 tsp vanilla extract?#&1 tbsp butter, melted?#&5 large eggs?#&2/3 cup cold smoked 70% cocoa dark chocolate (cold smoking part is optional) (if Keto, swap with no sugar chocolate, such as Choc Zero Dark Chocolate)?#&1 cup small marshmallows (if Keto, use sugar free marshmallows or skip this ingredient)?#&?#&Plus, additional 1tbsp butter or coconut oil for coating the pan', 'American', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake/', 'Smoked, Grilled, Baked', 'Smoked Cheesecake Recipe, Smores Cheesecake Recipe, How to Smoke a Cheesecake, Traeger Smoked Cheesecake, Keto Cheesecake', 'Jan 20, 2020', 'Dessert, Cheesecake, Keto Cheesecake', 'Instructions?#&?#&Preheat your oven oven to 400 degrees (to bake the crust).?#&?#&Lightly oil your springform pan with a bit of coconut oil or butter. Pulse the graham crackers in the food processor until they have turned into crumbs. Add the brown sugar and gradually add the melted butter until mixed.?#&?#&Press the graham cracker crust into the pan, it will go up the side of the pan about 1/3 of the way, trying to make as even in thickness as possible. Bake for about 8 minutes or until lightly browned.?#&?#&Filling:?#&?#&In a food processor or stand mixer, combine the cream cheese, sugar, maple syrup, vanilla, lemon juice and zest. Gradually add the eggs slowly one by one until everything is well combined.?#&?#&Pour the batter in the springform pan.?#&?#&Smoke the cheesecake for 30 minutes – during this time, the top will become golden from the smoke. Meanwhile, turn the oven to 350 degrees. Remove the cheesecake from the smoker and place in oven and cook for an additional 45 minutes or until the middle no longer ripples when touching it. While cooking in the oven, the cake will expand much more and gain volume on the top that will eventually go back down as the cake continues to cook.?#&?#&Remove from the oven and let cool on the counter for 20 minutes, then transfer to the refrigerator and let the cake cool for a few hours until ready to serve.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'E4DDF2013FC27F4CA425EF027741F58C', X'B693FB4E2520304C9C0D25A8B7F002F9', X'B693FB4E2520304C9C0D25A8B7F002F9', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/11/thanksgiving-big-green-egg-turkey-recipe/', 'Guide to Cooking Thanksgiving Turkey on a Big Green Egg', 2, NULL, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/11/thanksgiving-big-green-egg-turkey-recipe/', '', '', 'Nov 5, 2019', '', '');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'1476FD455FEA6A499717B8EFB82A308A', X'F3B917BE739C414EB97C09B623340C79', X'F3B917BE739C414EB97C09B623340C79', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/10/grilled-chicken-for-3-easy-weeknight-meals-plus-keto-and-paleo-options/', 'Grilled Chicken for 3 Easy Weeknight Meals (Plus Keto and Paleo Options)', 2, NULL, 0, 'Grilled Chicken for 3 Easy Weeknight Dinners (Plus Keto and Paleo Options)', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chicken-thighs-on-the-grill72-150x150.jpg', '', '', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '35', '4 lbs grilled chicken', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Grilled Chicken + Salad Night:?#&?#&4 lbs boneless skinless chicken breast?#&1 container arugula?#&Olive oil, balsamic glaze, – or your favorite salad dressing for salad for night #1?#&Your favorite BBQ Rub, you can make your own with my ALL PURPOSE BBQ RUB RECIPE?#&?#&Taco Night:?#&?#&One pack of tortillas?#&1 large bunch Cilantro?#&4 Roma tomatoes?#&2 Avocados?#&?#&Pasta Night?#&?#&3 packages frozen zoodles OR 5 large zucchini that will need to be spiralized OR 1 box fettuccine noodles?#&1 1/2 cups Cream (paleo swap out: coconut cream or a nut butter)?#&1/2 cup Butter?#&1 ½ cups fresh grated Parmesan?#&2 cloves minced garlic', 'American', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/10/grilled-chicken-for-3-easy-weeknight-meals-plus-keto-and-paleo-options/', 'grill', 'grilled chicken for 3 nights of meals, grilled chicken tacos, grilled chicken alfredo, keto friendly chicken alfredo', 'Oct 25, 2019', 'american', 'Instructions?#&?#&Directions For Grilled Chicken:?#&?#&Fill your grill with Kingsford Charcoal Briquettes and prepare your grill for direct heat (charcoal spread out evenly on the bottom versus only on one side). If you would like to learn about how to start a charcoal grill or how to create direct and indirect zones on your grill they are part of my GRILL SCHOOL series which will teach you the fundamentals of grilling!?#&?#&Oil your grill grates with avocado oil or another high heat oil so your chicken doesn’t stick. Grill the chicken thighs on direct heat until the internal temperature reads 170 degrees as determined by an instant read thermometer like the Thermapen or the Thermopop.?#&?#&Remove the chicken from the grill and let rest before cutting into it. Serve with arugula salad and sliced heirloom tomatoes with a drizzle of balsamic glaze and olive oil on the first night. Reserve remaining chicken for dinner on night #2 and #3.?#&?#&Night 1: Chicken and Simple Arugula Salad?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Remove the chicken from the grill and let rest before cutting into it.?#&?#&Serve with arugula salad and sliced heirloom tomatoes with a drizzle of balsamic glaze and olive oil.?#&?#&If you eat carbs, you can easily throw in a grilled Texas Toast or bread to round out the mail. ?#&?#&Night 2: Chicken Tacos?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Reheat about 5-7 chicken thighs and tortillas in the toaster oven at 325. Serve with chopped cilantro, sour cream, and chopped tomatoes with your favorite hot sauce. Notes: Add black beans and rice to round out the meal if you have bigger appetites- this can be made in advance with canned beans and rice done in your rice cooker.?#&?#&Keto/Low Carb: Opt for low car tortillas OR use lettuce as your tortilla and pair with full fat sour cream?#&Paleo: Opt for grain free tortillas, such as almond, coconut or cassava tortillas from Siete foods, pair with coconut cream instead of sour cream?#&?#&Night 3: Cajun Chicken Alfredo ?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Boil noodles or pan fry your noodles until they are aldente. Meanwhile, make your sauce.?#&?#&Melt butter, and cream until it begins to simmer. Add the parmesan and let it continue to cook until the parm has melted.?#&?#&Add a tsp or more to taste of your favorite cajun seasoning.?#&?#&Keto: Your’e good to go- Alfredo sauce is naturally Keto (but pasta is not!) You’ll want to use zoodles or mirarcle noodles to be Keto, Low Carb or Paleo.?#&Paleo: You’re going to need to swap the cream with a nut milk and switch the Parmesan with nutritional yeast. The taste won’t be exactly the same but it will still be good. If you still use some parm it will be “paleoish” and still taste great!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'99F6CC58BE93E042867718237F717F31', X'EC1F4F80FB57484FAADE2A26EAA70C6B', X'EC1F4F80FB57484FAADE2A26EAA70C6B', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/09/keto-bbq-pork-pizzas/', 'Keto BBQ Pork Pizzas', 2, NULL, 0, 'Keto BBQ Pizzas', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/KETO-BBQ-PORK-Pizzas-72-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '4 personal pizzas', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 Smithfield Slow Roasted Golden Rotisserie Tenderloin?#&4 Low Carb Tortillas?#&1 cup sugar free, low carb BBQ sauce?#&1 cup shredded cheddar/mozzarella cheese?#&1 large bunch fresh oregano', 'American, BBQ', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/09/keto-bbq-pork-pizzas/', 'saute, bake', 'Keto BBQ Pizza, Keto BBQ Pork Pizza, Keto Pizza no fathead dough, keto pizza with low carb tortillas', 'Sep 9, 2019', 'American', 'Instructions?#&?#&Preheat oven to 375 degrees. While the oven preheats, slice the pork tenderloin into small, uniformly sized pieces.?#&Add a tbsp of coconut oil or avocado oil to a skillet and sauté the pork until it reaches an internal temp of 145 degrees; this should take 10 minutes or less.?#&While the pork is sautéing, toast the tortillas for 5 minutes.?#&Remove the tortillas, layer with BBQ sauce, cheese, and pork – equally divided among 4 pizzas.?#&Place pizzas back in the oven for 5 minutes or until the cheese has melted.?#&Remove the pizzas from the oven and garnish with fresh oregano and fresh pepper.?#&?#&Serve immediately!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'4CA19CDC8F423D449DECC7BC05B81CA6', X'5B6FA3C97F436B4EA0F49DEC4B4D9523', X'5B6FA3C97F436B4EA0F49DEC4B4D9523', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/07/cast-iron-grilled-mussels-in-a-white-wine-bacon-herb-butter-sauce/', 'Cast Iron Grilled Mussels in a White Wine, Bacon Herb Butter Sauce', 2, NULL, 0, 'Cast Iron Grilled Mussels in a White Wine, Bacon Herb Butter Sauce', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/DSC_016172-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '3', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 dozen mussels?#&2/3 cup Beringer Main and Vine Pinot Grigio?#&3 tbsp butter?#&1 strip bacon, partially cooked?#&1 small bunch of fresh thyme sprigs?#&4 cloves garlic, minced?#&Salt, to taste?#&1 tsp pepper', 'American, French', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/07/cast-iron-grilled-mussels-in-a-white-wine-bacon-herb-butter-sauce/', 'grill, cast iron', 'how to grill mussels, cast iron grilled mussels', 'Jul 26, 2019', 'american, grilled', 'Instructions?#&?#&Precook a slice of bacon so it is ¾ of the way cooked- this can easily be done in the microwave. Next, add the wine, butter, garlic, bacon (remove fatty parts of the bacon and chop before adding), thyme, salt and pepper.?#&?#&Add the mussels to the cast iron skillet and grill on direct heat over Kingsford Charcoal until the mussels open up- about 15 minutes or less. Serve with grilled or toasted crusty bread like ciabatta or French bread to sop up the white wine sauce.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'51D7434CC3BB8448A5C4AA30721131AC', X'8F95CC7227C5B34586CBA5328F5648A9', X'8F95CC7227C5B34586CBA5328F5648A9', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/06/low-carb-char-siu-pork-belly-burnt-ends/', 'Low-Carb “Char Siu” Pork Belly Burnt Ends', 2, NULL, 0, 'Low Carb Char Siu Pork Belly Burnt Ends', 'Jon Solberg', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/85C2B6BE-A957-44D6-B29B-F77BB54698A1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '45 min', '3-5 hour', '4-6 hours', '6', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Aluminum foil 1/2 pan?#&Smoking wood of choice, I used four chunks of oak?#&3 lbs. skinless pork belly?#&1½ Tsp of kosher salt (Morton)?#&½ Tsp black pepper (restaurant grind)?#&1 Tbsp olive oil?#&?#&Char Siu sauce:?#&?#&4 Tbsp tamari?#&2 Tbsp natural smooth peanut butter?#&4 Tbsp Sukrin Gold sugar substitute, or whatever sugar substitute you like?#&1 Tbsp oyster sauce?#&4 Tsp rice wine?#&1 Tsp Smoked Paprika?#&3 Tsp sesame oil?#&1 Tsp Louisiana hot sauce?#&1 Tsp ginger powder?#&1 Tsp garlic powder?#&½ Tsp 5-spice powder', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/06/low-carb-char-siu-pork-belly-burnt-ends/', '', 'char siu, 5-spice, pork belly, pork, chinese bbq', 'Jun 6, 2019', '', 'Instructions?#&?#&Cut pork belly into 1” cubes. In a large bowl toss the cubes in the olive oil, salt, and pepper.?#&?#&Combine the remaining ingredients in a saucepan over medium-to-low heat and whisk together until everything is dissolved. Remove the pan from the heat.?#&?#&Set your Big Green Egg up for indirect cooking and get the temperature to 275° and the cooking grate level.?#&?#&Smoke the pork belly with the fat side down until the cubes reach an internal temperature of around 190°f.   This will take around 2-3 hours.?#&?#&Try using a Thermapen for a precise temperature reading.?#&?#&Remove the cubes from the smoker and place in the aluminum ½ pan.?#&?#&Toss in the Char Sui sauce. Coat the cubes well then return to the smoker.?#&?#&Continue to cook uncovered for an additional hour or until the sauce has reduced.?#&?#&Plate and enjoy!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'64F67D9C8C9FC7439CB5692744579705', X'B1EC1F9E98E18642814AF04121D4D9A2', X'B1EC1F9E98E18642814AF04121D4D9A2', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/fire-roasted-poblano-queso-dip/', 'Fire Roasted Poblano Queso Dip', 2, NULL, 0, 'Fire Roasted Poblano Queso', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/smoked-poblano-queso-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '8', 'Ingredients?#&?#&16 oz Velveeta Queso Blanco (you need to use Velveeta in this recipe because of the way it melts)?#&1 poblano pepper?#&1 roma tomato, sliced in half lengthwise?#&dash smoked paprika?#&large bunch cilantro, added at the end', 'American, Mexican', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/fire-roasted-poblano-queso-dip/', 'Grill', 'smoked cheese dip, smoked queso, smoked poblano queso dip, velveeta mexican dip recipe, cheese dip on pellet smoker', 'Jan 30, 2020', 'Appetizer', 'Instructions?#&?#&Put the Velveeta in a grill safe bowl or cast iron pot. Preheat your grill to 350 degrees.?#&Add the cast iron pot, and let the poblano and tomato roast on the grill.?#&When the cheese has completely melted, and the poblano has begun to char, remove the poblano and tomato.?#&Roughly slice vegetables, and add to the cheese, stirring to combine.?#&Remove the cheese dip from the grill and roughly chop the cilantro and place as garnish on top.?#&Serve with tortilla chips. Or if you are eating low carb, try it with pork rinds.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'88498D3043AB634F99D93449F4867D97', X'93A5D5A024E86B49AE939689EAEB19B2', X'93A5D5A024E86B49AE939689EAEB19B2', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/pimento-cheese-jalapeno-poppers-atomic-buffalo-turds/', 'Pimento Cheese Jalapeno Poppers (Atomic Buffalo Turds)', 2, NULL, 0, 'Pimento Cheese Jalapeno Poppers (Atomic Buffalo Turds)', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Pimento-Cheese-Jalapeno-Poppers-ABT-72-e1580352593740-150x150.jpg', '', '', '10', '10', '20 minutes', '4', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 lb jalapenos, sliced lengthwise with seeds removed?#&1 lb bacon – precook the bacon for 3 minutes in microwave before placing on poppers?#&1/2 cup cream cheese?#&1/2 cup pimento cheese?#&dash bbq rub', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/pimento-cheese-jalapeno-poppers-atomic-buffalo-turds/', 'Grilled', 'ABT, atomic buffalo turds recipe, jalapeno poppers with bacon, cream cheese jalapeno, grilled jalapeno recipe, green mountain grills recipe, gmg jalapeno poppers recipe,', 'Jan 29, 2020', 'Appetizer', 'Instructions?#&?#&Place the cream cheese out so it can soften. Meanwhile, cut the tops off the jalapenos and slice them lengthwise in half, while also removing the seeds.?#&Microwave or cook the bacon so it is halfway done — this is about 3 minutes in the microwave.?#&Mix the cream cheese with the pimento cheese and add a generous scoop in each jalapeno.?#&Add a light dusting of bbq rub to the poppers.?#&Finish with a hearty piece of bacon on the top of the cheese mixture. This can be cut to fit.?#&Cook the jalapeno poppers at 350 degrees on your pellet smoker or grill for about 10 minutes or until the bottoms have begun to form nice char marks and the cheese has begun to melt.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'8CF0C683E4B2F54989604010E50C742A', X'8661239C8D7B0C45B13EF4BFC2C8CD1B', X'8661239C8D7B0C45B13EF4BFC2C8CD1B', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/alabama-white-sauce-chicken-wings/', 'Alabama White Sauce Chicken Wings', 2, NULL, 0, 'Alabama White Sauce Wings', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Alabama-White-Sauce-Chicken-wings-72dpi-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 min', '30 min', '35 minutes', '4', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 ¾ cups mayonnaise?#&¾ cup distilled white vinegar?#&½ cup apple juice?#&2 tsp prepared horseradish?#&1 tbsp fresh grated black pepper?#&Juice and zest of one lemon?#&1 tsp sea salt?#&Dash cayenne pepper?#&1 tsp sugar?#&Dash hot sauce?#&Dash smoked paprika, plus more for serving.', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/alabama-white-sauce-chicken-wings/', '', 'alabama white sauce, white bbq sauce recipe, chicken wings white sauce, mayo sauce, green mountain grills recipe idea, green mountain grills chicken wings, gmg recipe', 'Jan 29, 2020', 'Chicken Wings', 'Instructions?#&?#&Sauce Directions:?#&?#&Combine all ingredients in a pint sized mason jar, stir to combine, then shake to mix well. Can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.?#&?#&Grilling Directions:?#&?#&Preheat your pellet smoker to 350. Let chicken wings cook for about 25 minutes, then crank the smoker to 400 to get crispy skin. Use a thermapen or an internal read thermometer (if you use the Green Mountain Grill it comes with its own thermometer and it will tell you! I love that about this grill!) to test internal temperature – once the wings have reached an internal temperature of 170, pull them off the grill. Sprinkle with smoked paprika for color then drizzle with sauce before serving.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'3557C857B000124EA7552975206FC2B4', X'C9333F9C11E871488A57AAC1B8CC54E4', X'C9333F9C11E871488A57AAC1B8CC54E4', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/citrus-and-herb-smoked-whole-snapper/', 'Citrus and Herb Smoked Whole Snapper', 2, NULL, 0, 'Citrus and Herb Smoked Whole Snapper', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/smoked-whole-snapper-1280x640-1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '10 minutes', '30 minutes', '40 minutes', '2', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 Whole Snapper, inside gizzards removed and de-scaled (have your butcher do this for you)?#&1 lemon, thinly sliced?#&1 lime, thinly sliced?#&2 garlic cloves, minced?#&1 small bunch thyme?#&½ tbsp olive oil?#&2 tsp sea salt?#&2 tsp fresh ground pepper', 'American, Seafood', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/citrus-and-herb-smoked-whole-snapper/', 'Smoked, Grilled', 'smoked snapper, how to smoke snapper, how to smoke fish', 'Jan 21, 2020', 'American, Seafood, Fish', 'Instructions?#&?#&1) Drizzle the insides of the snapper first with olive oil, then add the salt, pepper and garlic and spread in the inside of the cavity evenly.?#&?#&2) layer lemon and lime slices in the cavity starting from front to back and then add the thyme sprigs in the cavity. Save any remaining lemon and lime slices for serving with the fish once it’s cooked.?#&?#&3) Place the snapper on a frog mat and smoke until the internal temperature reaches 145 degrees- this will take anywhere from 45 minutes to an hour depending on the size of the fish.?#&?#&4) Once the internal temp has been met, remove and serve immediately with remaining lemon and lime slices. The outer filets will remove pretty cleanly for serving but be extra vigilant about looking for bones before serving guests.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'ABEFD45DC6063F4AA27960B98CCD13E4', X'98CF5F172D297B4FA374952396DF7A4A', X'98CF5F172D297B4FA374952396DF7A4A', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake/', 'Smoked S’mores Cheesecake', 2, NULL, 0, 'Smoked S’mores Cheesecake', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake-1280x640-1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '30 minutes', '1 hour and a half', '2 hours', '8', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Equipment:?#&?#&Springform cheesecake pan (2 parts)?#&?#&Crust:?#&?#&12 oz (1 cup and a half) graham crackers, pureed in food processor (If Keto, skip or use almond flour instead)?#&3 tbsp light brown sugar (if Keto, swap with Swerve Brown Sugar)?#&6 tbsp melted butter – coconut oil could also be used?#&?#&Filling:?#&?#&4– 8 oz (block) Neufchatel cheese, room temperature?#&1/3 cup light brown sugar (or if keto, swap with Swerve Brown Sugar)?#&2 tbsp maple syrup (if keto, swap with Choc Zero Maple Syrup)?#&1 tsp lemon zest?#&1 tbsp fresh lemon juice?#&2 tsp vanilla extract?#&1 tbsp butter, melted?#&5 large eggs?#&2/3 cup cold smoked 70% cocoa dark chocolate (cold smoking part is optional) (if Keto, swap with no sugar chocolate, such as Choc Zero Dark Chocolate)?#&1 cup small marshmallows (if Keto, use sugar free marshmallows or skip this ingredient)?#&?#&Plus, additional 1tbsp butter or coconut oil for coating the pan', 'American', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake/', 'Smoked, Grilled, Baked', 'Smoked Cheesecake Recipe, Smores Cheesecake Recipe, How to Smoke a Cheesecake, Traeger Smoked Cheesecake, Keto Cheesecake', 'Jan 20, 2020', 'Dessert, Cheesecake, Keto Cheesecake', 'Instructions?#&?#&Preheat your oven oven to 400 degrees (to bake the crust).?#&?#&Lightly oil your springform pan with a bit of coconut oil or butter. Pulse the graham crackers in the food processor until they have turned into crumbs. Add the brown sugar and gradually add the melted butter until mixed.?#&?#&Press the graham cracker crust into the pan, it will go up the side of the pan about 1/3 of the way, trying to make as even in thickness as possible. Bake for about 8 minutes or until lightly browned.?#&?#&Filling:?#&?#&In a food processor or stand mixer, combine the cream cheese, sugar, maple syrup, vanilla, lemon juice and zest. Gradually add the eggs slowly one by one until everything is well combined.?#&?#&Pour the batter in the springform pan.?#&?#&Smoke the cheesecake for 30 minutes – during this time, the top will become golden from the smoke. Meanwhile, turn the oven to 350 degrees. Remove the cheesecake from the smoker and place in oven and cook for an additional 45 minutes or until the middle no longer ripples when touching it. While cooking in the oven, the cake will expand much more and gain volume on the top that will eventually go back down as the cake continues to cook.?#&?#&Remove from the oven and let cool on the counter for 20 minutes, then transfer to the refrigerator and let the cake cool for a few hours until ready to serve.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'ED6848DEC416994D92583CD1EF7A36B9', X'8F3D7ED6429309408F40F6C3182C38F4', X'8F3D7ED6429309408F40F6C3182C38F4', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/11/thanksgiving-big-green-egg-turkey-recipe/', 'Guide to Cooking Thanksgiving Turkey on a Big Green Egg', 2, NULL, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/11/thanksgiving-big-green-egg-turkey-recipe/', '', '', 'Nov 5, 2019', '', '');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'A68754DF8813F14C9E726C19DDAE84C4', X'1C14DDE022AC8B409137DBBF1BB83811', X'1C14DDE022AC8B409137DBBF1BB83811', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/10/grilled-chicken-for-3-easy-weeknight-meals-plus-keto-and-paleo-options/', 'Grilled Chicken for 3 Easy Weeknight Meals (Plus Keto and Paleo Options)', 2, NULL, 0, 'Grilled Chicken for 3 Easy Weeknight Dinners (Plus Keto and Paleo Options)', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chicken-thighs-on-the-grill72-150x150.jpg', '', '', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '35', '4 lbs grilled chicken', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Grilled Chicken + Salad Night:?#&?#&4 lbs boneless skinless chicken breast?#&1 container arugula?#&Olive oil, balsamic glaze, – or your favorite salad dressing for salad for night #1?#&Your favorite BBQ Rub, you can make your own with my ALL PURPOSE BBQ RUB RECIPE?#&?#&Taco Night:?#&?#&One pack of tortillas?#&1 large bunch Cilantro?#&4 Roma tomatoes?#&2 Avocados?#&?#&Pasta Night?#&?#&3 packages frozen zoodles OR 5 large zucchini that will need to be spiralized OR 1 box fettuccine noodles?#&1 1/2 cups Cream (paleo swap out: coconut cream or a nut butter)?#&1/2 cup Butter?#&1 ½ cups fresh grated Parmesan?#&2 cloves minced garlic', 'American', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/10/grilled-chicken-for-3-easy-weeknight-meals-plus-keto-and-paleo-options/', 'grill', 'grilled chicken for 3 nights of meals, grilled chicken tacos, grilled chicken alfredo, keto friendly chicken alfredo', 'Oct 25, 2019', 'american', 'Instructions?#&?#&Directions For Grilled Chicken:?#&?#&Fill your grill with Kingsford Charcoal Briquettes and prepare your grill for direct heat (charcoal spread out evenly on the bottom versus only on one side). If you would like to learn about how to start a charcoal grill or how to create direct and indirect zones on your grill they are part of my GRILL SCHOOL series which will teach you the fundamentals of grilling!?#&?#&Oil your grill grates with avocado oil or another high heat oil so your chicken doesn’t stick. Grill the chicken thighs on direct heat until the internal temperature reads 170 degrees as determined by an instant read thermometer like the Thermapen or the Thermopop.?#&?#&Remove the chicken from the grill and let rest before cutting into it. Serve with arugula salad and sliced heirloom tomatoes with a drizzle of balsamic glaze and olive oil on the first night. Reserve remaining chicken for dinner on night #2 and #3.?#&?#&Night 1: Chicken and Simple Arugula Salad?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Remove the chicken from the grill and let rest before cutting into it.?#&?#&Serve with arugula salad and sliced heirloom tomatoes with a drizzle of balsamic glaze and olive oil.?#&?#&If you eat carbs, you can easily throw in a grilled Texas Toast or bread to round out the mail. ?#&?#&Night 2: Chicken Tacos?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Reheat about 5-7 chicken thighs and tortillas in the toaster oven at 325. Serve with chopped cilantro, sour cream, and chopped tomatoes with your favorite hot sauce. Notes: Add black beans and rice to round out the meal if you have bigger appetites- this can be made in advance with canned beans and rice done in your rice cooker.?#&?#&Keto/Low Carb: Opt for low car tortillas OR use lettuce as your tortilla and pair with full fat sour cream?#&Paleo: Opt for grain free tortillas, such as almond, coconut or cassava tortillas from Siete foods, pair with coconut cream instead of sour cream?#&?#&Night 3: Cajun Chicken Alfredo ?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Boil noodles or pan fry your noodles until they are aldente. Meanwhile, make your sauce.?#&?#&Melt butter, and cream until it begins to simmer. Add the parmesan and let it continue to cook until the parm has melted.?#&?#&Add a tsp or more to taste of your favorite cajun seasoning.?#&?#&Keto: Your’e good to go- Alfredo sauce is naturally Keto (but pasta is not!) You’ll want to use zoodles or mirarcle noodles to be Keto, Low Carb or Paleo.?#&Paleo: You’re going to need to swap the cream with a nut milk and switch the Parmesan with nutritional yeast. The taste won’t be exactly the same but it will still be good. If you still use some parm it will be “paleoish” and still taste great!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'D9AFC770452A2D4483AC18079879F37E', X'942DA763B1BDF24E9115AC6800A60FEE', X'942DA763B1BDF24E9115AC6800A60FEE', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/09/keto-bbq-pork-pizzas/', 'Keto BBQ Pork Pizzas', 2, NULL, 0, 'Keto BBQ Pizzas', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/KETO-BBQ-PORK-Pizzas-72-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '4 personal pizzas', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 Smithfield Slow Roasted Golden Rotisserie Tenderloin?#&4 Low Carb Tortillas?#&1 cup sugar free, low carb BBQ sauce?#&1 cup shredded cheddar/mozzarella cheese?#&1 large bunch fresh oregano', 'American, BBQ', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/09/keto-bbq-pork-pizzas/', 'saute, bake', 'Keto BBQ Pizza, Keto BBQ Pork Pizza, Keto Pizza no fathead dough, keto pizza with low carb tortillas', 'Sep 9, 2019', 'American', 'Instructions?#&?#&Preheat oven to 375 degrees. While the oven preheats, slice the pork tenderloin into small, uniformly sized pieces.?#&Add a tbsp of coconut oil or avocado oil to a skillet and sauté the pork until it reaches an internal temp of 145 degrees; this should take 10 minutes or less.?#&While the pork is sautéing, toast the tortillas for 5 minutes.?#&Remove the tortillas, layer with BBQ sauce, cheese, and pork – equally divided among 4 pizzas.?#&Place pizzas back in the oven for 5 minutes or until the cheese has melted.?#&Remove the pizzas from the oven and garnish with fresh oregano and fresh pepper.?#&?#&Serve immediately!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'CC06EB016E045942B512F00C12A12CE2', X'4D1401541838BE45A68D2C75FD737158', X'4D1401541838BE45A68D2C75FD737158', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/07/cast-iron-grilled-mussels-in-a-white-wine-bacon-herb-butter-sauce/', 'Cast Iron Grilled Mussels in a White Wine, Bacon Herb Butter Sauce', 2, NULL, 0, 'Cast Iron Grilled Mussels in a White Wine, Bacon Herb Butter Sauce', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/DSC_016172-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '3', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 dozen mussels?#&2/3 cup Beringer Main and Vine Pinot Grigio?#&3 tbsp butter?#&1 strip bacon, partially cooked?#&1 small bunch of fresh thyme sprigs?#&4 cloves garlic, minced?#&Salt, to taste?#&1 tsp pepper', 'American, French', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/07/cast-iron-grilled-mussels-in-a-white-wine-bacon-herb-butter-sauce/', 'grill, cast iron', 'how to grill mussels, cast iron grilled mussels', 'Jul 26, 2019', 'american, grilled', 'Instructions?#&?#&Precook a slice of bacon so it is ¾ of the way cooked- this can easily be done in the microwave. Next, add the wine, butter, garlic, bacon (remove fatty parts of the bacon and chop before adding), thyme, salt and pepper.?#&?#&Add the mussels to the cast iron skillet and grill on direct heat over Kingsford Charcoal until the mussels open up- about 15 minutes or less. Serve with grilled or toasted crusty bread like ciabatta or French bread to sop up the white wine sauce.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'325137CECA9A314F92E1842253DE1C73', X'999732CA3849BA4AACFDACD1EC19960E', X'999732CA3849BA4AACFDACD1EC19960E', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/06/low-carb-char-siu-pork-belly-burnt-ends/', 'Low-Carb “Char Siu” Pork Belly Burnt Ends', 2, NULL, 0, 'Low Carb Char Siu Pork Belly Burnt Ends', 'Jon Solberg', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/85C2B6BE-A957-44D6-B29B-F77BB54698A1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '45 min', '3-5 hour', '4-6 hours', '6', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Aluminum foil 1/2 pan?#&Smoking wood of choice, I used four chunks of oak?#&3 lbs. skinless pork belly?#&1½ Tsp of kosher salt (Morton)?#&½ Tsp black pepper (restaurant grind)?#&1 Tbsp olive oil?#&?#&Char Siu sauce:?#&?#&4 Tbsp tamari?#&2 Tbsp natural smooth peanut butter?#&4 Tbsp Sukrin Gold sugar substitute, or whatever sugar substitute you like?#&1 Tbsp oyster sauce?#&4 Tsp rice wine?#&1 Tsp Smoked Paprika?#&3 Tsp sesame oil?#&1 Tsp Louisiana hot sauce?#&1 Tsp ginger powder?#&1 Tsp garlic powder?#&½ Tsp 5-spice powder', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/06/low-carb-char-siu-pork-belly-burnt-ends/', '', 'char siu, 5-spice, pork belly, pork, chinese bbq', 'Jun 6, 2019', '', 'Instructions?#&?#&Cut pork belly into 1” cubes. In a large bowl toss the cubes in the olive oil, salt, and pepper.?#&?#&Combine the remaining ingredients in a saucepan over medium-to-low heat and whisk together until everything is dissolved. Remove the pan from the heat.?#&?#&Set your Big Green Egg up for indirect cooking and get the temperature to 275° and the cooking grate level.?#&?#&Smoke the pork belly with the fat side down until the cubes reach an internal temperature of around 190°f.   This will take around 2-3 hours.?#&?#&Try using a Thermapen for a precise temperature reading.?#&?#&Remove the cubes from the smoker and place in the aluminum ½ pan.?#&?#&Toss in the Char Sui sauce. Coat the cubes well then return to the smoker.?#&?#&Continue to cook uncovered for an additional hour or until the sauce has reduced.?#&?#&Plate and enjoy!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'DDDDB0AB5C0D4B46AC17AD36C5F9E969', X'3FC1227E2CD2EB41901D3FEE6A451099', X'3FC1227E2CD2EB41901D3FEE6A451099', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/fire-roasted-poblano-queso-dip/', 'Fire Roasted Poblano Queso Dip', 2, NULL, 0, 'Fire Roasted Poblano Queso', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/smoked-poblano-queso-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '8', 'Ingredients?#&?#&16 oz Velveeta Queso Blanco (you need to use Velveeta in this recipe because of the way it melts)?#&1 poblano pepper?#&1 roma tomato, sliced in half lengthwise?#&dash smoked paprika?#&large bunch cilantro, added at the end', 'American, Mexican', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/fire-roasted-poblano-queso-dip/', 'Grill', 'smoked cheese dip, smoked queso, smoked poblano queso dip, velveeta mexican dip recipe, cheese dip on pellet smoker', 'Jan 30, 2020', 'Appetizer', 'Instructions?#&?#&Put the Velveeta in a grill safe bowl or cast iron pot. Preheat your grill to 350 degrees.?#&Add the cast iron pot, and let the poblano and tomato roast on the grill.?#&When the cheese has completely melted, and the poblano has begun to char, remove the poblano and tomato.?#&Roughly slice vegetables, and add to the cheese, stirring to combine.?#&Remove the cheese dip from the grill and roughly chop the cilantro and place as garnish on top.?#&Serve with tortilla chips. Or if you are eating low carb, try it with pork rinds.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'FFFB63D006529F41A9543AC95E5849AF', X'F0001C8C63020B4A996CCDE8DAAD4C6B', X'F0001C8C63020B4A996CCDE8DAAD4C6B', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/pimento-cheese-jalapeno-poppers-atomic-buffalo-turds/', 'Pimento Cheese Jalapeno Poppers (Atomic Buffalo Turds)', 2, NULL, 0, 'Pimento Cheese Jalapeno Poppers (Atomic Buffalo Turds)', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Pimento-Cheese-Jalapeno-Poppers-ABT-72-e1580352593740-150x150.jpg', '', '', '10', '10', '20 minutes', '4', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 lb jalapenos, sliced lengthwise with seeds removed?#&1 lb bacon – precook the bacon for 3 minutes in microwave before placing on poppers?#&1/2 cup cream cheese?#&1/2 cup pimento cheese?#&dash bbq rub', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/pimento-cheese-jalapeno-poppers-atomic-buffalo-turds/', 'Grilled', 'ABT, atomic buffalo turds recipe, jalapeno poppers with bacon, cream cheese jalapeno, grilled jalapeno recipe, green mountain grills recipe, gmg jalapeno poppers recipe,', 'Jan 29, 2020', 'Appetizer', 'Instructions?#&?#&Place the cream cheese out so it can soften. Meanwhile, cut the tops off the jalapenos and slice them lengthwise in half, while also removing the seeds.?#&Microwave or cook the bacon so it is halfway done — this is about 3 minutes in the microwave.?#&Mix the cream cheese with the pimento cheese and add a generous scoop in each jalapeno.?#&Add a light dusting of bbq rub to the poppers.?#&Finish with a hearty piece of bacon on the top of the cheese mixture. This can be cut to fit.?#&Cook the jalapeno poppers at 350 degrees on your pellet smoker or grill for about 10 minutes or until the bottoms have begun to form nice char marks and the cheese has begun to melt.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'EDBE80D568514B4792343D825201D8AD', X'9B1F93DDD94E094897F1292BA5BAADA8', X'9B1F93DDD94E094897F1292BA5BAADA8', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/alabama-white-sauce-chicken-wings/', 'Alabama White Sauce Chicken Wings', 2, NULL, 0, 'Alabama White Sauce Wings', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Alabama-White-Sauce-Chicken-wings-72dpi-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 min', '30 min', '35 minutes', '4', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 ¾ cups mayonnaise?#&¾ cup distilled white vinegar?#&½ cup apple juice?#&2 tsp prepared horseradish?#&1 tbsp fresh grated black pepper?#&Juice and zest of one lemon?#&1 tsp sea salt?#&Dash cayenne pepper?#&1 tsp sugar?#&Dash hot sauce?#&Dash smoked paprika, plus more for serving.', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/alabama-white-sauce-chicken-wings/', '', 'alabama white sauce, white bbq sauce recipe, chicken wings white sauce, mayo sauce, green mountain grills recipe idea, green mountain grills chicken wings, gmg recipe', 'Jan 29, 2020', 'Chicken Wings', 'Instructions?#&?#&Sauce Directions:?#&?#&Combine all ingredients in a pint sized mason jar, stir to combine, then shake to mix well. Can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.?#&?#&Grilling Directions:?#&?#&Preheat your pellet smoker to 350. Let chicken wings cook for about 25 minutes, then crank the smoker to 400 to get crispy skin. Use a thermapen or an internal read thermometer (if you use the Green Mountain Grill it comes with its own thermometer and it will tell you! I love that about this grill!) to test internal temperature – once the wings have reached an internal temperature of 170, pull them off the grill. Sprinkle with smoked paprika for color then drizzle with sauce before serving.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'F15D620C0869CD4EAF428B9D777626DB', X'92AAF7545DBE804493570ACC14FB241D', X'92AAF7545DBE804493570ACC14FB241D', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/citrus-and-herb-smoked-whole-snapper/', 'Citrus and Herb Smoked Whole Snapper', 2, NULL, 0, 'Citrus and Herb Smoked Whole Snapper', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/smoked-whole-snapper-1280x640-1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '10 minutes', '30 minutes', '40 minutes', '2', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 Whole Snapper, inside gizzards removed and de-scaled (have your butcher do this for you)?#&1 lemon, thinly sliced?#&1 lime, thinly sliced?#&2 garlic cloves, minced?#&1 small bunch thyme?#&½ tbsp olive oil?#&2 tsp sea salt?#&2 tsp fresh ground pepper', 'American, Seafood', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/citrus-and-herb-smoked-whole-snapper/', 'Smoked, Grilled', 'smoked snapper, how to smoke snapper, how to smoke fish', 'Jan 21, 2020', 'American, Seafood, Fish', 'Instructions?#&?#&1) Drizzle the insides of the snapper first with olive oil, then add the salt, pepper and garlic and spread in the inside of the cavity evenly.?#&?#&2) layer lemon and lime slices in the cavity starting from front to back and then add the thyme sprigs in the cavity. Save any remaining lemon and lime slices for serving with the fish once it’s cooked.?#&?#&3) Place the snapper on a frog mat and smoke until the internal temperature reaches 145 degrees- this will take anywhere from 45 minutes to an hour depending on the size of the fish.?#&?#&4) Once the internal temp has been met, remove and serve immediately with remaining lemon and lime slices. The outer filets will remove pretty cleanly for serving but be extra vigilant about looking for bones before serving guests.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'216A34D58B97D14AAAB102FAF16352D8', X'4D4A4C53993C8A438C5C4FD679899B75', X'4D4A4C53993C8A438C5C4FD679899B75', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake/', 'Smoked S’mores Cheesecake', 2, NULL, 0, 'Smoked S’mores Cheesecake', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake-1280x640-1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '30 minutes', '1 hour and a half', '2 hours', '8', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Equipment:?#&?#&Springform cheesecake pan (2 parts)?#&?#&Crust:?#&?#&12 oz (1 cup and a half) graham crackers, pureed in food processor (If Keto, skip or use almond flour instead)?#&3 tbsp light brown sugar (if Keto, swap with Swerve Brown Sugar)?#&6 tbsp melted butter – coconut oil could also be used?#&?#&Filling:?#&?#&4– 8 oz (block) Neufchatel cheese, room temperature?#&1/3 cup light brown sugar (or if keto, swap with Swerve Brown Sugar)?#&2 tbsp maple syrup (if keto, swap with Choc Zero Maple Syrup)?#&1 tsp lemon zest?#&1 tbsp fresh lemon juice?#&2 tsp vanilla extract?#&1 tbsp butter, melted?#&5 large eggs?#&2/3 cup cold smoked 70% cocoa dark chocolate (cold smoking part is optional) (if Keto, swap with no sugar chocolate, such as Choc Zero Dark Chocolate)?#&1 cup small marshmallows (if Keto, use sugar free marshmallows or skip this ingredient)?#&?#&Plus, additional 1tbsp butter or coconut oil for coating the pan', 'American', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake/', 'Smoked, Grilled, Baked', 'Smoked Cheesecake Recipe, Smores Cheesecake Recipe, How to Smoke a Cheesecake, Traeger Smoked Cheesecake, Keto Cheesecake', 'Jan 20, 2020', 'Dessert, Cheesecake, Keto Cheesecake', 'Instructions?#&?#&Preheat your oven oven to 400 degrees (to bake the crust).?#&?#&Lightly oil your springform pan with a bit of coconut oil or butter. Pulse the graham crackers in the food processor until they have turned into crumbs. Add the brown sugar and gradually add the melted butter until mixed.?#&?#&Press the graham cracker crust into the pan, it will go up the side of the pan about 1/3 of the way, trying to make as even in thickness as possible. Bake for about 8 minutes or until lightly browned.?#&?#&Filling:?#&?#&In a food processor or stand mixer, combine the cream cheese, sugar, maple syrup, vanilla, lemon juice and zest. Gradually add the eggs slowly one by one until everything is well combined.?#&?#&Pour the batter in the springform pan.?#&?#&Smoke the cheesecake for 30 minutes – during this time, the top will become golden from the smoke. Meanwhile, turn the oven to 350 degrees. Remove the cheesecake from the smoker and place in oven and cook for an additional 45 minutes or until the middle no longer ripples when touching it. While cooking in the oven, the cake will expand much more and gain volume on the top that will eventually go back down as the cake continues to cook.?#&?#&Remove from the oven and let cool on the counter for 20 minutes, then transfer to the refrigerator and let the cake cool for a few hours until ready to serve.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'83E58E03B43A254B8291368F96B40449', X'B8EE9D2257E7984781E41C56449820BD', X'B8EE9D2257E7984781E41C56449820BD', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/11/thanksgiving-big-green-egg-turkey-recipe/', 'Guide to Cooking Thanksgiving Turkey on a Big Green Egg', 2, NULL, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/11/thanksgiving-big-green-egg-turkey-recipe/', '', '', 'Nov 5, 2019', '', '');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'04CFD92CF4A86E4B8F78CE0AE07FCE2B', X'B4359FAF5BE0C0489E2B866577ED0898', X'B4359FAF5BE0C0489E2B866577ED0898', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/10/grilled-chicken-for-3-easy-weeknight-meals-plus-keto-and-paleo-options/', 'Grilled Chicken for 3 Easy Weeknight Meals (Plus Keto and Paleo Options)', 2, NULL, 0, 'Grilled Chicken for 3 Easy Weeknight Dinners (Plus Keto and Paleo Options)', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chicken-thighs-on-the-grill72-150x150.jpg', '', '', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '35', '4 lbs grilled chicken', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Grilled Chicken + Salad Night:?#&?#&4 lbs boneless skinless chicken breast?#&1 container arugula?#&Olive oil, balsamic glaze, – or your favorite salad dressing for salad for night #1?#&Your favorite BBQ Rub, you can make your own with my ALL PURPOSE BBQ RUB RECIPE?#&?#&Taco Night:?#&?#&One pack of tortillas?#&1 large bunch Cilantro?#&4 Roma tomatoes?#&2 Avocados?#&?#&Pasta Night?#&?#&3 packages frozen zoodles OR 5 large zucchini that will need to be spiralized OR 1 box fettuccine noodles?#&1 1/2 cups Cream (paleo swap out: coconut cream or a nut butter)?#&1/2 cup Butter?#&1 ½ cups fresh grated Parmesan?#&2 cloves minced garlic', 'American', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/10/grilled-chicken-for-3-easy-weeknight-meals-plus-keto-and-paleo-options/', 'grill', 'grilled chicken for 3 nights of meals, grilled chicken tacos, grilled chicken alfredo, keto friendly chicken alfredo', 'Oct 25, 2019', 'american', 'Instructions?#&?#&Directions For Grilled Chicken:?#&?#&Fill your grill with Kingsford Charcoal Briquettes and prepare your grill for direct heat (charcoal spread out evenly on the bottom versus only on one side). If you would like to learn about how to start a charcoal grill or how to create direct and indirect zones on your grill they are part of my GRILL SCHOOL series which will teach you the fundamentals of grilling!?#&?#&Oil your grill grates with avocado oil or another high heat oil so your chicken doesn’t stick. Grill the chicken thighs on direct heat until the internal temperature reads 170 degrees as determined by an instant read thermometer like the Thermapen or the Thermopop.?#&?#&Remove the chicken from the grill and let rest before cutting into it. Serve with arugula salad and sliced heirloom tomatoes with a drizzle of balsamic glaze and olive oil on the first night. Reserve remaining chicken for dinner on night #2 and #3.?#&?#&Night 1: Chicken and Simple Arugula Salad?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Remove the chicken from the grill and let rest before cutting into it.?#&?#&Serve with arugula salad and sliced heirloom tomatoes with a drizzle of balsamic glaze and olive oil.?#&?#&If you eat carbs, you can easily throw in a grilled Texas Toast or bread to round out the mail. ?#&?#&Night 2: Chicken Tacos?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Reheat about 5-7 chicken thighs and tortillas in the toaster oven at 325. Serve with chopped cilantro, sour cream, and chopped tomatoes with your favorite hot sauce. Notes: Add black beans and rice to round out the meal if you have bigger appetites- this can be made in advance with canned beans and rice done in your rice cooker.?#&?#&Keto/Low Carb: Opt for low car tortillas OR use lettuce as your tortilla and pair with full fat sour cream?#&Paleo: Opt for grain free tortillas, such as almond, coconut or cassava tortillas from Siete foods, pair with coconut cream instead of sour cream?#&?#&Night 3: Cajun Chicken Alfredo ?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Boil noodles or pan fry your noodles until they are aldente. Meanwhile, make your sauce.?#&?#&Melt butter, and cream until it begins to simmer. Add the parmesan and let it continue to cook until the parm has melted.?#&?#&Add a tsp or more to taste of your favorite cajun seasoning.?#&?#&Keto: Your’e good to go- Alfredo sauce is naturally Keto (but pasta is not!) You’ll want to use zoodles or mirarcle noodles to be Keto, Low Carb or Paleo.?#&Paleo: You’re going to need to swap the cream with a nut milk and switch the Parmesan with nutritional yeast. The taste won’t be exactly the same but it will still be good. If you still use some parm it will be “paleoish” and still taste great!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'78249F252F5A524289513C9568D36201', X'959D670DE6E7314280D6A01D303ABACD', X'959D670DE6E7314280D6A01D303ABACD', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/09/keto-bbq-pork-pizzas/', 'Keto BBQ Pork Pizzas', 2, NULL, 0, 'Keto BBQ Pizzas', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/KETO-BBQ-PORK-Pizzas-72-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '4 personal pizzas', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 Smithfield Slow Roasted Golden Rotisserie Tenderloin?#&4 Low Carb Tortillas?#&1 cup sugar free, low carb BBQ sauce?#&1 cup shredded cheddar/mozzarella cheese?#&1 large bunch fresh oregano', 'American, BBQ', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/09/keto-bbq-pork-pizzas/', 'saute, bake', 'Keto BBQ Pizza, Keto BBQ Pork Pizza, Keto Pizza no fathead dough, keto pizza with low carb tortillas', 'Sep 9, 2019', 'American', 'Instructions?#&?#&Preheat oven to 375 degrees. While the oven preheats, slice the pork tenderloin into small, uniformly sized pieces.?#&Add a tbsp of coconut oil or avocado oil to a skillet and sauté the pork until it reaches an internal temp of 145 degrees; this should take 10 minutes or less.?#&While the pork is sautéing, toast the tortillas for 5 minutes.?#&Remove the tortillas, layer with BBQ sauce, cheese, and pork – equally divided among 4 pizzas.?#&Place pizzas back in the oven for 5 minutes or until the cheese has melted.?#&Remove the pizzas from the oven and garnish with fresh oregano and fresh pepper.?#&?#&Serve immediately!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'7FFB03C50B8FEF47A905F4353EA3CCE8', X'EBD01BADFC040F49BD017F579EF8CFC6', X'EBD01BADFC040F49BD017F579EF8CFC6', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/07/cast-iron-grilled-mussels-in-a-white-wine-bacon-herb-butter-sauce/', 'Cast Iron Grilled Mussels in a White Wine, Bacon Herb Butter Sauce', 2, NULL, 0, 'Cast Iron Grilled Mussels in a White Wine, Bacon Herb Butter Sauce', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/DSC_016172-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '3', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 dozen mussels?#&2/3 cup Beringer Main and Vine Pinot Grigio?#&3 tbsp butter?#&1 strip bacon, partially cooked?#&1 small bunch of fresh thyme sprigs?#&4 cloves garlic, minced?#&Salt, to taste?#&1 tsp pepper', 'American, French', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/07/cast-iron-grilled-mussels-in-a-white-wine-bacon-herb-butter-sauce/', 'grill, cast iron', 'how to grill mussels, cast iron grilled mussels', 'Jul 26, 2019', 'american, grilled', 'Instructions?#&?#&Precook a slice of bacon so it is ¾ of the way cooked- this can easily be done in the microwave. Next, add the wine, butter, garlic, bacon (remove fatty parts of the bacon and chop before adding), thyme, salt and pepper.?#&?#&Add the mussels to the cast iron skillet and grill on direct heat over Kingsford Charcoal until the mussels open up- about 15 minutes or less. Serve with grilled or toasted crusty bread like ciabatta or French bread to sop up the white wine sauce.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'F33118DCE6116A4E90377749C3D7FACB', X'D40FA29F0C42E4419765D15AB34B612D', X'D40FA29F0C42E4419765D15AB34B612D', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/06/low-carb-char-siu-pork-belly-burnt-ends/', 'Low-Carb “Char Siu” Pork Belly Burnt Ends', 2, NULL, 0, 'Low Carb Char Siu Pork Belly Burnt Ends', 'Jon Solberg', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/85C2B6BE-A957-44D6-B29B-F77BB54698A1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '45 min', '3-5 hour', '4-6 hours', '6', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Aluminum foil 1/2 pan?#&Smoking wood of choice, I used four chunks of oak?#&3 lbs. skinless pork belly?#&1½ Tsp of kosher salt (Morton)?#&½ Tsp black pepper (restaurant grind)?#&1 Tbsp olive oil?#&?#&Char Siu sauce:?#&?#&4 Tbsp tamari?#&2 Tbsp natural smooth peanut butter?#&4 Tbsp Sukrin Gold sugar substitute, or whatever sugar substitute you like?#&1 Tbsp oyster sauce?#&4 Tsp rice wine?#&1 Tsp Smoked Paprika?#&3 Tsp sesame oil?#&1 Tsp Louisiana hot sauce?#&1 Tsp ginger powder?#&1 Tsp garlic powder?#&½ Tsp 5-spice powder', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/06/low-carb-char-siu-pork-belly-burnt-ends/', '', 'char siu, 5-spice, pork belly, pork, chinese bbq', 'Jun 6, 2019', '', 'Instructions?#&?#&Cut pork belly into 1” cubes. In a large bowl toss the cubes in the olive oil, salt, and pepper.?#&?#&Combine the remaining ingredients in a saucepan over medium-to-low heat and whisk together until everything is dissolved. Remove the pan from the heat.?#&?#&Set your Big Green Egg up for indirect cooking and get the temperature to 275° and the cooking grate level.?#&?#&Smoke the pork belly with the fat side down until the cubes reach an internal temperature of around 190°f.   This will take around 2-3 hours.?#&?#&Try using a Thermapen for a precise temperature reading.?#&?#&Remove the cubes from the smoker and place in the aluminum ½ pan.?#&?#&Toss in the Char Sui sauce. Coat the cubes well then return to the smoker.?#&?#&Continue to cook uncovered for an additional hour or until the sauce has reduced.?#&?#&Plate and enjoy!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'DEF045C7A8EFD34C87844BDB69757EDD', X'AC3610ADB97D374BBF6F12106AE0A198', X'AC3610ADB97D374BBF6F12106AE0A198', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/fire-roasted-poblano-queso-dip/', 'Fire Roasted Poblano Queso Dip', 2, NULL, 0, 'Fire Roasted Poblano Queso', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/smoked-poblano-queso-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '8', 'Ingredients?#&?#&16 oz Velveeta Queso Blanco (you need to use Velveeta in this recipe because of the way it melts)?#&1 poblano pepper?#&1 roma tomato, sliced in half lengthwise?#&dash smoked paprika?#&large bunch cilantro, added at the end', 'American, Mexican', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/fire-roasted-poblano-queso-dip/', 'Grill', 'smoked cheese dip, smoked queso, smoked poblano queso dip, velveeta mexican dip recipe, cheese dip on pellet smoker', 'Jan 30, 2020', 'Appetizer', 'Instructions?#&?#&Put the Velveeta in a grill safe bowl or cast iron pot. Preheat your grill to 350 degrees.?#&Add the cast iron pot, and let the poblano and tomato roast on the grill.?#&When the cheese has completely melted, and the poblano has begun to char, remove the poblano and tomato.?#&Roughly slice vegetables, and add to the cheese, stirring to combine.?#&Remove the cheese dip from the grill and roughly chop the cilantro and place as garnish on top.?#&Serve with tortilla chips. Or if you are eating low carb, try it with pork rinds.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'30EAF6A66908BD4DBF29E304FBD35CDE', X'FE7AE17FA046F9448A6DA8A202147085', X'FE7AE17FA046F9448A6DA8A202147085', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/pimento-cheese-jalapeno-poppers-atomic-buffalo-turds/', 'Pimento Cheese Jalapeno Poppers (Atomic Buffalo Turds)', 2, NULL, 0, 'Pimento Cheese Jalapeno Poppers (Atomic Buffalo Turds)', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Pimento-Cheese-Jalapeno-Poppers-ABT-72-e1580352593740-150x150.jpg', '', '', '10', '10', '20 minutes', '4', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 lb jalapenos, sliced lengthwise with seeds removed?#&1 lb bacon – precook the bacon for 3 minutes in microwave before placing on poppers?#&1/2 cup cream cheese?#&1/2 cup pimento cheese?#&dash bbq rub', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/pimento-cheese-jalapeno-poppers-atomic-buffalo-turds/', 'Grilled', 'ABT, atomic buffalo turds recipe, jalapeno poppers with bacon, cream cheese jalapeno, grilled jalapeno recipe, green mountain grills recipe, gmg jalapeno poppers recipe,', 'Jan 29, 2020', 'Appetizer', 'Instructions?#&?#&Place the cream cheese out so it can soften. Meanwhile, cut the tops off the jalapenos and slice them lengthwise in half, while also removing the seeds.?#&Microwave or cook the bacon so it is halfway done — this is about 3 minutes in the microwave.?#&Mix the cream cheese with the pimento cheese and add a generous scoop in each jalapeno.?#&Add a light dusting of bbq rub to the poppers.?#&Finish with a hearty piece of bacon on the top of the cheese mixture. This can be cut to fit.?#&Cook the jalapeno poppers at 350 degrees on your pellet smoker or grill for about 10 minutes or until the bottoms have begun to form nice char marks and the cheese has begun to melt.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'BC7776811A73114A839D1D289346C906', X'A9A459A3946CD743A4D619E1B6A0D1D4', X'A9A459A3946CD743A4D619E1B6A0D1D4', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/alabama-white-sauce-chicken-wings/', 'Alabama White Sauce Chicken Wings', 2, NULL, 0, 'Alabama White Sauce Wings', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Alabama-White-Sauce-Chicken-wings-72dpi-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 min', '30 min', '35 minutes', '4', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 ¾ cups mayonnaise?#&¾ cup distilled white vinegar?#&½ cup apple juice?#&2 tsp prepared horseradish?#&1 tbsp fresh grated black pepper?#&Juice and zest of one lemon?#&1 tsp sea salt?#&Dash cayenne pepper?#&1 tsp sugar?#&Dash hot sauce?#&Dash smoked paprika, plus more for serving.', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/alabama-white-sauce-chicken-wings/', '', 'alabama white sauce, white bbq sauce recipe, chicken wings white sauce, mayo sauce, green mountain grills recipe idea, green mountain grills chicken wings, gmg recipe', 'Jan 29, 2020', 'Chicken Wings', 'Instructions?#&?#&Sauce Directions:?#&?#&Combine all ingredients in a pint sized mason jar, stir to combine, then shake to mix well. Can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.?#&?#&Grilling Directions:?#&?#&Preheat your pellet smoker to 350. Let chicken wings cook for about 25 minutes, then crank the smoker to 400 to get crispy skin. Use a thermapen or an internal read thermometer (if you use the Green Mountain Grill it comes with its own thermometer and it will tell you! I love that about this grill!) to test internal temperature – once the wings have reached an internal temperature of 170, pull them off the grill. Sprinkle with smoked paprika for color then drizzle with sauce before serving.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'A01064F38116534D905286B8DDF87FFB', X'D5570B7F41595C45AB0F8A3F9284E991', X'D5570B7F41595C45AB0F8A3F9284E991', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/citrus-and-herb-smoked-whole-snapper/', 'Citrus and Herb Smoked Whole Snapper', 2, NULL, 0, 'Citrus and Herb Smoked Whole Snapper', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/smoked-whole-snapper-1280x640-1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '10 minutes', '30 minutes', '40 minutes', '2', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 Whole Snapper, inside gizzards removed and de-scaled (have your butcher do this for you)?#&1 lemon, thinly sliced?#&1 lime, thinly sliced?#&2 garlic cloves, minced?#&1 small bunch thyme?#&½ tbsp olive oil?#&2 tsp sea salt?#&2 tsp fresh ground pepper', 'American, Seafood', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/citrus-and-herb-smoked-whole-snapper/', 'Smoked, Grilled', 'smoked snapper, how to smoke snapper, how to smoke fish', 'Jan 21, 2020', 'American, Seafood, Fish', 'Instructions?#&?#&1) Drizzle the insides of the snapper first with olive oil, then add the salt, pepper and garlic and spread in the inside of the cavity evenly.?#&?#&2) layer lemon and lime slices in the cavity starting from front to back and then add the thyme sprigs in the cavity. Save any remaining lemon and lime slices for serving with the fish once it’s cooked.?#&?#&3) Place the snapper on a frog mat and smoke until the internal temperature reaches 145 degrees- this will take anywhere from 45 minutes to an hour depending on the size of the fish.?#&?#&4) Once the internal temp has been met, remove and serve immediately with remaining lemon and lime slices. The outer filets will remove pretty cleanly for serving but be extra vigilant about looking for bones before serving guests.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'3D7E364ED3A30C49B7C4D6F867E5D8EE', X'42FAF0067CD5A143AB12F6D70881A521', X'42FAF0067CD5A143AB12F6D70881A521', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake/', 'Smoked S’mores Cheesecake', 2, NULL, 0, 'Smoked S’mores Cheesecake', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake-1280x640-1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '30 minutes', '1 hour and a half', '2 hours', '8', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Equipment:?#&?#&Springform cheesecake pan (2 parts)?#&?#&Crust:?#&?#&12 oz (1 cup and a half) graham crackers, pureed in food processor (If Keto, skip or use almond flour instead)?#&3 tbsp light brown sugar (if Keto, swap with Swerve Brown Sugar)?#&6 tbsp melted butter – coconut oil could also be used?#&?#&Filling:?#&?#&4– 8 oz (block) Neufchatel cheese, room temperature?#&1/3 cup light brown sugar (or if keto, swap with Swerve Brown Sugar)?#&2 tbsp maple syrup (if keto, swap with Choc Zero Maple Syrup)?#&1 tsp lemon zest?#&1 tbsp fresh lemon juice?#&2 tsp vanilla extract?#&1 tbsp butter, melted?#&5 large eggs?#&2/3 cup cold smoked 70% cocoa dark chocolate (cold smoking part is optional) (if Keto, swap with no sugar chocolate, such as Choc Zero Dark Chocolate)?#&1 cup small marshmallows (if Keto, use sugar free marshmallows or skip this ingredient)?#&?#&Plus, additional 1tbsp butter or coconut oil for coating the pan', 'American', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake/', 'Smoked, Grilled, Baked', 'Smoked Cheesecake Recipe, Smores Cheesecake Recipe, How to Smoke a Cheesecake, Traeger Smoked Cheesecake, Keto Cheesecake', 'Jan 20, 2020', 'Dessert, Cheesecake, Keto Cheesecake', 'Instructions?#&?#&Preheat your oven oven to 400 degrees (to bake the crust).?#&?#&Lightly oil your springform pan with a bit of coconut oil or butter. Pulse the graham crackers in the food processor until they have turned into crumbs. Add the brown sugar and gradually add the melted butter until mixed.?#&?#&Press the graham cracker crust into the pan, it will go up the side of the pan about 1/3 of the way, trying to make as even in thickness as possible. Bake for about 8 minutes or until lightly browned.?#&?#&Filling:?#&?#&In a food processor or stand mixer, combine the cream cheese, sugar, maple syrup, vanilla, lemon juice and zest. Gradually add the eggs slowly one by one until everything is well combined.?#&?#&Pour the batter in the springform pan.?#&?#&Smoke the cheesecake for 30 minutes – during this time, the top will become golden from the smoke. Meanwhile, turn the oven to 350 degrees. Remove the cheesecake from the smoker and place in oven and cook for an additional 45 minutes or until the middle no longer ripples when touching it. While cooking in the oven, the cake will expand much more and gain volume on the top that will eventually go back down as the cake continues to cook.?#&?#&Remove from the oven and let cool on the counter for 20 minutes, then transfer to the refrigerator and let the cake cool for a few hours until ready to serve.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'BE72EEABC01CC74B9EA6F0A8BF32BE5C', X'DDF62029DAC94841B5E08A68509F04B8', X'DDF62029DAC94841B5E08A68509F04B8', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/11/thanksgiving-big-green-egg-turkey-recipe/', 'Guide to Cooking Thanksgiving Turkey on a Big Green Egg', 2, NULL, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/11/thanksgiving-big-green-egg-turkey-recipe/', '', '', 'Nov 5, 2019', '', '');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'8B9D3AB72A4D8643B088E48DB41F698B', X'DC679E6959F04345BFBA24233B4D4436', X'DC679E6959F04345BFBA24233B4D4436', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/10/grilled-chicken-for-3-easy-weeknight-meals-plus-keto-and-paleo-options/', 'Grilled Chicken for 3 Easy Weeknight Meals (Plus Keto and Paleo Options)', 2, NULL, 0, 'Grilled Chicken for 3 Easy Weeknight Dinners (Plus Keto and Paleo Options)', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chicken-thighs-on-the-grill72-150x150.jpg', '', '', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '35', '4 lbs grilled chicken', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Grilled Chicken + Salad Night:?#&?#&4 lbs boneless skinless chicken breast?#&1 container arugula?#&Olive oil, balsamic glaze, – or your favorite salad dressing for salad for night #1?#&Your favorite BBQ Rub, you can make your own with my ALL PURPOSE BBQ RUB RECIPE?#&?#&Taco Night:?#&?#&One pack of tortillas?#&1 large bunch Cilantro?#&4 Roma tomatoes?#&2 Avocados?#&?#&Pasta Night?#&?#&3 packages frozen zoodles OR 5 large zucchini that will need to be spiralized OR 1 box fettuccine noodles?#&1 1/2 cups Cream (paleo swap out: coconut cream or a nut butter)?#&1/2 cup Butter?#&1 ½ cups fresh grated Parmesan?#&2 cloves minced garlic', 'American', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/10/grilled-chicken-for-3-easy-weeknight-meals-plus-keto-and-paleo-options/', 'grill', 'grilled chicken for 3 nights of meals, grilled chicken tacos, grilled chicken alfredo, keto friendly chicken alfredo', 'Oct 25, 2019', 'american', 'Instructions?#&?#&Directions For Grilled Chicken:?#&?#&Fill your grill with Kingsford Charcoal Briquettes and prepare your grill for direct heat (charcoal spread out evenly on the bottom versus only on one side). If you would like to learn about how to start a charcoal grill or how to create direct and indirect zones on your grill they are part of my GRILL SCHOOL series which will teach you the fundamentals of grilling!?#&?#&Oil your grill grates with avocado oil or another high heat oil so your chicken doesn’t stick. Grill the chicken thighs on direct heat until the internal temperature reads 170 degrees as determined by an instant read thermometer like the Thermapen or the Thermopop.?#&?#&Remove the chicken from the grill and let rest before cutting into it. Serve with arugula salad and sliced heirloom tomatoes with a drizzle of balsamic glaze and olive oil on the first night. Reserve remaining chicken for dinner on night #2 and #3.?#&?#&Night 1: Chicken and Simple Arugula Salad?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Remove the chicken from the grill and let rest before cutting into it.?#&?#&Serve with arugula salad and sliced heirloom tomatoes with a drizzle of balsamic glaze and olive oil.?#&?#&If you eat carbs, you can easily throw in a grilled Texas Toast or bread to round out the mail. ?#&?#&Night 2: Chicken Tacos?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Reheat about 5-7 chicken thighs and tortillas in the toaster oven at 325. Serve with chopped cilantro, sour cream, and chopped tomatoes with your favorite hot sauce. Notes: Add black beans and rice to round out the meal if you have bigger appetites- this can be made in advance with canned beans and rice done in your rice cooker.?#&?#&Keto/Low Carb: Opt for low car tortillas OR use lettuce as your tortilla and pair with full fat sour cream?#&Paleo: Opt for grain free tortillas, such as almond, coconut or cassava tortillas from Siete foods, pair with coconut cream instead of sour cream?#&?#&Night 3: Cajun Chicken Alfredo ?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Boil noodles or pan fry your noodles until they are aldente. Meanwhile, make your sauce.?#&?#&Melt butter, and cream until it begins to simmer. Add the parmesan and let it continue to cook until the parm has melted.?#&?#&Add a tsp or more to taste of your favorite cajun seasoning.?#&?#&Keto: Your’e good to go- Alfredo sauce is naturally Keto (but pasta is not!) You’ll want to use zoodles or mirarcle noodles to be Keto, Low Carb or Paleo.?#&Paleo: You’re going to need to swap the cream with a nut milk and switch the Parmesan with nutritional yeast. The taste won’t be exactly the same but it will still be good. If you still use some parm it will be “paleoish” and still taste great!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'5323CE6344581240B379A6245ED3D36D', X'5C0B841EFC714F418E13372D70446ED6', X'5C0B841EFC714F418E13372D70446ED6', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/09/keto-bbq-pork-pizzas/', 'Keto BBQ Pork Pizzas', 2, NULL, 0, 'Keto BBQ Pizzas', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/KETO-BBQ-PORK-Pizzas-72-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '4 personal pizzas', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 Smithfield Slow Roasted Golden Rotisserie Tenderloin?#&4 Low Carb Tortillas?#&1 cup sugar free, low carb BBQ sauce?#&1 cup shredded cheddar/mozzarella cheese?#&1 large bunch fresh oregano', 'American, BBQ', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/09/keto-bbq-pork-pizzas/', 'saute, bake', 'Keto BBQ Pizza, Keto BBQ Pork Pizza, Keto Pizza no fathead dough, keto pizza with low carb tortillas', 'Sep 9, 2019', 'American', 'Instructions?#&?#&Preheat oven to 375 degrees. While the oven preheats, slice the pork tenderloin into small, uniformly sized pieces.?#&Add a tbsp of coconut oil or avocado oil to a skillet and sauté the pork until it reaches an internal temp of 145 degrees; this should take 10 minutes or less.?#&While the pork is sautéing, toast the tortillas for 5 minutes.?#&Remove the tortillas, layer with BBQ sauce, cheese, and pork – equally divided among 4 pizzas.?#&Place pizzas back in the oven for 5 minutes or until the cheese has melted.?#&Remove the pizzas from the oven and garnish with fresh oregano and fresh pepper.?#&?#&Serve immediately!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'5642F7E594C87445957E80DADC2F6378', X'32D6DA269E100D42BBA270DF6281C97F', X'32D6DA269E100D42BBA270DF6281C97F', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/07/cast-iron-grilled-mussels-in-a-white-wine-bacon-herb-butter-sauce/', 'Cast Iron Grilled Mussels in a White Wine, Bacon Herb Butter Sauce', 2, NULL, 0, 'Cast Iron Grilled Mussels in a White Wine, Bacon Herb Butter Sauce', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/DSC_016172-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '3', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 dozen mussels?#&2/3 cup Beringer Main and Vine Pinot Grigio?#&3 tbsp butter?#&1 strip bacon, partially cooked?#&1 small bunch of fresh thyme sprigs?#&4 cloves garlic, minced?#&Salt, to taste?#&1 tsp pepper', 'American, French', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/07/cast-iron-grilled-mussels-in-a-white-wine-bacon-herb-butter-sauce/', 'grill, cast iron', 'how to grill mussels, cast iron grilled mussels', 'Jul 26, 2019', 'american, grilled', 'Instructions?#&?#&Precook a slice of bacon so it is ¾ of the way cooked- this can easily be done in the microwave. Next, add the wine, butter, garlic, bacon (remove fatty parts of the bacon and chop before adding), thyme, salt and pepper.?#&?#&Add the mussels to the cast iron skillet and grill on direct heat over Kingsford Charcoal until the mussels open up- about 15 minutes or less. Serve with grilled or toasted crusty bread like ciabatta or French bread to sop up the white wine sauce.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'A21900D31ED006499421710B5E6AD979', X'13D047C01EB02045B6C0B9DA29E366C3', X'13D047C01EB02045B6C0B9DA29E366C3', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/06/low-carb-char-siu-pork-belly-burnt-ends/', 'Low-Carb “Char Siu” Pork Belly Burnt Ends', 2, NULL, 0, 'Low Carb Char Siu Pork Belly Burnt Ends', 'Jon Solberg', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/85C2B6BE-A957-44D6-B29B-F77BB54698A1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '45 min', '3-5 hour', '4-6 hours', '6', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Aluminum foil 1/2 pan?#&Smoking wood of choice, I used four chunks of oak?#&3 lbs. skinless pork belly?#&1½ Tsp of kosher salt (Morton)?#&½ Tsp black pepper (restaurant grind)?#&1 Tbsp olive oil?#&?#&Char Siu sauce:?#&?#&4 Tbsp tamari?#&2 Tbsp natural smooth peanut butter?#&4 Tbsp Sukrin Gold sugar substitute, or whatever sugar substitute you like?#&1 Tbsp oyster sauce?#&4 Tsp rice wine?#&1 Tsp Smoked Paprika?#&3 Tsp sesame oil?#&1 Tsp Louisiana hot sauce?#&1 Tsp ginger powder?#&1 Tsp garlic powder?#&½ Tsp 5-spice powder', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/06/low-carb-char-siu-pork-belly-burnt-ends/', '', 'char siu, 5-spice, pork belly, pork, chinese bbq', 'Jun 6, 2019', '', 'Instructions?#&?#&Cut pork belly into 1” cubes. In a large bowl toss the cubes in the olive oil, salt, and pepper.?#&?#&Combine the remaining ingredients in a saucepan over medium-to-low heat and whisk together until everything is dissolved. Remove the pan from the heat.?#&?#&Set your Big Green Egg up for indirect cooking and get the temperature to 275° and the cooking grate level.?#&?#&Smoke the pork belly with the fat side down until the cubes reach an internal temperature of around 190°f.   This will take around 2-3 hours.?#&?#&Try using a Thermapen for a precise temperature reading.?#&?#&Remove the cubes from the smoker and place in the aluminum ½ pan.?#&?#&Toss in the Char Sui sauce. Coat the cubes well then return to the smoker.?#&?#&Continue to cook uncovered for an additional hour or until the sauce has reduced.?#&?#&Plate and enjoy!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'4A84FC17E92A6A4898A39A34AD2FE467', X'5A2EF2E353E5524D91B48C6488D7BD93', X'5A2EF2E353E5524D91B48C6488D7BD93', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/fire-roasted-poblano-queso-dip/', 'Fire Roasted Poblano Queso Dip', 2, NULL, 0, 'Fire Roasted Poblano Queso', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/smoked-poblano-queso-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '8', 'Ingredients?#&?#&16 oz Velveeta Queso Blanco (you need to use Velveeta in this recipe because of the way it melts)?#&1 poblano pepper?#&1 roma tomato, sliced in half lengthwise?#&dash smoked paprika?#&large bunch cilantro, added at the end', 'American, Mexican', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/fire-roasted-poblano-queso-dip/', 'Grill', 'smoked cheese dip, smoked queso, smoked poblano queso dip, velveeta mexican dip recipe, cheese dip on pellet smoker', 'Jan 30, 2020', 'Appetizer', 'Instructions?#&?#&Put the Velveeta in a grill safe bowl or cast iron pot. Preheat your grill to 350 degrees.?#&Add the cast iron pot, and let the poblano and tomato roast on the grill.?#&When the cheese has completely melted, and the poblano has begun to char, remove the poblano and tomato.?#&Roughly slice vegetables, and add to the cheese, stirring to combine.?#&Remove the cheese dip from the grill and roughly chop the cilantro and place as garnish on top.?#&Serve with tortilla chips. Or if you are eating low carb, try it with pork rinds.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'D8F24D322AE0584392194B787EAECFB3', X'C79A2C4F9CCADD45A359612349344132', X'C79A2C4F9CCADD45A359612349344132', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/pimento-cheese-jalapeno-poppers-atomic-buffalo-turds/', 'Pimento Cheese Jalapeno Poppers (Atomic Buffalo Turds)', 2, NULL, 0, 'Pimento Cheese Jalapeno Poppers (Atomic Buffalo Turds)', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Pimento-Cheese-Jalapeno-Poppers-ABT-72-e1580352593740-150x150.jpg', '', '', '10', '10', '20 minutes', '4', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 lb jalapenos, sliced lengthwise with seeds removed?#&1 lb bacon – precook the bacon for 3 minutes in microwave before placing on poppers?#&1/2 cup cream cheese?#&1/2 cup pimento cheese?#&dash bbq rub', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/pimento-cheese-jalapeno-poppers-atomic-buffalo-turds/', 'Grilled', 'ABT, atomic buffalo turds recipe, jalapeno poppers with bacon, cream cheese jalapeno, grilled jalapeno recipe, green mountain grills recipe, gmg jalapeno poppers recipe,', 'Jan 29, 2020', 'Appetizer', 'Instructions?#&?#&Place the cream cheese out so it can soften. Meanwhile, cut the tops off the jalapenos and slice them lengthwise in half, while also removing the seeds.?#&Microwave or cook the bacon so it is halfway done — this is about 3 minutes in the microwave.?#&Mix the cream cheese with the pimento cheese and add a generous scoop in each jalapeno.?#&Add a light dusting of bbq rub to the poppers.?#&Finish with a hearty piece of bacon on the top of the cheese mixture. This can be cut to fit.?#&Cook the jalapeno poppers at 350 degrees on your pellet smoker or grill for about 10 minutes or until the bottoms have begun to form nice char marks and the cheese has begun to melt.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'D89BBB6EA7A3804F8933A176AEC4B7A7', X'8414C00954458A4783B8D71C95D2D938', X'8414C00954458A4783B8D71C95D2D938', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/alabama-white-sauce-chicken-wings/', 'Alabama White Sauce Chicken Wings', 2, NULL, 0, 'Alabama White Sauce Wings', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Alabama-White-Sauce-Chicken-wings-72dpi-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 min', '30 min', '35 minutes', '4', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 ¾ cups mayonnaise?#&¾ cup distilled white vinegar?#&½ cup apple juice?#&2 tsp prepared horseradish?#&1 tbsp fresh grated black pepper?#&Juice and zest of one lemon?#&1 tsp sea salt?#&Dash cayenne pepper?#&1 tsp sugar?#&Dash hot sauce?#&Dash smoked paprika, plus more for serving.', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/alabama-white-sauce-chicken-wings/', '', 'alabama white sauce, white bbq sauce recipe, chicken wings white sauce, mayo sauce, green mountain grills recipe idea, green mountain grills chicken wings, gmg recipe', 'Jan 29, 2020', 'Chicken Wings', 'Instructions?#&?#&Sauce Directions:?#&?#&Combine all ingredients in a pint sized mason jar, stir to combine, then shake to mix well. Can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.?#&?#&Grilling Directions:?#&?#&Preheat your pellet smoker to 350. Let chicken wings cook for about 25 minutes, then crank the smoker to 400 to get crispy skin. Use a thermapen or an internal read thermometer (if you use the Green Mountain Grill it comes with its own thermometer and it will tell you! I love that about this grill!) to test internal temperature – once the wings have reached an internal temperature of 170, pull them off the grill. Sprinkle with smoked paprika for color then drizzle with sauce before serving.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'AB16479996E30143BB270557E73AB6A1', X'7BC47F381869DA4790C124976FC5E562', X'7BC47F381869DA4790C124976FC5E562', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/citrus-and-herb-smoked-whole-snapper/', 'Citrus and Herb Smoked Whole Snapper', 2, NULL, 0, 'Citrus and Herb Smoked Whole Snapper', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/smoked-whole-snapper-1280x640-1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '10 minutes', '30 minutes', '40 minutes', '2', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 Whole Snapper, inside gizzards removed and de-scaled (have your butcher do this for you)?#&1 lemon, thinly sliced?#&1 lime, thinly sliced?#&2 garlic cloves, minced?#&1 small bunch thyme?#&½ tbsp olive oil?#&2 tsp sea salt?#&2 tsp fresh ground pepper', 'American, Seafood', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/citrus-and-herb-smoked-whole-snapper/', 'Smoked, Grilled', 'smoked snapper, how to smoke snapper, how to smoke fish', 'Jan 21, 2020', 'American, Seafood, Fish', 'Instructions?#&?#&1) Drizzle the insides of the snapper first with olive oil, then add the salt, pepper and garlic and spread in the inside of the cavity evenly.?#&?#&2) layer lemon and lime slices in the cavity starting from front to back and then add the thyme sprigs in the cavity. Save any remaining lemon and lime slices for serving with the fish once it’s cooked.?#&?#&3) Place the snapper on a frog mat and smoke until the internal temperature reaches 145 degrees- this will take anywhere from 45 minutes to an hour depending on the size of the fish.?#&?#&4) Once the internal temp has been met, remove and serve immediately with remaining lemon and lime slices. The outer filets will remove pretty cleanly for serving but be extra vigilant about looking for bones before serving guests.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'4A7DE6011340AC4F9CB7F98124DBA5C7', X'4DBEA0106B53AA4AB0B30BA1A2D00CE2', X'4DBEA0106B53AA4AB0B30BA1A2D00CE2', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake/', 'Smoked S’mores Cheesecake', 2, NULL, 0, 'Smoked S’mores Cheesecake', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake-1280x640-1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '30 minutes', '1 hour and a half', '2 hours', '8', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Equipment:?#&?#&Springform cheesecake pan (2 parts)?#&?#&Crust:?#&?#&12 oz (1 cup and a half) graham crackers, pureed in food processor (If Keto, skip or use almond flour instead)?#&3 tbsp light brown sugar (if Keto, swap with Swerve Brown Sugar)?#&6 tbsp melted butter – coconut oil could also be used?#&?#&Filling:?#&?#&4– 8 oz (block) Neufchatel cheese, room temperature?#&1/3 cup light brown sugar (or if keto, swap with Swerve Brown Sugar)?#&2 tbsp maple syrup (if keto, swap with Choc Zero Maple Syrup)?#&1 tsp lemon zest?#&1 tbsp fresh lemon juice?#&2 tsp vanilla extract?#&1 tbsp butter, melted?#&5 large eggs?#&2/3 cup cold smoked 70% cocoa dark chocolate (cold smoking part is optional) (if Keto, swap with no sugar chocolate, such as Choc Zero Dark Chocolate)?#&1 cup small marshmallows (if Keto, use sugar free marshmallows or skip this ingredient)?#&?#&Plus, additional 1tbsp butter or coconut oil for coating the pan', 'American', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake/', 'Smoked, Grilled, Baked', 'Smoked Cheesecake Recipe, Smores Cheesecake Recipe, How to Smoke a Cheesecake, Traeger Smoked Cheesecake, Keto Cheesecake', 'Jan 20, 2020', 'Dessert, Cheesecake, Keto Cheesecake', 'Instructions?#&?#&Preheat your oven oven to 400 degrees (to bake the crust).?#&?#&Lightly oil your springform pan with a bit of coconut oil or butter. Pulse the graham crackers in the food processor until they have turned into crumbs. Add the brown sugar and gradually add the melted butter until mixed.?#&?#&Press the graham cracker crust into the pan, it will go up the side of the pan about 1/3 of the way, trying to make as even in thickness as possible. Bake for about 8 minutes or until lightly browned.?#&?#&Filling:?#&?#&In a food processor or stand mixer, combine the cream cheese, sugar, maple syrup, vanilla, lemon juice and zest. Gradually add the eggs slowly one by one until everything is well combined.?#&?#&Pour the batter in the springform pan.?#&?#&Smoke the cheesecake for 30 minutes – during this time, the top will become golden from the smoke. Meanwhile, turn the oven to 350 degrees. Remove the cheesecake from the smoker and place in oven and cook for an additional 45 minutes or until the middle no longer ripples when touching it. While cooking in the oven, the cake will expand much more and gain volume on the top that will eventually go back down as the cake continues to cook.?#&?#&Remove from the oven and let cool on the counter for 20 minutes, then transfer to the refrigerator and let the cake cool for a few hours until ready to serve.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'2F7FF49C4E86B84384002E868D1D89D8', X'78D557684095B7478D48CAE21F940D34', X'78D557684095B7478D48CAE21F940D34', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/11/thanksgiving-big-green-egg-turkey-recipe/', 'Guide to Cooking Thanksgiving Turkey on a Big Green Egg', 2, NULL, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/11/thanksgiving-big-green-egg-turkey-recipe/', '', '', 'Nov 5, 2019', '', '');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'2537FB09E74AD746A289FFDA971AE61D', X'F1B1C31A025C6C4EA40D608628F93062', X'F1B1C31A025C6C4EA40D608628F93062', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/10/grilled-chicken-for-3-easy-weeknight-meals-plus-keto-and-paleo-options/', 'Grilled Chicken for 3 Easy Weeknight Meals (Plus Keto and Paleo Options)', 2, NULL, 0, 'Grilled Chicken for 3 Easy Weeknight Dinners (Plus Keto and Paleo Options)', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chicken-thighs-on-the-grill72-150x150.jpg', '', '', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '35', '4 lbs grilled chicken', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Grilled Chicken + Salad Night:?#&?#&4 lbs boneless skinless chicken breast?#&1 container arugula?#&Olive oil, balsamic glaze, – or your favorite salad dressing for salad for night #1?#&Your favorite BBQ Rub, you can make your own with my ALL PURPOSE BBQ RUB RECIPE?#&?#&Taco Night:?#&?#&One pack of tortillas?#&1 large bunch Cilantro?#&4 Roma tomatoes?#&2 Avocados?#&?#&Pasta Night?#&?#&3 packages frozen zoodles OR 5 large zucchini that will need to be spiralized OR 1 box fettuccine noodles?#&1 1/2 cups Cream (paleo swap out: coconut cream or a nut butter)?#&1/2 cup Butter?#&1 ½ cups fresh grated Parmesan?#&2 cloves minced garlic', 'American', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/10/grilled-chicken-for-3-easy-weeknight-meals-plus-keto-and-paleo-options/', 'grill', 'grilled chicken for 3 nights of meals, grilled chicken tacos, grilled chicken alfredo, keto friendly chicken alfredo', 'Oct 25, 2019', 'american', 'Instructions?#&?#&Directions For Grilled Chicken:?#&?#&Fill your grill with Kingsford Charcoal Briquettes and prepare your grill for direct heat (charcoal spread out evenly on the bottom versus only on one side). If you would like to learn about how to start a charcoal grill or how to create direct and indirect zones on your grill they are part of my GRILL SCHOOL series which will teach you the fundamentals of grilling!?#&?#&Oil your grill grates with avocado oil or another high heat oil so your chicken doesn’t stick. Grill the chicken thighs on direct heat until the internal temperature reads 170 degrees as determined by an instant read thermometer like the Thermapen or the Thermopop.?#&?#&Remove the chicken from the grill and let rest before cutting into it. Serve with arugula salad and sliced heirloom tomatoes with a drizzle of balsamic glaze and olive oil on the first night. Reserve remaining chicken for dinner on night #2 and #3.?#&?#&Night 1: Chicken and Simple Arugula Salad?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Remove the chicken from the grill and let rest before cutting into it.?#&?#&Serve with arugula salad and sliced heirloom tomatoes with a drizzle of balsamic glaze and olive oil.?#&?#&If you eat carbs, you can easily throw in a grilled Texas Toast or bread to round out the mail. ?#&?#&Night 2: Chicken Tacos?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Reheat about 5-7 chicken thighs and tortillas in the toaster oven at 325. Serve with chopped cilantro, sour cream, and chopped tomatoes with your favorite hot sauce. Notes: Add black beans and rice to round out the meal if you have bigger appetites- this can be made in advance with canned beans and rice done in your rice cooker.?#&?#&Keto/Low Carb: Opt for low car tortillas OR use lettuce as your tortilla and pair with full fat sour cream?#&Paleo: Opt for grain free tortillas, such as almond, coconut or cassava tortillas from Siete foods, pair with coconut cream instead of sour cream?#&?#&Night 3: Cajun Chicken Alfredo ?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Boil noodles or pan fry your noodles until they are aldente. Meanwhile, make your sauce.?#&?#&Melt butter, and cream until it begins to simmer. Add the parmesan and let it continue to cook until the parm has melted.?#&?#&Add a tsp or more to taste of your favorite cajun seasoning.?#&?#&Keto: Your’e good to go- Alfredo sauce is naturally Keto (but pasta is not!) You’ll want to use zoodles or mirarcle noodles to be Keto, Low Carb or Paleo.?#&Paleo: You’re going to need to swap the cream with a nut milk and switch the Parmesan with nutritional yeast. The taste won’t be exactly the same but it will still be good. If you still use some parm it will be “paleoish” and still taste great!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'84A8FF88E7745547910E29512D575404', X'0647DF832F6B4648B6DFF2871E6F0C8B', X'0647DF832F6B4648B6DFF2871E6F0C8B', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/09/keto-bbq-pork-pizzas/', 'Keto BBQ Pork Pizzas', 2, NULL, 0, 'Keto BBQ Pizzas', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/KETO-BBQ-PORK-Pizzas-72-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '4 personal pizzas', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 Smithfield Slow Roasted Golden Rotisserie Tenderloin?#&4 Low Carb Tortillas?#&1 cup sugar free, low carb BBQ sauce?#&1 cup shredded cheddar/mozzarella cheese?#&1 large bunch fresh oregano', 'American, BBQ', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/09/keto-bbq-pork-pizzas/', 'saute, bake', 'Keto BBQ Pizza, Keto BBQ Pork Pizza, Keto Pizza no fathead dough, keto pizza with low carb tortillas', 'Sep 9, 2019', 'American', 'Instructions?#&?#&Preheat oven to 375 degrees. While the oven preheats, slice the pork tenderloin into small, uniformly sized pieces.?#&Add a tbsp of coconut oil or avocado oil to a skillet and sauté the pork until it reaches an internal temp of 145 degrees; this should take 10 minutes or less.?#&While the pork is sautéing, toast the tortillas for 5 minutes.?#&Remove the tortillas, layer with BBQ sauce, cheese, and pork – equally divided among 4 pizzas.?#&Place pizzas back in the oven for 5 minutes or until the cheese has melted.?#&Remove the pizzas from the oven and garnish with fresh oregano and fresh pepper.?#&?#&Serve immediately!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'CCBA9D2095138340964120DAE31DF6DD', X'9A294FEDF52A8C45A6C3D9A2DF5E9BB2', X'9A294FEDF52A8C45A6C3D9A2DF5E9BB2', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/07/cast-iron-grilled-mussels-in-a-white-wine-bacon-herb-butter-sauce/', 'Cast Iron Grilled Mussels in a White Wine, Bacon Herb Butter Sauce', 2, NULL, 0, 'Cast Iron Grilled Mussels in a White Wine, Bacon Herb Butter Sauce', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/DSC_016172-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '3', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 dozen mussels?#&2/3 cup Beringer Main and Vine Pinot Grigio?#&3 tbsp butter?#&1 strip bacon, partially cooked?#&1 small bunch of fresh thyme sprigs?#&4 cloves garlic, minced?#&Salt, to taste?#&1 tsp pepper', 'American, French', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/07/cast-iron-grilled-mussels-in-a-white-wine-bacon-herb-butter-sauce/', 'grill, cast iron', 'how to grill mussels, cast iron grilled mussels', 'Jul 26, 2019', 'american, grilled', 'Instructions?#&?#&Precook a slice of bacon so it is ¾ of the way cooked- this can easily be done in the microwave. Next, add the wine, butter, garlic, bacon (remove fatty parts of the bacon and chop before adding), thyme, salt and pepper.?#&?#&Add the mussels to the cast iron skillet and grill on direct heat over Kingsford Charcoal until the mussels open up- about 15 minutes or less. Serve with grilled or toasted crusty bread like ciabatta or French bread to sop up the white wine sauce.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'180FDB153110874DACF1D084A0FA2A07', X'ACEDA02049057D47B0BE2175CCEC8DA3', X'ACEDA02049057D47B0BE2175CCEC8DA3', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/06/low-carb-char-siu-pork-belly-burnt-ends/', 'Low-Carb “Char Siu” Pork Belly Burnt Ends', 2, NULL, 0, 'Low Carb Char Siu Pork Belly Burnt Ends', 'Jon Solberg', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/85C2B6BE-A957-44D6-B29B-F77BB54698A1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '45 min', '3-5 hour', '4-6 hours', '6', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Aluminum foil 1/2 pan?#&Smoking wood of choice, I used four chunks of oak?#&3 lbs. skinless pork belly?#&1½ Tsp of kosher salt (Morton)?#&½ Tsp black pepper (restaurant grind)?#&1 Tbsp olive oil?#&?#&Char Siu sauce:?#&?#&4 Tbsp tamari?#&2 Tbsp natural smooth peanut butter?#&4 Tbsp Sukrin Gold sugar substitute, or whatever sugar substitute you like?#&1 Tbsp oyster sauce?#&4 Tsp rice wine?#&1 Tsp Smoked Paprika?#&3 Tsp sesame oil?#&1 Tsp Louisiana hot sauce?#&1 Tsp ginger powder?#&1 Tsp garlic powder?#&½ Tsp 5-spice powder', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/06/low-carb-char-siu-pork-belly-burnt-ends/', '', 'char siu, 5-spice, pork belly, pork, chinese bbq', 'Jun 6, 2019', '', 'Instructions?#&?#&Cut pork belly into 1” cubes. In a large bowl toss the cubes in the olive oil, salt, and pepper.?#&?#&Combine the remaining ingredients in a saucepan over medium-to-low heat and whisk together until everything is dissolved. Remove the pan from the heat.?#&?#&Set your Big Green Egg up for indirect cooking and get the temperature to 275° and the cooking grate level.?#&?#&Smoke the pork belly with the fat side down until the cubes reach an internal temperature of around 190°f.   This will take around 2-3 hours.?#&?#&Try using a Thermapen for a precise temperature reading.?#&?#&Remove the cubes from the smoker and place in the aluminum ½ pan.?#&?#&Toss in the Char Sui sauce. Coat the cubes well then return to the smoker.?#&?#&Continue to cook uncovered for an additional hour or until the sauce has reduced.?#&?#&Plate and enjoy!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'32FA0DCC3801024F838D2593409EC9DF', X'F9D153CC25201340AD70F3637D06AFFF', X'F9D153CC25201340AD70F3637D06AFFF', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/fire-roasted-poblano-queso-dip/', 'Fire Roasted Poblano Queso Dip', 2, NULL, 0, 'Fire Roasted Poblano Queso', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/smoked-poblano-queso-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '8', 'Ingredients?#&?#&16 oz Velveeta Queso Blanco (you need to use Velveeta in this recipe because of the way it melts)?#&1 poblano pepper?#&1 roma tomato, sliced in half lengthwise?#&dash smoked paprika?#&large bunch cilantro, added at the end', 'American, Mexican', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/fire-roasted-poblano-queso-dip/', 'Grill', 'smoked cheese dip, smoked queso, smoked poblano queso dip, velveeta mexican dip recipe, cheese dip on pellet smoker', 'Jan 30, 2020', 'Appetizer', 'Instructions?#&?#&Put the Velveeta in a grill safe bowl or cast iron pot. Preheat your grill to 350 degrees.?#&Add the cast iron pot, and let the poblano and tomato roast on the grill.?#&When the cheese has completely melted, and the poblano has begun to char, remove the poblano and tomato.?#&Roughly slice vegetables, and add to the cheese, stirring to combine.?#&Remove the cheese dip from the grill and roughly chop the cilantro and place as garnish on top.?#&Serve with tortilla chips. Or if you are eating low carb, try it with pork rinds.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'A246E4C3DDEAFD44B2760F5E0B284313', X'793D693BEE7FA64390137150892DDD19', X'793D693BEE7FA64390137150892DDD19', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/pimento-cheese-jalapeno-poppers-atomic-buffalo-turds/', 'Pimento Cheese Jalapeno Poppers (Atomic Buffalo Turds)', 2, NULL, 0, 'Pimento Cheese Jalapeno Poppers (Atomic Buffalo Turds)', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Pimento-Cheese-Jalapeno-Poppers-ABT-72-e1580352593740-150x150.jpg', '', '', '10', '10', '20 minutes', '4', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 lb jalapenos, sliced lengthwise with seeds removed?#&1 lb bacon – precook the bacon for 3 minutes in microwave before placing on poppers?#&1/2 cup cream cheese?#&1/2 cup pimento cheese?#&dash bbq rub', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/pimento-cheese-jalapeno-poppers-atomic-buffalo-turds/', 'Grilled', 'ABT, atomic buffalo turds recipe, jalapeno poppers with bacon, cream cheese jalapeno, grilled jalapeno recipe, green mountain grills recipe, gmg jalapeno poppers recipe,', 'Jan 29, 2020', 'Appetizer', 'Instructions?#&?#&Place the cream cheese out so it can soften. Meanwhile, cut the tops off the jalapenos and slice them lengthwise in half, while also removing the seeds.?#&Microwave or cook the bacon so it is halfway done — this is about 3 minutes in the microwave.?#&Mix the cream cheese with the pimento cheese and add a generous scoop in each jalapeno.?#&Add a light dusting of bbq rub to the poppers.?#&Finish with a hearty piece of bacon on the top of the cheese mixture. This can be cut to fit.?#&Cook the jalapeno poppers at 350 degrees on your pellet smoker or grill for about 10 minutes or until the bottoms have begun to form nice char marks and the cheese has begun to melt.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'2E9B23EF87125249B158DB4F58C43B9E', X'50698E48D41E6F4D9ACF2909C7849098', X'50698E48D41E6F4D9ACF2909C7849098', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/alabama-white-sauce-chicken-wings/', 'Alabama White Sauce Chicken Wings', 2, NULL, 0, 'Alabama White Sauce Wings', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Alabama-White-Sauce-Chicken-wings-72dpi-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 min', '30 min', '35 minutes', '4', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 ¾ cups mayonnaise?#&¾ cup distilled white vinegar?#&½ cup apple juice?#&2 tsp prepared horseradish?#&1 tbsp fresh grated black pepper?#&Juice and zest of one lemon?#&1 tsp sea salt?#&Dash cayenne pepper?#&1 tsp sugar?#&Dash hot sauce?#&Dash smoked paprika, plus more for serving.', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/alabama-white-sauce-chicken-wings/', '', 'alabama white sauce, white bbq sauce recipe, chicken wings white sauce, mayo sauce, green mountain grills recipe idea, green mountain grills chicken wings, gmg recipe', 'Jan 29, 2020', 'Chicken Wings', 'Instructions?#&?#&Sauce Directions:?#&?#&Combine all ingredients in a pint sized mason jar, stir to combine, then shake to mix well. Can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.?#&?#&Grilling Directions:?#&?#&Preheat your pellet smoker to 350. Let chicken wings cook for about 25 minutes, then crank the smoker to 400 to get crispy skin. Use a thermapen or an internal read thermometer (if you use the Green Mountain Grill it comes with its own thermometer and it will tell you! I love that about this grill!) to test internal temperature – once the wings have reached an internal temperature of 170, pull them off the grill. Sprinkle with smoked paprika for color then drizzle with sauce before serving.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'589D7FC63B5896478319251C78D6D3D3', X'B75EA848A59DB746B7C4B63B1FCFDE3F', X'B75EA848A59DB746B7C4B63B1FCFDE3F', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/citrus-and-herb-smoked-whole-snapper/', 'Citrus and Herb Smoked Whole Snapper', 2, NULL, 0, 'Citrus and Herb Smoked Whole Snapper', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/smoked-whole-snapper-1280x640-1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '10 minutes', '30 minutes', '40 minutes', '2', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 Whole Snapper, inside gizzards removed and de-scaled (have your butcher do this for you)?#&1 lemon, thinly sliced?#&1 lime, thinly sliced?#&2 garlic cloves, minced?#&1 small bunch thyme?#&½ tbsp olive oil?#&2 tsp sea salt?#&2 tsp fresh ground pepper', 'American, Seafood', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/citrus-and-herb-smoked-whole-snapper/', 'Smoked, Grilled', 'smoked snapper, how to smoke snapper, how to smoke fish', 'Jan 21, 2020', 'American, Seafood, Fish', 'Instructions?#&?#&1) Drizzle the insides of the snapper first with olive oil, then add the salt, pepper and garlic and spread in the inside of the cavity evenly.?#&?#&2) layer lemon and lime slices in the cavity starting from front to back and then add the thyme sprigs in the cavity. Save any remaining lemon and lime slices for serving with the fish once it’s cooked.?#&?#&3) Place the snapper on a frog mat and smoke until the internal temperature reaches 145 degrees- this will take anywhere from 45 minutes to an hour depending on the size of the fish.?#&?#&4) Once the internal temp has been met, remove and serve immediately with remaining lemon and lime slices. The outer filets will remove pretty cleanly for serving but be extra vigilant about looking for bones before serving guests.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'7489FF1F956401438ACE10DBF029E9BE', X'B43BD6A5563E9145AFB571FDA7C76E00', X'B43BD6A5563E9145AFB571FDA7C76E00', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake/', 'Smoked S’mores Cheesecake', 2, NULL, 0, 'Smoked S’mores Cheesecake', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake-1280x640-1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '30 minutes', '1 hour and a half', '2 hours', '8', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Equipment:?#&?#&Springform cheesecake pan (2 parts)?#&?#&Crust:?#&?#&12 oz (1 cup and a half) graham crackers, pureed in food processor (If Keto, skip or use almond flour instead)?#&3 tbsp light brown sugar (if Keto, swap with Swerve Brown Sugar)?#&6 tbsp melted butter – coconut oil could also be used?#&?#&Filling:?#&?#&4– 8 oz (block) Neufchatel cheese, room temperature?#&1/3 cup light brown sugar (or if keto, swap with Swerve Brown Sugar)?#&2 tbsp maple syrup (if keto, swap with Choc Zero Maple Syrup)?#&1 tsp lemon zest?#&1 tbsp fresh lemon juice?#&2 tsp vanilla extract?#&1 tbsp butter, melted?#&5 large eggs?#&2/3 cup cold smoked 70% cocoa dark chocolate (cold smoking part is optional) (if Keto, swap with no sugar chocolate, such as Choc Zero Dark Chocolate)?#&1 cup small marshmallows (if Keto, use sugar free marshmallows or skip this ingredient)?#&?#&Plus, additional 1tbsp butter or coconut oil for coating the pan', 'American', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake/', 'Smoked, Grilled, Baked', 'Smoked Cheesecake Recipe, Smores Cheesecake Recipe, How to Smoke a Cheesecake, Traeger Smoked Cheesecake, Keto Cheesecake', 'Jan 20, 2020', 'Dessert, Cheesecake, Keto Cheesecake', 'Instructions?#&?#&Preheat your oven oven to 400 degrees (to bake the crust).?#&?#&Lightly oil your springform pan with a bit of coconut oil or butter. Pulse the graham crackers in the food processor until they have turned into crumbs. Add the brown sugar and gradually add the melted butter until mixed.?#&?#&Press the graham cracker crust into the pan, it will go up the side of the pan about 1/3 of the way, trying to make as even in thickness as possible. Bake for about 8 minutes or until lightly browned.?#&?#&Filling:?#&?#&In a food processor or stand mixer, combine the cream cheese, sugar, maple syrup, vanilla, lemon juice and zest. Gradually add the eggs slowly one by one until everything is well combined.?#&?#&Pour the batter in the springform pan.?#&?#&Smoke the cheesecake for 30 minutes – during this time, the top will become golden from the smoke. Meanwhile, turn the oven to 350 degrees. Remove the cheesecake from the smoker and place in oven and cook for an additional 45 minutes or until the middle no longer ripples when touching it. While cooking in the oven, the cake will expand much more and gain volume on the top that will eventually go back down as the cake continues to cook.?#&?#&Remove from the oven and let cool on the counter for 20 minutes, then transfer to the refrigerator and let the cake cool for a few hours until ready to serve.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'B913077D1332E94195B768FBF2E474F8', X'FDEC24F3EFEB6B489320A645C7664747', X'FDEC24F3EFEB6B489320A645C7664747', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/11/thanksgiving-big-green-egg-turkey-recipe/', 'Guide to Cooking Thanksgiving Turkey on a Big Green Egg', 2, NULL, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/11/thanksgiving-big-green-egg-turkey-recipe/', '', '', 'Nov 5, 2019', '', '');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'1EA9DA53839ED340BC849504F7F4E276', X'3DFDD4015354D74E9F31A8CC05DF277A', X'3DFDD4015354D74E9F31A8CC05DF277A', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/10/grilled-chicken-for-3-easy-weeknight-meals-plus-keto-and-paleo-options/', 'Grilled Chicken for 3 Easy Weeknight Meals (Plus Keto and Paleo Options)', 2, NULL, 0, 'Grilled Chicken for 3 Easy Weeknight Dinners (Plus Keto and Paleo Options)', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chicken-thighs-on-the-grill72-150x150.jpg', '', '', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '35', '4 lbs grilled chicken', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Grilled Chicken + Salad Night:?#&?#&4 lbs boneless skinless chicken breast?#&1 container arugula?#&Olive oil, balsamic glaze, – or your favorite salad dressing for salad for night #1?#&Your favorite BBQ Rub, you can make your own with my ALL PURPOSE BBQ RUB RECIPE?#&?#&Taco Night:?#&?#&One pack of tortillas?#&1 large bunch Cilantro?#&4 Roma tomatoes?#&2 Avocados?#&?#&Pasta Night?#&?#&3 packages frozen zoodles OR 5 large zucchini that will need to be spiralized OR 1 box fettuccine noodles?#&1 1/2 cups Cream (paleo swap out: coconut cream or a nut butter)?#&1/2 cup Butter?#&1 ½ cups fresh grated Parmesan?#&2 cloves minced garlic', 'American', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/10/grilled-chicken-for-3-easy-weeknight-meals-plus-keto-and-paleo-options/', 'grill', 'grilled chicken for 3 nights of meals, grilled chicken tacos, grilled chicken alfredo, keto friendly chicken alfredo', 'Oct 25, 2019', 'american', 'Instructions?#&?#&Directions For Grilled Chicken:?#&?#&Fill your grill with Kingsford Charcoal Briquettes and prepare your grill for direct heat (charcoal spread out evenly on the bottom versus only on one side). If you would like to learn about how to start a charcoal grill or how to create direct and indirect zones on your grill they are part of my GRILL SCHOOL series which will teach you the fundamentals of grilling!?#&?#&Oil your grill grates with avocado oil or another high heat oil so your chicken doesn’t stick. Grill the chicken thighs on direct heat until the internal temperature reads 170 degrees as determined by an instant read thermometer like the Thermapen or the Thermopop.?#&?#&Remove the chicken from the grill and let rest before cutting into it. Serve with arugula salad and sliced heirloom tomatoes with a drizzle of balsamic glaze and olive oil on the first night. Reserve remaining chicken for dinner on night #2 and #3.?#&?#&Night 1: Chicken and Simple Arugula Salad?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Remove the chicken from the grill and let rest before cutting into it.?#&?#&Serve with arugula salad and sliced heirloom tomatoes with a drizzle of balsamic glaze and olive oil.?#&?#&If you eat carbs, you can easily throw in a grilled Texas Toast or bread to round out the mail. ?#&?#&Night 2: Chicken Tacos?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Reheat about 5-7 chicken thighs and tortillas in the toaster oven at 325. Serve with chopped cilantro, sour cream, and chopped tomatoes with your favorite hot sauce. Notes: Add black beans and rice to round out the meal if you have bigger appetites- this can be made in advance with canned beans and rice done in your rice cooker.?#&?#&Keto/Low Carb: Opt for low car tortillas OR use lettuce as your tortilla and pair with full fat sour cream?#&Paleo: Opt for grain free tortillas, such as almond, coconut or cassava tortillas from Siete foods, pair with coconut cream instead of sour cream?#&?#&Night 3: Cajun Chicken Alfredo ?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Boil noodles or pan fry your noodles until they are aldente. Meanwhile, make your sauce.?#&?#&Melt butter, and cream until it begins to simmer. Add the parmesan and let it continue to cook until the parm has melted.?#&?#&Add a tsp or more to taste of your favorite cajun seasoning.?#&?#&Keto: Your’e good to go- Alfredo sauce is naturally Keto (but pasta is not!) You’ll want to use zoodles or mirarcle noodles to be Keto, Low Carb or Paleo.?#&Paleo: You’re going to need to swap the cream with a nut milk and switch the Parmesan with nutritional yeast. The taste won’t be exactly the same but it will still be good. If you still use some parm it will be “paleoish” and still taste great!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'E18E9836FFA06442ACB1DDCCD0C558D5', X'3C03A9A55166F641A2B2B74C2320461F', X'3C03A9A55166F641A2B2B74C2320461F', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/09/keto-bbq-pork-pizzas/', 'Keto BBQ Pork Pizzas', 2, NULL, 0, 'Keto BBQ Pizzas', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/KETO-BBQ-PORK-Pizzas-72-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '4 personal pizzas', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 Smithfield Slow Roasted Golden Rotisserie Tenderloin?#&4 Low Carb Tortillas?#&1 cup sugar free, low carb BBQ sauce?#&1 cup shredded cheddar/mozzarella cheese?#&1 large bunch fresh oregano', 'American, BBQ', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/09/keto-bbq-pork-pizzas/', 'saute, bake', 'Keto BBQ Pizza, Keto BBQ Pork Pizza, Keto Pizza no fathead dough, keto pizza with low carb tortillas', 'Sep 9, 2019', 'American', 'Instructions?#&?#&Preheat oven to 375 degrees. While the oven preheats, slice the pork tenderloin into small, uniformly sized pieces.?#&Add a tbsp of coconut oil or avocado oil to a skillet and sauté the pork until it reaches an internal temp of 145 degrees; this should take 10 minutes or less.?#&While the pork is sautéing, toast the tortillas for 5 minutes.?#&Remove the tortillas, layer with BBQ sauce, cheese, and pork – equally divided among 4 pizzas.?#&Place pizzas back in the oven for 5 minutes or until the cheese has melted.?#&Remove the pizzas from the oven and garnish with fresh oregano and fresh pepper.?#&?#&Serve immediately!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'93BE98AF3ABC134FBA0AE691CA2F8034', X'70C01B0A0C478541870B32AD4BAF12A8', X'70C01B0A0C478541870B32AD4BAF12A8', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/07/cast-iron-grilled-mussels-in-a-white-wine-bacon-herb-butter-sauce/', 'Cast Iron Grilled Mussels in a White Wine, Bacon Herb Butter Sauce', 2, NULL, 0, 'Cast Iron Grilled Mussels in a White Wine, Bacon Herb Butter Sauce', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/DSC_016172-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '3', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 dozen mussels?#&2/3 cup Beringer Main and Vine Pinot Grigio?#&3 tbsp butter?#&1 strip bacon, partially cooked?#&1 small bunch of fresh thyme sprigs?#&4 cloves garlic, minced?#&Salt, to taste?#&1 tsp pepper', 'American, French', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/07/cast-iron-grilled-mussels-in-a-white-wine-bacon-herb-butter-sauce/', 'grill, cast iron', 'how to grill mussels, cast iron grilled mussels', 'Jul 26, 2019', 'american, grilled', 'Instructions?#&?#&Precook a slice of bacon so it is ¾ of the way cooked- this can easily be done in the microwave. Next, add the wine, butter, garlic, bacon (remove fatty parts of the bacon and chop before adding), thyme, salt and pepper.?#&?#&Add the mussels to the cast iron skillet and grill on direct heat over Kingsford Charcoal until the mussels open up- about 15 minutes or less. Serve with grilled or toasted crusty bread like ciabatta or French bread to sop up the white wine sauce.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'635AAAAD88058E42A866ED07EEC10427', X'20ADCC73525A53408E76AAA9817BC760', X'20ADCC73525A53408E76AAA9817BC760', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/06/low-carb-char-siu-pork-belly-burnt-ends/', 'Low-Carb “Char Siu” Pork Belly Burnt Ends', 2, NULL, 0, 'Low Carb Char Siu Pork Belly Burnt Ends', 'Jon Solberg', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/85C2B6BE-A957-44D6-B29B-F77BB54698A1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '45 min', '3-5 hour', '4-6 hours', '6', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Aluminum foil 1/2 pan?#&Smoking wood of choice, I used four chunks of oak?#&3 lbs. skinless pork belly?#&1½ Tsp of kosher salt (Morton)?#&½ Tsp black pepper (restaurant grind)?#&1 Tbsp olive oil?#&?#&Char Siu sauce:?#&?#&4 Tbsp tamari?#&2 Tbsp natural smooth peanut butter?#&4 Tbsp Sukrin Gold sugar substitute, or whatever sugar substitute you like?#&1 Tbsp oyster sauce?#&4 Tsp rice wine?#&1 Tsp Smoked Paprika?#&3 Tsp sesame oil?#&1 Tsp Louisiana hot sauce?#&1 Tsp ginger powder?#&1 Tsp garlic powder?#&½ Tsp 5-spice powder', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/06/low-carb-char-siu-pork-belly-burnt-ends/', '', 'char siu, 5-spice, pork belly, pork, chinese bbq', 'Jun 6, 2019', '', 'Instructions?#&?#&Cut pork belly into 1” cubes. In a large bowl toss the cubes in the olive oil, salt, and pepper.?#&?#&Combine the remaining ingredients in a saucepan over medium-to-low heat and whisk together until everything is dissolved. Remove the pan from the heat.?#&?#&Set your Big Green Egg up for indirect cooking and get the temperature to 275° and the cooking grate level.?#&?#&Smoke the pork belly with the fat side down until the cubes reach an internal temperature of around 190°f.   This will take around 2-3 hours.?#&?#&Try using a Thermapen for a precise temperature reading.?#&?#&Remove the cubes from the smoker and place in the aluminum ½ pan.?#&?#&Toss in the Char Sui sauce. Coat the cubes well then return to the smoker.?#&?#&Continue to cook uncovered for an additional hour or until the sauce has reduced.?#&?#&Plate and enjoy!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'9869D60EBC074D48A598ED42BBD38C72', X'DD7492EA304D5F40873E8F48C7A9E61D', X'DD7492EA304D5F40873E8F48C7A9E61D', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/fire-roasted-poblano-queso-dip/', 'Fire Roasted Poblano Queso Dip', 2, NULL, 0, 'Fire Roasted Poblano Queso', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/smoked-poblano-queso-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '8', 'Ingredients?#&?#&16 oz Velveeta Queso Blanco (you need to use Velveeta in this recipe because of the way it melts)?#&1 poblano pepper?#&1 roma tomato, sliced in half lengthwise?#&dash smoked paprika?#&large bunch cilantro, added at the end', 'American, Mexican', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/fire-roasted-poblano-queso-dip/', 'Grill', 'smoked cheese dip, smoked queso, smoked poblano queso dip, velveeta mexican dip recipe, cheese dip on pellet smoker', 'Jan 30, 2020', 'Appetizer', 'Instructions?#&?#&Put the Velveeta in a grill safe bowl or cast iron pot. Preheat your grill to 350 degrees.?#&Add the cast iron pot, and let the poblano and tomato roast on the grill.?#&When the cheese has completely melted, and the poblano has begun to char, remove the poblano and tomato.?#&Roughly slice vegetables, and add to the cheese, stirring to combine.?#&Remove the cheese dip from the grill and roughly chop the cilantro and place as garnish on top.?#&Serve with tortilla chips. Or if you are eating low carb, try it with pork rinds.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'65EB2F034D104E4D83CB25FADE827539', X'1E8C8FA35F25C84399E87C017E6863EA', X'1E8C8FA35F25C84399E87C017E6863EA', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/pimento-cheese-jalapeno-poppers-atomic-buffalo-turds/', 'Pimento Cheese Jalapeno Poppers (Atomic Buffalo Turds)', 2, NULL, 0, 'Pimento Cheese Jalapeno Poppers (Atomic Buffalo Turds)', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Pimento-Cheese-Jalapeno-Poppers-ABT-72-e1580352593740-150x150.jpg', '', '', '10', '10', '20 minutes', '4', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 lb jalapenos, sliced lengthwise with seeds removed?#&1 lb bacon – precook the bacon for 3 minutes in microwave before placing on poppers?#&1/2 cup cream cheese?#&1/2 cup pimento cheese?#&dash bbq rub', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/pimento-cheese-jalapeno-poppers-atomic-buffalo-turds/', 'Grilled', 'ABT, atomic buffalo turds recipe, jalapeno poppers with bacon, cream cheese jalapeno, grilled jalapeno recipe, green mountain grills recipe, gmg jalapeno poppers recipe,', 'Jan 29, 2020', 'Appetizer', 'Instructions?#&?#&Place the cream cheese out so it can soften. Meanwhile, cut the tops off the jalapenos and slice them lengthwise in half, while also removing the seeds.?#&Microwave or cook the bacon so it is halfway done — this is about 3 minutes in the microwave.?#&Mix the cream cheese with the pimento cheese and add a generous scoop in each jalapeno.?#&Add a light dusting of bbq rub to the poppers.?#&Finish with a hearty piece of bacon on the top of the cheese mixture. This can be cut to fit.?#&Cook the jalapeno poppers at 350 degrees on your pellet smoker or grill for about 10 minutes or until the bottoms have begun to form nice char marks and the cheese has begun to melt.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'3016700667CC8141ABBB5B35E26765E5', X'88330581A1712D40BEB9213D40FE6EBB', X'88330581A1712D40BEB9213D40FE6EBB', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/alabama-white-sauce-chicken-wings/', 'Alabama White Sauce Chicken Wings', 2, NULL, 0, 'Alabama White Sauce Wings', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Alabama-White-Sauce-Chicken-wings-72dpi-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 min', '30 min', '35 minutes', '4', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 ¾ cups mayonnaise?#&¾ cup distilled white vinegar?#&½ cup apple juice?#&2 tsp prepared horseradish?#&1 tbsp fresh grated black pepper?#&Juice and zest of one lemon?#&1 tsp sea salt?#&Dash cayenne pepper?#&1 tsp sugar?#&Dash hot sauce?#&Dash smoked paprika, plus more for serving.', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/alabama-white-sauce-chicken-wings/', '', 'alabama white sauce, white bbq sauce recipe, chicken wings white sauce, mayo sauce, green mountain grills recipe idea, green mountain grills chicken wings, gmg recipe', 'Jan 29, 2020', 'Chicken Wings', 'Instructions?#&?#&Sauce Directions:?#&?#&Combine all ingredients in a pint sized mason jar, stir to combine, then shake to mix well. Can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.?#&?#&Grilling Directions:?#&?#&Preheat your pellet smoker to 350. Let chicken wings cook for about 25 minutes, then crank the smoker to 400 to get crispy skin. Use a thermapen or an internal read thermometer (if you use the Green Mountain Grill it comes with its own thermometer and it will tell you! I love that about this grill!) to test internal temperature – once the wings have reached an internal temperature of 170, pull them off the grill. Sprinkle with smoked paprika for color then drizzle with sauce before serving.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'5A5B21CA22D0C1499380460D7F03F412', X'F6F31614AE30B043A6009413F8760A3D', X'F6F31614AE30B043A6009413F8760A3D', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/citrus-and-herb-smoked-whole-snapper/', 'Citrus and Herb Smoked Whole Snapper', 2, NULL, 0, 'Citrus and Herb Smoked Whole Snapper', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/smoked-whole-snapper-1280x640-1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '10 minutes', '30 minutes', '40 minutes', '2', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 Whole Snapper, inside gizzards removed and de-scaled (have your butcher do this for you)?#&1 lemon, thinly sliced?#&1 lime, thinly sliced?#&2 garlic cloves, minced?#&1 small bunch thyme?#&½ tbsp olive oil?#&2 tsp sea salt?#&2 tsp fresh ground pepper', 'American, Seafood', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/citrus-and-herb-smoked-whole-snapper/', 'Smoked, Grilled', 'smoked snapper, how to smoke snapper, how to smoke fish', 'Jan 21, 2020', 'American, Seafood, Fish', 'Instructions?#&?#&1) Drizzle the insides of the snapper first with olive oil, then add the salt, pepper and garlic and spread in the inside of the cavity evenly.?#&?#&2) layer lemon and lime slices in the cavity starting from front to back and then add the thyme sprigs in the cavity. Save any remaining lemon and lime slices for serving with the fish once it’s cooked.?#&?#&3) Place the snapper on a frog mat and smoke until the internal temperature reaches 145 degrees- this will take anywhere from 45 minutes to an hour depending on the size of the fish.?#&?#&4) Once the internal temp has been met, remove and serve immediately with remaining lemon and lime slices. The outer filets will remove pretty cleanly for serving but be extra vigilant about looking for bones before serving guests.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'B92311291613124E91908F44C3CF1A69', X'69247ABD2BF5D94492E5291D0F32A75D', X'69247ABD2BF5D94492E5291D0F32A75D', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake/', 'Smoked S’mores Cheesecake', 2, NULL, 0, 'Smoked S’mores Cheesecake', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake-1280x640-1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '30 minutes', '1 hour and a half', '2 hours', '8', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Equipment:?#&?#&Springform cheesecake pan (2 parts)?#&?#&Crust:?#&?#&12 oz (1 cup and a half) graham crackers, pureed in food processor (If Keto, skip or use almond flour instead)?#&3 tbsp light brown sugar (if Keto, swap with Swerve Brown Sugar)?#&6 tbsp melted butter – coconut oil could also be used?#&?#&Filling:?#&?#&4– 8 oz (block) Neufchatel cheese, room temperature?#&1/3 cup light brown sugar (or if keto, swap with Swerve Brown Sugar)?#&2 tbsp maple syrup (if keto, swap with Choc Zero Maple Syrup)?#&1 tsp lemon zest?#&1 tbsp fresh lemon juice?#&2 tsp vanilla extract?#&1 tbsp butter, melted?#&5 large eggs?#&2/3 cup cold smoked 70% cocoa dark chocolate (cold smoking part is optional) (if Keto, swap with no sugar chocolate, such as Choc Zero Dark Chocolate)?#&1 cup small marshmallows (if Keto, use sugar free marshmallows or skip this ingredient)?#&?#&Plus, additional 1tbsp butter or coconut oil for coating the pan', 'American', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake/', 'Smoked, Grilled, Baked', 'Smoked Cheesecake Recipe, Smores Cheesecake Recipe, How to Smoke a Cheesecake, Traeger Smoked Cheesecake, Keto Cheesecake', 'Jan 20, 2020', 'Dessert, Cheesecake, Keto Cheesecake', 'Instructions?#&?#&Preheat your oven oven to 400 degrees (to bake the crust).?#&?#&Lightly oil your springform pan with a bit of coconut oil or butter. Pulse the graham crackers in the food processor until they have turned into crumbs. Add the brown sugar and gradually add the melted butter until mixed.?#&?#&Press the graham cracker crust into the pan, it will go up the side of the pan about 1/3 of the way, trying to make as even in thickness as possible. Bake for about 8 minutes or until lightly browned.?#&?#&Filling:?#&?#&In a food processor or stand mixer, combine the cream cheese, sugar, maple syrup, vanilla, lemon juice and zest. Gradually add the eggs slowly one by one until everything is well combined.?#&?#&Pour the batter in the springform pan.?#&?#&Smoke the cheesecake for 30 minutes – during this time, the top will become golden from the smoke. Meanwhile, turn the oven to 350 degrees. Remove the cheesecake from the smoker and place in oven and cook for an additional 45 minutes or until the middle no longer ripples when touching it. While cooking in the oven, the cake will expand much more and gain volume on the top that will eventually go back down as the cake continues to cook.?#&?#&Remove from the oven and let cool on the counter for 20 minutes, then transfer to the refrigerator and let the cake cool for a few hours until ready to serve.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'7A09CCE5181AE946AD5AB57FF8558A26', X'2BDA9C8165BCEE42B603938A1291C010', X'2BDA9C8165BCEE42B603938A1291C010', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/11/thanksgiving-big-green-egg-turkey-recipe/', 'Guide to Cooking Thanksgiving Turkey on a Big Green Egg', 2, NULL, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/11/thanksgiving-big-green-egg-turkey-recipe/', '', '', 'Nov 5, 2019', '', '');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'6025483C01DE7C4F9C5C5C1BF24B6212', X'22EB69EC6CD22349AA2EE81D12A3D9AC', X'22EB69EC6CD22349AA2EE81D12A3D9AC', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/10/grilled-chicken-for-3-easy-weeknight-meals-plus-keto-and-paleo-options/', 'Grilled Chicken for 3 Easy Weeknight Meals (Plus Keto and Paleo Options)', 2, NULL, 0, 'Grilled Chicken for 3 Easy Weeknight Dinners (Plus Keto and Paleo Options)', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chicken-thighs-on-the-grill72-150x150.jpg', '', '', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '35', '4 lbs grilled chicken', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Grilled Chicken + Salad Night:?#&?#&4 lbs boneless skinless chicken breast?#&1 container arugula?#&Olive oil, balsamic glaze, – or your favorite salad dressing for salad for night #1?#&Your favorite BBQ Rub, you can make your own with my ALL PURPOSE BBQ RUB RECIPE?#&?#&Taco Night:?#&?#&One pack of tortillas?#&1 large bunch Cilantro?#&4 Roma tomatoes?#&2 Avocados?#&?#&Pasta Night?#&?#&3 packages frozen zoodles OR 5 large zucchini that will need to be spiralized OR 1 box fettuccine noodles?#&1 1/2 cups Cream (paleo swap out: coconut cream or a nut butter)?#&1/2 cup Butter?#&1 ½ cups fresh grated Parmesan?#&2 cloves minced garlic', 'American', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/10/grilled-chicken-for-3-easy-weeknight-meals-plus-keto-and-paleo-options/', 'grill', 'grilled chicken for 3 nights of meals, grilled chicken tacos, grilled chicken alfredo, keto friendly chicken alfredo', 'Oct 25, 2019', 'american', 'Instructions?#&?#&Directions For Grilled Chicken:?#&?#&Fill your grill with Kingsford Charcoal Briquettes and prepare your grill for direct heat (charcoal spread out evenly on the bottom versus only on one side). If you would like to learn about how to start a charcoal grill or how to create direct and indirect zones on your grill they are part of my GRILL SCHOOL series which will teach you the fundamentals of grilling!?#&?#&Oil your grill grates with avocado oil or another high heat oil so your chicken doesn’t stick. Grill the chicken thighs on direct heat until the internal temperature reads 170 degrees as determined by an instant read thermometer like the Thermapen or the Thermopop.?#&?#&Remove the chicken from the grill and let rest before cutting into it. Serve with arugula salad and sliced heirloom tomatoes with a drizzle of balsamic glaze and olive oil on the first night. Reserve remaining chicken for dinner on night #2 and #3.?#&?#&Night 1: Chicken and Simple Arugula Salad?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Remove the chicken from the grill and let rest before cutting into it.?#&?#&Serve with arugula salad and sliced heirloom tomatoes with a drizzle of balsamic glaze and olive oil.?#&?#&If you eat carbs, you can easily throw in a grilled Texas Toast or bread to round out the mail. ?#&?#&Night 2: Chicken Tacos?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Reheat about 5-7 chicken thighs and tortillas in the toaster oven at 325. Serve with chopped cilantro, sour cream, and chopped tomatoes with your favorite hot sauce. Notes: Add black beans and rice to round out the meal if you have bigger appetites- this can be made in advance with canned beans and rice done in your rice cooker.?#&?#&Keto/Low Carb: Opt for low car tortillas OR use lettuce as your tortilla and pair with full fat sour cream?#&Paleo: Opt for grain free tortillas, such as almond, coconut or cassava tortillas from Siete foods, pair with coconut cream instead of sour cream?#&?#&Night 3: Cajun Chicken Alfredo ?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Boil noodles or pan fry your noodles until they are aldente. Meanwhile, make your sauce.?#&?#&Melt butter, and cream until it begins to simmer. Add the parmesan and let it continue to cook until the parm has melted.?#&?#&Add a tsp or more to taste of your favorite cajun seasoning.?#&?#&Keto: Your’e good to go- Alfredo sauce is naturally Keto (but pasta is not!) You’ll want to use zoodles or mirarcle noodles to be Keto, Low Carb or Paleo.?#&Paleo: You’re going to need to swap the cream with a nut milk and switch the Parmesan with nutritional yeast. The taste won’t be exactly the same but it will still be good. If you still use some parm it will be “paleoish” and still taste great!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'F6B19609EBF1F7409C2898201C27156E', X'56EAE105E46205449497FFF5F8BB8CA8', X'56EAE105E46205449497FFF5F8BB8CA8', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/09/keto-bbq-pork-pizzas/', 'Keto BBQ Pork Pizzas', 2, NULL, 0, 'Keto BBQ Pizzas', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/KETO-BBQ-PORK-Pizzas-72-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '4 personal pizzas', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 Smithfield Slow Roasted Golden Rotisserie Tenderloin?#&4 Low Carb Tortillas?#&1 cup sugar free, low carb BBQ sauce?#&1 cup shredded cheddar/mozzarella cheese?#&1 large bunch fresh oregano', 'American, BBQ', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/09/keto-bbq-pork-pizzas/', 'saute, bake', 'Keto BBQ Pizza, Keto BBQ Pork Pizza, Keto Pizza no fathead dough, keto pizza with low carb tortillas', 'Sep 9, 2019', 'American', 'Instructions?#&?#&Preheat oven to 375 degrees. While the oven preheats, slice the pork tenderloin into small, uniformly sized pieces.?#&Add a tbsp of coconut oil or avocado oil to a skillet and sauté the pork until it reaches an internal temp of 145 degrees; this should take 10 minutes or less.?#&While the pork is sautéing, toast the tortillas for 5 minutes.?#&Remove the tortillas, layer with BBQ sauce, cheese, and pork – equally divided among 4 pizzas.?#&Place pizzas back in the oven for 5 minutes or until the cheese has melted.?#&Remove the pizzas from the oven and garnish with fresh oregano and fresh pepper.?#&?#&Serve immediately!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'06BC5B9CDA114F4192CBEF3DDAE47695', X'96030B313A534C44B5934AACEC850479', X'96030B313A534C44B5934AACEC850479', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/07/cast-iron-grilled-mussels-in-a-white-wine-bacon-herb-butter-sauce/', 'Cast Iron Grilled Mussels in a White Wine, Bacon Herb Butter Sauce', 2, NULL, 0, 'Cast Iron Grilled Mussels in a White Wine, Bacon Herb Butter Sauce', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/DSC_016172-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '3', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 dozen mussels?#&2/3 cup Beringer Main and Vine Pinot Grigio?#&3 tbsp butter?#&1 strip bacon, partially cooked?#&1 small bunch of fresh thyme sprigs?#&4 cloves garlic, minced?#&Salt, to taste?#&1 tsp pepper', 'American, French', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/07/cast-iron-grilled-mussels-in-a-white-wine-bacon-herb-butter-sauce/', 'grill, cast iron', 'how to grill mussels, cast iron grilled mussels', 'Jul 26, 2019', 'american, grilled', 'Instructions?#&?#&Precook a slice of bacon so it is ¾ of the way cooked- this can easily be done in the microwave. Next, add the wine, butter, garlic, bacon (remove fatty parts of the bacon and chop before adding), thyme, salt and pepper.?#&?#&Add the mussels to the cast iron skillet and grill on direct heat over Kingsford Charcoal until the mussels open up- about 15 minutes or less. Serve with grilled or toasted crusty bread like ciabatta or French bread to sop up the white wine sauce.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'5EAD5CA90CC55B41878A72B15DF6C1B8', X'6F3AFD7769BB4D498734C1A621924C3F', X'6F3AFD7769BB4D498734C1A621924C3F', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/06/low-carb-char-siu-pork-belly-burnt-ends/', 'Low-Carb “Char Siu” Pork Belly Burnt Ends', 2, NULL, 0, 'Low Carb Char Siu Pork Belly Burnt Ends', 'Jon Solberg', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/85C2B6BE-A957-44D6-B29B-F77BB54698A1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '45 min', '3-5 hour', '4-6 hours', '6', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Aluminum foil 1/2 pan?#&Smoking wood of choice, I used four chunks of oak?#&3 lbs. skinless pork belly?#&1½ Tsp of kosher salt (Morton)?#&½ Tsp black pepper (restaurant grind)?#&1 Tbsp olive oil?#&?#&Char Siu sauce:?#&?#&4 Tbsp tamari?#&2 Tbsp natural smooth peanut butter?#&4 Tbsp Sukrin Gold sugar substitute, or whatever sugar substitute you like?#&1 Tbsp oyster sauce?#&4 Tsp rice wine?#&1 Tsp Smoked Paprika?#&3 Tsp sesame oil?#&1 Tsp Louisiana hot sauce?#&1 Tsp ginger powder?#&1 Tsp garlic powder?#&½ Tsp 5-spice powder', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/06/low-carb-char-siu-pork-belly-burnt-ends/', '', 'char siu, 5-spice, pork belly, pork, chinese bbq', 'Jun 6, 2019', '', 'Instructions?#&?#&Cut pork belly into 1” cubes. In a large bowl toss the cubes in the olive oil, salt, and pepper.?#&?#&Combine the remaining ingredients in a saucepan over medium-to-low heat and whisk together until everything is dissolved. Remove the pan from the heat.?#&?#&Set your Big Green Egg up for indirect cooking and get the temperature to 275° and the cooking grate level.?#&?#&Smoke the pork belly with the fat side down until the cubes reach an internal temperature of around 190°f.   This will take around 2-3 hours.?#&?#&Try using a Thermapen for a precise temperature reading.?#&?#&Remove the cubes from the smoker and place in the aluminum ½ pan.?#&?#&Toss in the Char Sui sauce. Coat the cubes well then return to the smoker.?#&?#&Continue to cook uncovered for an additional hour or until the sauce has reduced.?#&?#&Plate and enjoy!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'6A3A27668CCD564980AD3570AE7CAF4E', X'EB70C265418F6047895948B915C204BE', X'EB70C265418F6047895948B915C204BE', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/fire-roasted-poblano-queso-dip/', 'Fire Roasted Poblano Queso Dip', 2, NULL, 0, 'Fire Roasted Poblano Queso', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/smoked-poblano-queso-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '8', 'Ingredients?#&?#&16 oz Velveeta Queso Blanco (you need to use Velveeta in this recipe because of the way it melts)?#&1 poblano pepper?#&1 roma tomato, sliced in half lengthwise?#&dash smoked paprika?#&large bunch cilantro, added at the end', 'American, Mexican', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/fire-roasted-poblano-queso-dip/', 'Grill', 'smoked cheese dip, smoked queso, smoked poblano queso dip, velveeta mexican dip recipe, cheese dip on pellet smoker', 'Jan 30, 2020', 'Appetizer', 'Instructions?#&?#&Put the Velveeta in a grill safe bowl or cast iron pot. Preheat your grill to 350 degrees.?#&Add the cast iron pot, and let the poblano and tomato roast on the grill.?#&When the cheese has completely melted, and the poblano has begun to char, remove the poblano and tomato.?#&Roughly slice vegetables, and add to the cheese, stirring to combine.?#&Remove the cheese dip from the grill and roughly chop the cilantro and place as garnish on top.?#&Serve with tortilla chips. Or if you are eating low carb, try it with pork rinds.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'2D674F7015A32C4693EA43227EA73EBB', X'04262235442C8144A08C05BFF423CAB0', X'04262235442C8144A08C05BFF423CAB0', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/pimento-cheese-jalapeno-poppers-atomic-buffalo-turds/', 'Pimento Cheese Jalapeno Poppers (Atomic Buffalo Turds)', 2, NULL, 0, 'Pimento Cheese Jalapeno Poppers (Atomic Buffalo Turds)', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Pimento-Cheese-Jalapeno-Poppers-ABT-72-e1580352593740-150x150.jpg', '', '', '10', '10', '20 minutes', '4', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 lb jalapenos, sliced lengthwise with seeds removed?#&1 lb bacon – precook the bacon for 3 minutes in microwave before placing on poppers?#&1/2 cup cream cheese?#&1/2 cup pimento cheese?#&dash bbq rub', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/pimento-cheese-jalapeno-poppers-atomic-buffalo-turds/', 'Grilled', 'ABT, atomic buffalo turds recipe, jalapeno poppers with bacon, cream cheese jalapeno, grilled jalapeno recipe, green mountain grills recipe, gmg jalapeno poppers recipe,', 'Jan 29, 2020', 'Appetizer', 'Instructions?#&?#&Place the cream cheese out so it can soften. Meanwhile, cut the tops off the jalapenos and slice them lengthwise in half, while also removing the seeds.?#&Microwave or cook the bacon so it is halfway done — this is about 3 minutes in the microwave.?#&Mix the cream cheese with the pimento cheese and add a generous scoop in each jalapeno.?#&Add a light dusting of bbq rub to the poppers.?#&Finish with a hearty piece of bacon on the top of the cheese mixture. This can be cut to fit.?#&Cook the jalapeno poppers at 350 degrees on your pellet smoker or grill for about 10 minutes or until the bottoms have begun to form nice char marks and the cheese has begun to melt.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'5DB42EF7D27AF04A9C5196380E33754B', X'218446FF2AAE03418D92BD4A4BFB97EF', X'218446FF2AAE03418D92BD4A4BFB97EF', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/alabama-white-sauce-chicken-wings/', 'Alabama White Sauce Chicken Wings', 2, NULL, 0, 'Alabama White Sauce Wings', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Alabama-White-Sauce-Chicken-wings-72dpi-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 min', '30 min', '35 minutes', '4', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 ¾ cups mayonnaise?#&¾ cup distilled white vinegar?#&½ cup apple juice?#&2 tsp prepared horseradish?#&1 tbsp fresh grated black pepper?#&Juice and zest of one lemon?#&1 tsp sea salt?#&Dash cayenne pepper?#&1 tsp sugar?#&Dash hot sauce?#&Dash smoked paprika, plus more for serving.', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/alabama-white-sauce-chicken-wings/', '', 'alabama white sauce, white bbq sauce recipe, chicken wings white sauce, mayo sauce, green mountain grills recipe idea, green mountain grills chicken wings, gmg recipe', 'Jan 29, 2020', 'Chicken Wings', 'Instructions?#&?#&Sauce Directions:?#&?#&Combine all ingredients in a pint sized mason jar, stir to combine, then shake to mix well. Can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.?#&?#&Grilling Directions:?#&?#&Preheat your pellet smoker to 350. Let chicken wings cook for about 25 minutes, then crank the smoker to 400 to get crispy skin. Use a thermapen or an internal read thermometer (if you use the Green Mountain Grill it comes with its own thermometer and it will tell you! I love that about this grill!) to test internal temperature – once the wings have reached an internal temperature of 170, pull them off the grill. Sprinkle with smoked paprika for color then drizzle with sauce before serving.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'1E7C1F7AC0859940A5C2894EB89B61DD', X'30FDDC6B35D2D6478FFBF45639AE33A2', X'30FDDC6B35D2D6478FFBF45639AE33A2', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/citrus-and-herb-smoked-whole-snapper/', 'Citrus and Herb Smoked Whole Snapper', 2, NULL, 0, 'Citrus and Herb Smoked Whole Snapper', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/smoked-whole-snapper-1280x640-1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '10 minutes', '30 minutes', '40 minutes', '2', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 Whole Snapper, inside gizzards removed and de-scaled (have your butcher do this for you)?#&1 lemon, thinly sliced?#&1 lime, thinly sliced?#&2 garlic cloves, minced?#&1 small bunch thyme?#&½ tbsp olive oil?#&2 tsp sea salt?#&2 tsp fresh ground pepper', 'American, Seafood', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/citrus-and-herb-smoked-whole-snapper/', 'Smoked, Grilled', 'smoked snapper, how to smoke snapper, how to smoke fish', 'Jan 21, 2020', 'American, Seafood, Fish', 'Instructions?#&?#&1) Drizzle the insides of the snapper first with olive oil, then add the salt, pepper and garlic and spread in the inside of the cavity evenly.?#&?#&2) layer lemon and lime slices in the cavity starting from front to back and then add the thyme sprigs in the cavity. Save any remaining lemon and lime slices for serving with the fish once it’s cooked.?#&?#&3) Place the snapper on a frog mat and smoke until the internal temperature reaches 145 degrees- this will take anywhere from 45 minutes to an hour depending on the size of the fish.?#&?#&4) Once the internal temp has been met, remove and serve immediately with remaining lemon and lime slices. The outer filets will remove pretty cleanly for serving but be extra vigilant about looking for bones before serving guests.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'02E876B4C5C4774BBEDD81FC5517A7E4', X'B9C95381AD46134D87FD5A22630A48FC', X'B9C95381AD46134D87FD5A22630A48FC', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake/', 'Smoked S’mores Cheesecake', 2, NULL, 0, 'Smoked S’mores Cheesecake', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake-1280x640-1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '30 minutes', '1 hour and a half', '2 hours', '8', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Equipment:?#&?#&Springform cheesecake pan (2 parts)?#&?#&Crust:?#&?#&12 oz (1 cup and a half) graham crackers, pureed in food processor (If Keto, skip or use almond flour instead)?#&3 tbsp light brown sugar (if Keto, swap with Swerve Brown Sugar)?#&6 tbsp melted butter – coconut oil could also be used?#&?#&Filling:?#&?#&4– 8 oz (block) Neufchatel cheese, room temperature?#&1/3 cup light brown sugar (or if keto, swap with Swerve Brown Sugar)?#&2 tbsp maple syrup (if keto, swap with Choc Zero Maple Syrup)?#&1 tsp lemon zest?#&1 tbsp fresh lemon juice?#&2 tsp vanilla extract?#&1 tbsp butter, melted?#&5 large eggs?#&2/3 cup cold smoked 70% cocoa dark chocolate (cold smoking part is optional) (if Keto, swap with no sugar chocolate, such as Choc Zero Dark Chocolate)?#&1 cup small marshmallows (if Keto, use sugar free marshmallows or skip this ingredient)?#&?#&Plus, additional 1tbsp butter or coconut oil for coating the pan', 'American', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/campfire-smores-cheesecake/', 'Smoked, Grilled, Baked', 'Smoked Cheesecake Recipe, Smores Cheesecake Recipe, How to Smoke a Cheesecake, Traeger Smoked Cheesecake, Keto Cheesecake', 'Jan 20, 2020', 'Dessert, Cheesecake, Keto Cheesecake', 'Instructions?#&?#&Preheat your oven oven to 400 degrees (to bake the crust).?#&?#&Lightly oil your springform pan with a bit of coconut oil or butter. Pulse the graham crackers in the food processor until they have turned into crumbs. Add the brown sugar and gradually add the melted butter until mixed.?#&?#&Press the graham cracker crust into the pan, it will go up the side of the pan about 1/3 of the way, trying to make as even in thickness as possible. Bake for about 8 minutes or until lightly browned.?#&?#&Filling:?#&?#&In a food processor or stand mixer, combine the cream cheese, sugar, maple syrup, vanilla, lemon juice and zest. Gradually add the eggs slowly one by one until everything is well combined.?#&?#&Pour the batter in the springform pan.?#&?#&Smoke the cheesecake for 30 minutes – during this time, the top will become golden from the smoke. Meanwhile, turn the oven to 350 degrees. Remove the cheesecake from the smoker and place in oven and cook for an additional 45 minutes or until the middle no longer ripples when touching it. While cooking in the oven, the cake will expand much more and gain volume on the top that will eventually go back down as the cake continues to cook.?#&?#&Remove from the oven and let cool on the counter for 20 minutes, then transfer to the refrigerator and let the cake cool for a few hours until ready to serve.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'765B51A5584C254BBA6BD9D92DCD2E21', X'C6A310BB075A5641A5E829827B49F947', X'C6A310BB075A5641A5E829827B49F947', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/11/thanksgiving-big-green-egg-turkey-recipe/', 'Guide to Cooking Thanksgiving Turkey on a Big Green Egg', 2, NULL, 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/11/thanksgiving-big-green-egg-turkey-recipe/', '', '', 'Nov 5, 2019', '', '');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'AE6CC591E390C04F88925B50281267FE', X'46A3AD773BEE714ABD38E1138BFBD494', X'46A3AD773BEE714ABD38E1138BFBD494', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/10/grilled-chicken-for-3-easy-weeknight-meals-plus-keto-and-paleo-options/', 'Grilled Chicken for 3 Easy Weeknight Meals (Plus Keto and Paleo Options)', 2, NULL, 0, 'Grilled Chicken for 3 Easy Weeknight Dinners (Plus Keto and Paleo Options)', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/chicken-thighs-on-the-grill72-150x150.jpg', '', '', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '35', '4 lbs grilled chicken', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Grilled Chicken + Salad Night:?#&?#&4 lbs boneless skinless chicken breast?#&1 container arugula?#&Olive oil, balsamic glaze, – or your favorite salad dressing for salad for night #1?#&Your favorite BBQ Rub, you can make your own with my ALL PURPOSE BBQ RUB RECIPE?#&?#&Taco Night:?#&?#&One pack of tortillas?#&1 large bunch Cilantro?#&4 Roma tomatoes?#&2 Avocados?#&?#&Pasta Night?#&?#&3 packages frozen zoodles OR 5 large zucchini that will need to be spiralized OR 1 box fettuccine noodles?#&1 1/2 cups Cream (paleo swap out: coconut cream or a nut butter)?#&1/2 cup Butter?#&1 ½ cups fresh grated Parmesan?#&2 cloves minced garlic', 'American', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/10/grilled-chicken-for-3-easy-weeknight-meals-plus-keto-and-paleo-options/', 'grill', 'grilled chicken for 3 nights of meals, grilled chicken tacos, grilled chicken alfredo, keto friendly chicken alfredo', 'Oct 25, 2019', 'american', 'Instructions?#&?#&Directions For Grilled Chicken:?#&?#&Fill your grill with Kingsford Charcoal Briquettes and prepare your grill for direct heat (charcoal spread out evenly on the bottom versus only on one side). If you would like to learn about how to start a charcoal grill or how to create direct and indirect zones on your grill they are part of my GRILL SCHOOL series which will teach you the fundamentals of grilling!?#&?#&Oil your grill grates with avocado oil or another high heat oil so your chicken doesn’t stick. Grill the chicken thighs on direct heat until the internal temperature reads 170 degrees as determined by an instant read thermometer like the Thermapen or the Thermopop.?#&?#&Remove the chicken from the grill and let rest before cutting into it. Serve with arugula salad and sliced heirloom tomatoes with a drizzle of balsamic glaze and olive oil on the first night. Reserve remaining chicken for dinner on night #2 and #3.?#&?#&Night 1: Chicken and Simple Arugula Salad?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Remove the chicken from the grill and let rest before cutting into it.?#&?#&Serve with arugula salad and sliced heirloom tomatoes with a drizzle of balsamic glaze and olive oil.?#&?#&If you eat carbs, you can easily throw in a grilled Texas Toast or bread to round out the mail. ?#&?#&Night 2: Chicken Tacos?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Reheat about 5-7 chicken thighs and tortillas in the toaster oven at 325. Serve with chopped cilantro, sour cream, and chopped tomatoes with your favorite hot sauce. Notes: Add black beans and rice to round out the meal if you have bigger appetites- this can be made in advance with canned beans and rice done in your rice cooker.?#&?#&Keto/Low Carb: Opt for low car tortillas OR use lettuce as your tortilla and pair with full fat sour cream?#&Paleo: Opt for grain free tortillas, such as almond, coconut or cassava tortillas from Siete foods, pair with coconut cream instead of sour cream?#&?#&Night 3: Cajun Chicken Alfredo ?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Boil noodles or pan fry your noodles until they are aldente. Meanwhile, make your sauce.?#&?#&Melt butter, and cream until it begins to simmer. Add the parmesan and let it continue to cook until the parm has melted.?#&?#&Add a tsp or more to taste of your favorite cajun seasoning.?#&?#&Keto: Your’e good to go- Alfredo sauce is naturally Keto (but pasta is not!) You’ll want to use zoodles or mirarcle noodles to be Keto, Low Carb or Paleo.?#&Paleo: You’re going to need to swap the cream with a nut milk and switch the Parmesan with nutritional yeast. The taste won’t be exactly the same but it will still be good. If you still use some parm it will be “paleoish” and still taste great!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'D6D00D5F0FB19C4CA91F831C1A7D5D33', X'42595A9D77D6004FA19E0E4219211747', X'42595A9D77D6004FA19E0E4219211747', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/09/keto-bbq-pork-pizzas/', 'Keto BBQ Pork Pizzas', 2, NULL, 0, 'Keto BBQ Pizzas', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/KETO-BBQ-PORK-Pizzas-72-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '4 personal pizzas', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 Smithfield Slow Roasted Golden Rotisserie Tenderloin?#&4 Low Carb Tortillas?#&1 cup sugar free, low carb BBQ sauce?#&1 cup shredded cheddar/mozzarella cheese?#&1 large bunch fresh oregano', 'American, BBQ', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/09/keto-bbq-pork-pizzas/', 'saute, bake', 'Keto BBQ Pizza, Keto BBQ Pork Pizza, Keto Pizza no fathead dough, keto pizza with low carb tortillas', 'Sep 9, 2019', 'American', 'Instructions?#&?#&Preheat oven to 375 degrees. While the oven preheats, slice the pork tenderloin into small, uniformly sized pieces.?#&Add a tbsp of coconut oil or avocado oil to a skillet and sauté the pork until it reaches an internal temp of 145 degrees; this should take 10 minutes or less.?#&While the pork is sautéing, toast the tortillas for 5 minutes.?#&Remove the tortillas, layer with BBQ sauce, cheese, and pork – equally divided among 4 pizzas.?#&Place pizzas back in the oven for 5 minutes or until the cheese has melted.?#&Remove the pizzas from the oven and garnish with fresh oregano and fresh pepper.?#&?#&Serve immediately!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'3B9F59707F83D24DB6FCE30E9E96A24F', X'BAFC4231B906BC4CBBBBB99443EF1FC9', X'BAFC4231B906BC4CBBBBB99443EF1FC9', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/07/cast-iron-grilled-mussels-in-a-white-wine-bacon-herb-butter-sauce/', 'Cast Iron Grilled Mussels in a White Wine, Bacon Herb Butter Sauce', 2, NULL, 0, 'Cast Iron Grilled Mussels in a White Wine, Bacon Herb Butter Sauce', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/DSC_016172-150x150.jpg', '', '', '5 minutes', '15 minutes', '20 minutes', '3', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 dozen mussels?#&2/3 cup Beringer Main and Vine Pinot Grigio?#&3 tbsp butter?#&1 strip bacon, partially cooked?#&1 small bunch of fresh thyme sprigs?#&4 cloves garlic, minced?#&Salt, to taste?#&1 tsp pepper', 'American, French', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/07/cast-iron-grilled-mussels-in-a-white-wine-bacon-herb-butter-sauce/', 'grill, cast iron', 'how to grill mussels, cast iron grilled mussels', 'Jul 26, 2019', 'american, grilled', 'Instructions?#&?#&Precook a slice of bacon so it is ¾ of the way cooked- this can easily be done in the microwave. Next, add the wine, butter, garlic, bacon (remove fatty parts of the bacon and chop before adding), thyme, salt and pepper.?#&?#&Add the mussels to the cast iron skillet and grill on direct heat over Kingsford Charcoal until the mussels open up- about 15 minutes or less. Serve with grilled or toasted crusty bread like ciabatta or French bread to sop up the white wine sauce.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'B8EC7619847FE5428E20DE7251442F0A', X'72886E5A1B917840A18623C6A6DE2606', X'72886E5A1B917840A18623C6A6DE2606', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/06/low-carb-char-siu-pork-belly-burnt-ends/', 'Low-Carb “Char Siu” Pork Belly Burnt Ends', 2, NULL, 0, 'Low Carb Char Siu Pork Belly Burnt Ends', 'Jon Solberg', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/85C2B6BE-A957-44D6-B29B-F77BB54698A1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '45 min', '3-5 hour', '4-6 hours', '6', 'Ingredients?#&?#&Aluminum foil 1/2 pan?#&Smoking wood of choice, I used four chunks of oak?#&3 lbs. skinless pork belly?#&1½ Tsp of kosher salt (Morton)?#&½ Tsp black pepper (restaurant grind)?#&1 Tbsp olive oil?#&?#&Char Siu sauce:?#&?#&4 Tbsp tamari?#&2 Tbsp natural smooth peanut butter?#&4 Tbsp Sukrin Gold sugar substitute, or whatever sugar substitute you like?#&1 Tbsp oyster sauce?#&4 Tsp rice wine?#&1 Tsp Smoked Paprika?#&3 Tsp sesame oil?#&1 Tsp Louisiana hot sauce?#&1 Tsp ginger powder?#&1 Tsp garlic powder?#&½ Tsp 5-spice powder', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/06/low-carb-char-siu-pork-belly-burnt-ends/', '', 'char siu, 5-spice, pork belly, pork, chinese bbq', 'Jun 6, 2019', '', 'Instructions?#&?#&Cut pork belly into 1” cubes. In a large bowl toss the cubes in the olive oil, salt, and pepper.?#&?#&Combine the remaining ingredients in a saucepan over medium-to-low heat and whisk together until everything is dissolved. Remove the pan from the heat.?#&?#&Set your Big Green Egg up for indirect cooking and get the temperature to 275° and the cooking grate level.?#&?#&Smoke the pork belly with the fat side down until the cubes reach an internal temperature of around 190°f.   This will take around 2-3 hours.?#&?#&Try using a Thermapen for a precise temperature reading.?#&?#&Remove the cubes from the smoker and place in the aluminum ½ pan.?#&?#&Toss in the Char Sui sauce. Coat the cubes well then return to the smoker.?#&?#&Continue to cook uncovered for an additional hour or until the sauce has reduced.?#&?#&Plate and enjoy!');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'6191A522B0F8744BABE74683E1B8BA0B', X'5D1564FF5CF2EC41A8317714D320A107', X'5D1564FF5CF2EC41A8317714D320A107', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/citrus-and-herb-smoked-whole-snapper/', 'Citrus and Herb Smoked Whole Snapper', 2, NULL, 0, 'Citrus and Herb Smoked Whole Snapper', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/smoked-whole-snapper-1280x640-1-150x150.jpg', '', '', '10 minutes', '30 minutes', '40 minutes', '2', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 Whole Snapper, inside gizzards removed and de-scaled (have your butcher do this for you)?#&1 lemon, thinly sliced?#&1 lime, thinly sliced?#&2 garlic cloves, minced?#&1 small bunch thyme?#&½ tbsp olive oil?#&2 tsp sea salt?#&2 tsp fresh ground pepper', 'American, Seafood', 'https://grillgirl.com/2020/01/citrus-and-herb-smoked-whole-snapper/', 'Smoked, Grilled', 'smoked snapper, how to smoke snapper, how to smoke fish', 'Jan 21, 2020', 'American, Seafood, Fish', 'Instructions?#&?#&1) Drizzle the insides of the snapper first with olive oil, then add the salt, pepper and garlic and spread in the inside of the cavity evenly.?#&?#&2) layer lemon and lime slices in the cavity starting from front to back and then add the thyme sprigs in the cavity. Save any remaining lemon and lime slices for serving with the fish once it’s cooked.?#&?#&3) Place the snapper on a frog mat and smoke until the internal temperature reaches 145 degrees- this will take anywhere from 45 minutes to an hour depending on the size of the fish.?#&?#&4) Once the internal temp has been met, remove and serve immediately with remaining lemon and lime slices. The outer filets will remove pretty cleanly for serving but be extra vigilant about looking for bones before serving guests.');
INSERT INTO `VWR INTERNAL Grillgirl recipeLink` (row_id, parent_row_id, out_parent_row_id, source_index, template_url, template_content_value, status, status_message, segment, name, author, image, aggregateRating, aggregateCount, prepTime, cookTime, totalTime, recipeYield, recipeIngredientHTML, recipeCuisine, url, recipeMethod, Keywords, dateModified, recipeCategory, recipeInstructionnsHTML) VALUES (X'D5AB55231513E84EB419AB412C6DBBA4', X'54EF7F8653600249A1702687E02FB1BF', X'54EF7F8653600249A1702687E02FB1BF', 0, 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/12/castironporktenderloin/', 'Cast Iron Pork Tenderloin with Apple Kale Chutney', 2, NULL, 0, 'Cast Iron Pork Tenderloin with Apple Kale Chutney', 'Robyn', 'https://grillgirl.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Cast-Iron-Pork-Tenderloin-with-apple-kale-chutney-wide72-150x150.jpg', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Ingredients?#&?#&1 Smithfield Roasted Garlic & Cracked Black Pepper Marinated Fresh Pork Tenderloin?#&¼ cup butter?#&3 cups chopped kale, stems removed?#&2 cups chopped apple (approximately 2 large apples)?#&1 dash cinnamon?#&1 dash ginger?#&¼ cup craisins or sweetened dried cranberries (golden raisins can be substituted too)?#&½ cup candied walnuts', '', 'https://grillgirl.com/2019/12/castironporktenderloin/', '', '', 'Dec 13, 2019', '', 'Instructions?#&?#&Directions:?#&?#&Preheat your oven to 375 degrees F. Heat your cast iron to medium-high heat and melt the butter. Sear the pork tenderloin on one side until browned, about two minutes, and then flip and brown the other side. Add the kale, apples and craisins, and stir to combine.?#&?#&Transfer your cast iron pan to the oven and let the pork tenderloin roast until it reaches an internal temperature of 145 degrees. Remove the cast iron from the oven and add the walnuts to the apple kale chutney. Slice the pork and serve with the chutney. Prepared to be surprised how quickly your kids will eat their veggies with this sweet and savory dish!');
